Text:"<s1384>1ST READING: </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>Sam:17: 32-50</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the First book of Samuel </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>David said to Saul, 'Let no one lose heart on his account; your servant will go and fight this Philistine'. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>But Saul answered David, 'You cannot go and fight the Philistine;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> you are only a boy and he has been a warrior from his youth'.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>David said to Saul, 'Your servant used to look after the sheep for his father </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and whenever a lion or a bear came out and took a sheep from the flock, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>I used to follow him up and strike him down and rescue it from his mouth;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> if he turned on me I seized him by  the hair at his jaw and struck him down and killed him.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Your servant has killed both lion and bear, and this uncircumcised Philistine shall be like one of them, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>for he has dared to insult the armies of the living God,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Yahweh who rescued me from the claws of lion and bear' David said, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>'will rescue me from the power of this Philistine.' Then Saul said to David, 'Go, and Yahweh be with you!\"</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Saul made David put on his own armour and put a bronze helmet on his head and gave  him a breastplate to wear, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and over David's armour he buckled his own sword;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> but not  being used to these things David found he could not walk. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>\"I cannot walk with these, 'he said to Saul 'I am not used to them. 'So they took them off again. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>He took his staff in his hand, picked five smooth stones from the river bed,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> put them in his shepherd's bag, in his pouch, and with his sling in his hand he went to meet the Philistine.  </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The Philistine, his shield-bearer in front of him, came nearer and nearer to David;</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> and the Philistine looked at David, and what he saw filled him with scorn, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>because David was only a youth, a boy of fresh complexion and pleasant bearing. </s>"},{ID:9,Style:{Background:{BodyRect:"0,0,10000,9300"}},
Text:"<s1384>The Philistine said to him, \"Am I a dog for you to come against me with sticks?!\"</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>And the Philistine cursed David by his gods. The Philistine said to David,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> \"Come over here and I will give your fresh to the birds of the air and the beasts of the field.'</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>But David answered the Philistine, \"You come against me with sword and spear and javelin,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> but I come against you in the name of Yahweh Sabaoth, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>the God of the armies of Israel that you have dared to insult. </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Today Yahweh will deliver you into my hand and I shall kill you. I will cut off you head, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>and this very day I will give your dead body and the bodies of the Philistine </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>army to the birds of the air and the wild beasts of the earth,</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> so that all the earth may know that there is a </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>God in Israel, and that all this assembly may know that it is not by sword or by spear that Yahweh gives the victory,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384> for Yahweh is lord  of the battle and he will deliver you into our power\". </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>No sooner had the Philistine started forward to confront David than David left the line of battle and ran to meet the Philistine.</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384> Putting his hand in his bag, he took out a stone and slung it and struck the </s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>Philistine on the forehead; the stone penetrated his forehead and he fell on his face to the ground. </s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>Thus David triumphed over the Philistine with a sling and a stone and struck the Philistine down and killed him. </s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>David had no sword in his hand. </s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>Word of the Lord. </s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"1ST READING"},{Guid:"RoXv7GGpskqSJ0msLlzJvg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>KUFUFUKA KWA BWANA MWAKA C</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384> 								Mwanzo 22:1-18</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Somo katika kitabu cha Mwanzo</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Siku zile: Mungu alimjaribu Abrahamu, akamwambia: \"Abrahamu!\"</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Naye akaitika, \"Mimi hapa!\" Mungu akasema: \"Umtwae mwanao Isaka, mwanao wa pekee umpendaye,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> uende katika nchi ya Moria, na huko utamtoa sadaka ya kuteketezwa juu ya mlima nitakaokuonyesha.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>\" Abrahamu akaamka asubuhi mapema, akatandika punda wake, akawachukua wawili kati ya watumishi wake, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>na mwanawe Isaka. Akapasua kuni za sadaka, akaondoka kwenda mahali pale alipoambiwa na Mungu.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Siku ya tatu, Abrahamu akainua macho, akaona mahali pale kwa mbali. Abrahamu akawaambia watumishi wake, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>\"Ngojeni hapa na punda. Mimi na mwanangu tutakwenda mpaka kule, tutaabudu, na kurudi kwenu.\" </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Abrahamu akatwaa kuni za sadaka, akamtwika Isaka mwanawe; yeye mwenyewe akachukua moto na kisu mkononi, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>wakaenda wote wawili pamoja. Isaka akamwambia baba yake, \"Babangu!\" Akajibu, \"Kuna nini, mwanangu?\"</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> Isaka akaongeza, \"Tazama, tunao moto na kuni lakini yuko wapi mwanakondoo wa sadaka?\" Abrahamu akajibu,</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> \"Mungu atatupatia mwanakondoo wa sadaka, mwanangu.\"
Nao wakaendelea wote wawili pamoja. Walipofika mahali pale alipoambiwa na Mungu, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Abrahamu akajenga hapo altare akapanga kuni, kisha akamfunga mwanawe Isaka, akamweka juu ya altare, juu ya kuni zile. </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Abrahamu akanyosha mkono, akashika kisu amchinje mwanawe.</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>Lakini malaika wa Bwana akamwita toka mbinguni, akasema, \"Abrahamu! Abrahamu!\" Naye akaitika, \"Mimi hapa!\"</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>Malaika akasema, \"Usimnyoshee mtoto mkono wako! Usimtende neno lolote! Sasa najua ya kuwa unamheshimu Mungu: </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>hukunikatalia mwanao, mwanao wa pekee.\" Abrahamu akainua macho, akaona kondoo dume, amenaswa kichakani kwa pembe zake. </s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>Abrahamu akaenda akamchukua kondoo, akamtoa sadaka ya kuteketezwa badala ya mwanawe.</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384> Mahali pale Abrahamu akapaita jina lake: Yahweh-yire, kama isemwavyo hata leo, \"Juu ya mlima, Bwana atajalia.\"</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>Malaika wa Bwana akamwita Abrahamu mara ya pili kutoka mbinguni, akasema, \"Naapa kwa nafsi yangu, asema Bwana: </s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>kwa kuwa umefanya jambo hilo, wala hukunikatalia mwanao, mwanao wa pekee,</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384> mimi nitakujaza baraka, nitaufanya uzao wako kuwa mwingi kama nyota za mbinguni na kama mchanga ulioko pwani ya bahari,</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384> tena uzao wako utashinda mlango wa maadui wake. Katika uzao wako mataifa yote ya dunia yatajipatia baraka, kwa sababu umetii sauti yangu.\"</s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384>Neno la Bwana.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
