Text:"Glory be to God"},{Guid:"EgqhefGqHEOCPV5eR1zwrQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>The passion of our Lord Jesus Christ according to Luke</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: the elders of the people both chief priests and scribes,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>arose, and brought Jesus before Pirate. And they began to accuse him saying,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>S. “We found this man perverting our nation, and forbidding us to give tribute to Caesar, and saying that he himself is Christ a king.”</s>"},{ID:70,
Text:"<s1384>N. And Pilate asked him, </s>"},{ID:71,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Are you the King of the Jews?”</s>"},{ID:72,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he answered him,
	“You have said so.”</s>"},{ID:73,
Text:"<s1384>N.  And Pilate said to the chief priests and the multitudes, </s>"},{ID:74,
Text:"<s1384>S.  “I find no crime in this man.”</s>"},{ID:75,
Text:"<s1384>N. But they were urgent, saying, </s>"},{ID:76,
Text:"<s1384>S. “He stirs up the people, teaching throughout all Judea, from Galilee even to this place.”</s>"},{ID:77,
Text:"<s1384>N.  When Pilate heard this, he asked whether the man was a Galilean. </s>"},{ID:78,
Text:"<s1384> And when he learned that he belonged to Herod’s jurisdiction, he sent him over to Herod,</s>"},{ID:78,
Text:"<s1384> who was himself in Jerusalem at that time.
When Herod saw Jesus, </s>"},{ID:79,
Text:"<s1384>he was very glad, for he had long desired to see him, because he had heard about him,</s>"},{ID:79,
Text:"<s1384> and he was hoping to see some sign done by him. </s>"},{ID:80,
Text:"<s1384>So he questioned him at some length; but he made no answer.
The chief priests and the scribes stood by,</s>"},{ID:80,
Text:"<s1384> vehemently accusing him. And Herod with his soldiers treated him with contempt and mocked him; then, </s>"},{ID:81,
Text:"<s1384>clothing him in gorgeous apparel, he sent him back to Pilate.</s>"},{ID:81,
Text:"<s1384>And Herod and Pilate became friends with each other that very day, for before this they had been at enmity with each other.</s>"},{ID:82,
Text:"<s1384>Pilate then called together the chief priests and the rulers and the people, and said to them,</s>"},{ID:82,
Text:"<s1384>S. “You brought me this man as one who was perverting the people; and after examining him before you,</s>"},{ID:83,
Text:"<s1384> behold, I did not find this man guilty of any of your charges against him; neither did Herod,</s>"},{ID:84,
Text:"<s1384> for he sent him back to us.  Behold, nothing deserving death has been done by him; I will therefore chastise him and release him.”</s>"},{ID:85,
Text:"<s1384>N. But they all cried out together, </s>"},{ID:86,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Away with this man, and release to us Barabbas” – </s>"},{ID:87,
Text:"<s1384>N. a man who had been thrown into prison for an insurrection started in the city, and for murder.</s>"},{ID:88,
Text:"<s1384>Pilate addressed them once more, desiring to release Jesus; but they shouted out,</s>"},{ID:89,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Crucify, crucify him!”</s>"},{ID:90,
Text:"<s1384>N. A third time he said to them, </s>"},{ID:91,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Why, what evil has he done?
I have found in him no crime deserving death; I will therefore chastise him and release him.”</s>"},{ID:92,
Text:"<s1384>N. But they were urgent, demanding with loud cries that he should be crucified.</s>"},{ID:93,
Text:"<s1384>And their voices prevailed.  So Pilate gave sentence that their demand should be granted. </s>"},{ID:94,
Text:"<s1384> He released the man who had been thrown into prison for insurrection and murder, whom they asked for; but Jesus he delivered up to their will.</s>"},{ID:95,
Text:"<s1384>And as they led him away, they seized one Simon of Cyrene, who was coming in from the country, and laid on him the cross, to carry it behind Jesus.  </s>"},{ID:96,
Text:"<s1384>And there followed him a great multitude of the people, and of women who bewailed and lamented him.  But Jesus turning to them said, </s>"},{ID:97,
Text:"<s1384>“Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your children. For behold, the days are coming when they will say, </s>"},{ID:98,
Text:"<s1384>‘Blessed are the barren, and the womb that never bore, and the breasts that never nursed!”</s>"},{ID:99,
Text:"<s1384>Then they will begin to say to the mountains, ‘Fall on us’; and to the hills, ‘Cover us.’</s>"},{ID:100,
Text:"<s1384>For if they do this when the wood is green, what will happen when it is dry?”</s>"},{ID:101,
Text:"<s1384>N. Two others also, who were criminals, were led away to be put to death with him.  And when they came to the place which is called The Skull, there they crucified him, </s>"},{ID:102,
Text:"<s1384>and the criminals, one on the right and one on the left.  And Jesus said, 
“Father, forgive them; for they know not what they do.”
N. And they cast lots to divide his garments.</s>"},{ID:103,
Text:"<s1384>  And the people stood by, watching; but the rulers scoffed at him, saying, </s>"},{ID:104,
Text:"<s1384>S. “He saved others; let him save himself, if he is the Christ of God, his Chosen One!”</s>"},{ID:105,
Text:"<s1384>N. The soldiers also mocked him, coming up and offering him vinegar, and saying, </s>"},{ID:106,
Text:"<s1384>S. “If you are the King of the Jews, save yourself!”</s>"},{ID:107,
Text:"<s1384>N. There was also an inscription over him, “This is the King of the Jews.”One of the criminals who were hanged railed at him, saying, </s>"},{ID:108,
Text:"<s1384>S.  “Are you not the Christ?
Save yourself and us!”</s>"},{ID:109,
Text:"<s1384>N.  But the other rebuked him, saying, </s>"},{ID:110,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Do you not fear God, since you are under the same sentence of condemnation?</s>"},{ID:111,
Text:"<s1384>And we indeed justly; for we are receiving the due reward of our deeds; but this man has done nothing wrong.”</s>"},{ID:112,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he said,</s>"},{ID:113,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Jesus, remember me when you come in your kingly power.”</s>"},{ID:114,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he said to him,
 
“Truly, I say to you, today you will be with me in Paradise.”</s>"},{ID:115,
Text:"<s1384>N.  It was now about the sixth hour, and there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour, </s>"},{ID:116,
Text:"<s1384>while the sun’s light failed; and the curtain of the temple was torn two.   Then Jesus, crying with a loud voice, said, 
“Father, into your hands I commit my spirit!”</s>"},{ID:117,
Text:"<s1384>N. And having said this he breathed his last.
Now when the centurion saw what had taken place, he praised God, and said, </s>"},{ID:118,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Certainly this man was innocent!”</s>"},{ID:119,
Text:"<s1384>N. And all the multitudes who assembled to see the sight, when they saw what had taken place, returned home beating their breasts.</s>"},{ID:120,
Text:"<s1384>And all his acquaintances and the women who had followed him from Galilee stood at a distance and saw these things.</s>"},{ID:121,
Text:"<s1384>Now there was a man named Joseph from the Jewish town of Arimathea. He was a member of the council, a good and righteous man, who had not consented to their purpose and deed,</s>"},{ID:122,
Text:"<s1384> and he was looking for the kingdom of God.  This man went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus. </s>"},{ID:123,
Text:"<s1384>Then he took it down and wrapped it in a linen shroud, and laid him in a rock-hewn tomb, where no one had ever yet been laid.  It was the of Preparation, </s>"},{ID:124,
Text:"<s1384>and the Sabbath was beginning.  The women who had come with him from Galilee followed, and saw the tomb, </s>"},{ID:125,
Text:"<s1384>and how his body was laid; and they returned, and prepared spices and ointments.  On the Sabbath they rested according to the commandment.</s>"},{ID:126,
Text:"<s1384> The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"Gopel (Short)"},{Guid:"2n+BPcQxE0O+JIUCwflX8w",Verses:[{
Text:"A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 22:15-21"},{ID:2,
Text:"At that time:
The Pharisees went and took counsel how to entangle Jesus in his talk."},{ID:3,
Text:" And they sent their disciples to him, along with the Herodians, saying, "},{ID:4,
Text:"“Teacher, we know that you are true, and teach the way of God truthfully, and care for no man; for you do not regard the position of men."},{ID:5,
Text:"Tell us, then, what you think.  Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?”
But Jesus, aware of their malice, said,"},{ID:6,
Text:" “Why put me to the test, you hypocrites? Show me the money for the tax.” And they brought him a coin. And Jesus said to them, “Whose likeness and inscription is this?”"},{ID:7,
Text:"They said, “Caesar’s.”
Then he said to them, “Render therefore to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s.”"},{ID:8,
Text:"The Gospel of the Lord."}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"gospel"},{Guid:"/1AcuqSRXESN3SVGD4gI1w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The conclusion of the Holy Gospel according to Mark		Mk. 16:15-20</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus appearing to the eleven said to them, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“Go into all the world and preach the Gospel to the whole creation.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  He who believes and is baptized will be saved; but he who does not believe will be condemned. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And these signs will accompany those who believe: in my name they will cast out demons;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> they will speak in new tongues; they will pick up serpents, and if they drink any deadly thing, it will not hurt them; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>they will lay their hands on the sick, and they will recover,”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>So then the Lord Jesus, after he had spoken to them, was taken up into heaven, and sat down at the right hand of God.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And they went forth and preached everywhere, while the lord worked with them and confirmed the message by the signs that attended it.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Amen. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL"},{Guid:"G4jJP8czO0ajtYffkvgdSA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL 									Luke 1:39-56</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>	    
In those days Mary arose and went with haste into the hill country, to a city of Judah, and she entered the house of Zechariah and greeted Elizabeth.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> And when Elizabeth heard the greeting of Mary, the child leaped in her womb; and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit and she exclaimed  with a loud cry,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> “Blessed are you among women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb! And why is this granted me, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> For behold, when the voice of your greeting came to my ears, the child in my womb leaped for joy. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> And blessed is she who believed that there would be a fulfilment of what was spoken to her from the Lord.”  </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And Mary said, “My soul magnifies the Lord, and my spirit rejoices in God my Savior, for he has regarded the low estate of his handmaiden. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> For behold, henceforth all generations will call me blessed; for he who is mighty has done great things for me, and holy is his name.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> And his mercy is on those who fear him from generation to generation. He has shown strength with his arm,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> he has scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts, he has put down the mighty from their thrones, and exalted those of low degrees;</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> he has filled the hungry with good things, and the rich he has sent empty away.  He has helped his servant Israel,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> in remembrance of his mercy, as he spoke to our fathers, to Abraham and to his posterity for ever.”  </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>And Mary remained with her about three months, and returned to her home.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL "},{Guid:"ZAcRaFrb106JwNcBKnqaLg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL   									Luke 2:22-40</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A Reading from the Holy Gospel According to Luke</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>When the time came for their purification according to the law of Moses, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>the parents of Jesus brought him up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord (as it is written in the law of the Lord, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>“Every male that opens the womb shall be called holy to the Lord”) and to offer a sacrifice according to what is said in the law of the Lord, “</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> a pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons”.  Now there was a man in Jerusalem, whose name was Simeon, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and this man was righteous and devout, looking for the consolation of Israel, and the Holy Spirit was upon him. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> And it had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he should not see death before he had seen the Lord’s Christ.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>An inspired by the Spirit he came into the temple; and when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him according to the custom of the law,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> he took him up in his arms and blessed God and said, “Lord, now let your servant depart in peace, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>according to your word; for my eyes have seen your salvation which you have prepared in the presence of all peoples, a light for revelation to the Gentiles, and for glory to your people Israel.” </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> And his father and his mother marveled at what was said about him; and Simeon blessed them and said to Mary his mother, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>“Behold, this child is set for the fall and rising of many in Israel, and for a sign that is spoken against (and a sword will pierce through your own soul also),</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> that thoughts out of many hearts may be revealed.”   And there was a prophetess, Anna, the daughter of Phanuel, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>of the tribe of Asher; she was of a great age, having  lived with her husband seven years from her virginity, </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>and as a widow till she was eighty-four.  She did not depart from the temple, </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>worshipping  with fasting and prayer night and day.  And coming up at that very hour she gave thanks to God, </s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>and spoke of him to all who were looking  for the redemption of Jerusalem.  </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>And when they had performed everything according to the law of the Lord, they returned into Galilee, </s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>to their own city, Nazareth.  And the child grew and became strong, filled with wisdom and the favour of God was upon him.   </s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL  "},{Guid:"O7jxE1yyJEy7X+fOoLlvdw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Seeing the crowds, Jesus went up on the mountain,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>and when he sat down his disciples came to him.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>And he opened his mouth and taught them, saying:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>\"Blessed are the poor in spirit,
for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>\" Blessed are those who mourn, for they 
shall be comforted.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>\"Blessed are the meek, for they shall inherit the
earth.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>\"Blessed are those who hunger and thirst
for righteousness, for they shall be satisfied.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>\"Blessed are the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>\"Blessed are the pure in heart, for they shall see God.
\"Blessed are the peacemakers,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> for they shall
be called sons of God.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>\"Blessed are those who are persecuted for 
righteousnes' sake, for theirs is the kingdom of 
heaven.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>\"Blessed are you when men revile you and persecute
you and utter all kinds of evil against you 
falsely on my account. Rejoice and be glad, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>for your reward is great in heaven.\"</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"Gospel
"},{Guid:"oqG08qV3sUWhdHoBcys2BQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	              Mark 4:35-41</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>On that day, when evening had come, Jesus said to his disciples, “Let us go across to the other side.”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And leaving the crowd, they took him with them, just as he was, in the boat.  And other boats were with him.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And a great storm of wind arose, and the waves beat into the boat, so that the boat was already filling.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>  But he was in the stern, asleep on the cushion; and they woke him and said to him, “Teacher, do you not care if we perish?”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he awoke and rebuked the wind, and said to the sea, “Peace! Be still!” 
And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>  He said to them, “Why are you afraid? Have you no faith?”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And they were filled with awe, and said to one another, “Who then is this, that even wind and sea obey him?”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"ZZJu/jtxTU2zlcr9HnhkQw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to John   		     John 12:20-33</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Among those who went up to worship at the feast were some Greeks.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>So these came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida in Galilee, and said to him,” Sir, we wish to see Jesus.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Philip went and told Andrew;
Andrew went with Philip and they told Jesus. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus answered them.
“The hour has come for the Son of man to be glorified.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Truly, truly, I say to you, unless a grain of wheat falls into the earth and dies, it remains alone;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> but if it dies, it bears much fruit.
He who loves his life loses it, and he who hates his life in this world will keep it for eternal life.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>If any one serves me, he must follow me; and where I am, there shall my servant be also; if any one serves me, the Father will honour him.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“Now is my soul troubled.
And what shall I say?
‘Father, save me from this hour’?</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>No, for this purpose I have come this hour.
Father, glorify your name.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Then a voice came from heaven, “I have glorified it, and I will glorify it again.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The crowd standing by heard it and said that it had thundered.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>  Others said, ”An angel has spoken to him.”
Jesus answered, “This voice has come for your sake, not for mine.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Now is the judgement of this world, now shall the ruler of this world be cast out; </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>and I, when I am lifted up from the earth, will draw all men to myself.”</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>He said this to show by what death he was to die.</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"M6ZNv2wwgkuGS5ewvyYaWw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	              Mark 4:26-34</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus said to the crowds, “The kingdom of God is as if a man should scatter seed upon the ground,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and should sleep and rise night and day, and the seed should sprout and grow, he knows not how.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>The earth produces of itself, first the blade, then the ear, then the full grain in the ear.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>But when the grain is ripe, at once he puts in the sickle, because the harvest has come.”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he said, “With what can we compare the kingdom of God, or what parable shall we use for it?</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>It is like a grain of mustard seed, which, when sown upon the ground, is the smallest of all the seeds on earth; </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>yet when it is sown it grows up and becomes the greatest of all shrubs, and puts forth large branches,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> so that the birds of the air can make nests in its shade.”
With many such parables he spoke the word to them,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> as they were able to hear it; he did not speak to them without a parable, but privately to his own disciples he explained everything.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"wgY/PM+2AkyXYN3WNyPDiA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to John   		     John 2:13-25</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The Passover of the Jews was at hand, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>In the temple he found those who were selling oxen and sheep and pigeons, and the money-changers at their business.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> And making a whip of cords, he drove them all, with the sheep and oxen,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> out of the temple; and he poured out the coins of the money-changers and overturned their tables.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he told those who sold the pigeons, “Take these things away; you shall not make my Father’s house a house of trade.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>His disciples remembered that it was written, “Zeal for your house will consume me.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Jews then said to him, “What sign have you to show us for doing this?”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus answered them, “Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Jews then said, “It has taken forty-six years to build this temple, and will you raise it up in three days?”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>But he spoke of the temple of his body. When therefore he was raised from the dead,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> his disciples remembered that he had said this; and they believed the Scripture and the word which Jesus had spoken.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Now when he was in Jerusalem at the Passover feast, many believed in his name when they saw the signs which he did;</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> but Jesus did not trust himself to them, because he knew all men and needed no one to bear witness of man; for he himself knew what was in man.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"/ygPSauVDkaEJsOsRnLt2w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1846>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1846>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 25:1-13</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1846>At that time:
Jesus told his disciples this parable: “The kingdom of heaven shall be compared to ten maidens who took their lamps and went to meet the bridegroom.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1846> Five of them were foolish, and five were wise.  For when the foolish took their lamps, they took no oil with them;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1846> but the wise took flasks of oil with their lamps.  As the bridegroom was delayed, they all slumbered and slept.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1846>“But at midnight there was a cry, ‘Behold, the bridegroom! Come out to meet him.’</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1846>“Then all those maidens rose and trimmed their lamps. And the foolish said to the wise, ‘Give us some of your oil, for our lamps are going out.’</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1846>“But the wise replied, ‘Perhaps there will not be enough for us and for you; go rather to the dealers and buy for yourselves.’</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1846>“And while they went to buy, the bridegroom came, and those who were ready went in with him to the marriage feast; and the door was shut. </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1846>Afterward the other maidens came also, saying, ‘Lord, lord, open to us.’
“But he replied, ‘Truly, I say to you, I do not know you.’</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1846>“Watch therefore, for you know neither the day nor the hour.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1846>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"smq4FE7AzEa8cyTX1OjrTw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 2:41-52</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The parents of Jesus went to Jerusalem every year at the feast of the Passover. And when he was twelve years old, they went up according to custom; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and when the feast was ended, as they were returning, the boy Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> His parents did not know it, but supposing him to be in the company they went a day’s journey, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and they sought him among their kinsfolk and acquaintances; and when they did not find him, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>they returned to Jerusalem, seeking him. After three days they found him in the temple, sitting among the teachers,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> listening to them and asking them questions; and all who heard him were amazed at his understanding and his answers.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And when they saw him they were astonished; and his mother said to him, “Son, why have you treated us so? </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Behold, your father and I have been looking for you anxiously.”
And he said to them, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>“How is it that you sought me? Did you not know that I must be in my Father’s house?” </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>And they did not understand the saying which he spoke to them.
And he went down with them and came to Nazareth, and was obedient to them;</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> and his mother kept all these things in her heart. 
And Jesus increased in wisdom and in stature, and in favour with God and man.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"LB0zueKLvU+9ctz7DypDoA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 6:60-69</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Many of the disciples of Jesus said, “This is a hard saying; who can listen to it?”
But Jesus, knowing in himself that his disciples murmured at it, </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>said to them, “Do you take offence at this?Then what if you were to see the Son of man ascending where he was before?</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Spirit that gives life, the flesh is of no avail; the words that I have spoken to you are Spirit and life.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>But there are some of you that do not believe.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For Jesus knew from the first who those were that did not believe, and who it was that would betray him.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he said, “This is why I told you that no one can come to me unless it is granted him by the Father.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>After this many of his disciples drew back and no longer walked with him. 
Jesus said to the Twelve, “Will you also go away?”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Simon Peter answered him, “Lord, to whom shall we go? 
You have the words of eternal life;</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> and we have believed, and have come to know, that you are Holy One of God.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"+vcma/d3P0m26EtRJI2Bog",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark		Mark 14:12-16, 22-26</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>On the first day of Unleavened Bread, when they sacrificed the Passover lamb, his disciples said to Jesus, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“Where will you have us go and prepare for you to eat the Passover?” 
And he sent two of his disciples, and said to them,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> “Go into the city, and a man carrying a jar of water will meet you; follow him, and wherever he enters, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>say to the householder, ‘The Teacher says, Where is my guest room, where I am to eat the Passover with my disciples?’ </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he will show you a large upper room furnished and ready; there prepare for us.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>and the disciples set out and went to the city, and found it as he had told them; and they prepared the Passover.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And as they were eating, he took bread and blessed, and broke it, and gave it to them, and said, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“Take; this is my body.” And he took a chalice, and when he had given thanks he gave it to them, and they all drank of it.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to them, “This is my blood of the covenant, which is poured out for many.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>  Truly, I say to you, I shall not drink again of the fruit of the vine until that day when I drink it new in the kingdom of God.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>And when they had sung a hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"lq/AkLZ5V0+cTF6ULi77Eg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	      Mark 9:38-43,45,47-48</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>John said to Jesus, “Teacher, we saw a man casting out demons in your name, and we forbade him, because he was not following us.”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>But Jesus said, “Do not forbid him; for no one who does a mighty work in my name will be able soon after to speak evil of me.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> For he that is not against us is for us. For truly, I say to you, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>whoever gives you a cup of water to drink because you bear the name of Christ, will by no means lose his reward.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Whoever causes one of these little ones who believe in me to sin, it would be better for him if a great millstone </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>were hung round his neck and he were thrown into the sea.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And if your hand causes you to sin, cut it off; it is better for you to enter life maimed that with two hands to go to hell, to the unquenchable fire.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>And if your foot causes you to sin, cut it off; it is better for you to enter life lame than with two feet to be thrown into hell.  </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And if your eyes causes you to sin, pluck it out; it is better for you to enter the kingdom of God with one eye than with two eyes to be thrown into hell,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> where their worm does not die, and the fire is not quenched.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"TxFGtDK1m0eXI31m+YDA4A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 1:1-4,4:14-21</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>In as much as many have undertaken to compile a narrative of the things which have been accomplished among us,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> just as they were delivered to us by those who from the beginning were eyewitnesses and ministers of the word,  </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>it seemed good to me also, having followed  all things closely  for some time past, to write an orderly account for you, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>most excellent Theophilus, that you may know the truth concerning the things of which you have been informed.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus returned in the power of the Spirit into Galilee, and a report concerning him went out through all the surrounding country.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>  And he taught in their synagogues, being glorified by all.
And he came to Nazareth, where he had been brought up; </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and he went to the synagogue, as was his custom, on the Sabbath day.  
And he stood up to read;</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> and there was given to him the Book of the Prophet Isaiah.
He opened the book and found the place where it was written: </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>“The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, because he has anointed me to preach good news to the poor. </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>He has sent me to proclaim release to the captives and recovering of sight to the blind, to set at liberty those who are oppressed,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> to proclaim the acceptable year of the Lord.”
And he closed the book, and gave it back to the attendant,</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> and sat down; and the eyes of all in the synagogue were fixed on him.  And he began to say to them,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> “Today this Scripture has been fulfilled in your hearing.”</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"7wWbkuYvHUadm0uCVMfn0A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	      Mark 12:28b-34</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
One of the scribes came up to Jesus and asked him, “Which commandment is the first of all?” Jesus answered,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> “The first is, “Hear, O Israel: The Lord our God, the Lord is one; and you shall love the Lord your God with all your hearts, and with all your soul, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and with all your mind, and with all your strength.’  The second is this, ‘You shall love your neighbor as yourself.’</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> There is no other commandment greater than these.”And the scribe said to him, “You are right, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Teacher; you have truly said that he is one, and there is no other but he; and to love him with all the heart,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and with all the  understanding, and with all the strength, and to love one’s neighbor as oneself, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>is much more than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices.” And when Jesus saw that he answered wisely,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> he said to him, “You are not far from the kingdom of God.” And after that no one dared to ask him any question.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"eQsEEnD8AkCBGCpK+z0GHg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 21:25-28,34-36</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus said to his disciples, “There will be signs in sun and moon and stars,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and upon the earth distress of nations in perplexity at the roaring of the sea and the waves,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> men fainting with fear and with foreboding of what is coming on the world; for the powers of the heavens will be shaken.  </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And then they will see the Son of man coming in a cloud with power and great glory. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Now when these things begin to take place, look up and raise your heads, because your redemption is drawing near.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>But take head to yourselves lest your hearts be weighted down with dissipation and drunkenness and cares of this life,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> and that day come upon you suddenly like a snare; for it will come upon all who dwell upon the face of the whole earth. </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> But watch at all times, praying to have strength to escape all these things that will take place, and to stand before the Son of man.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"OacKS7SglECQkpHaasLifA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	      Mark 10:2-16</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Pharisees came up and in order to test Jesus asked, “Is it lawful for a man to divorce his wife?”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>He answered them, “What did Moses command you?”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>They said, “Moses allowed a man to write a certificate of divorce, and to put her away.”
But Jesus said to them, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>“For your hardness of heart he wrote you this commandment. But from the beginning of creation,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> ‘God made them male and female.’
‘For this reason a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and the two shall become one flesh.’ So they are no longer two but one flesh.
What therefore God has joined together, let no man put asunder.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And in the house the disciples asked him again about this matter. 
And he said to them, “Whoever divorces his wife and marries another,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> commits adultery against her; and if she divorces her husband and marries another, she commits adultery.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> And they were bringing children to him, that he might touch them; and the disciples rebuked them. </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>But when Jesus saw it he was indignant, and said to them, “Let the children come to me, do not hinder them; for to such belongs the kingdom of God.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Truly, I say to you, whoever does not receive the kingdom of God like a child shall not enter it.” And he took them in his arms and blessed them, laying his hands upon them.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"gKKLNwpwLkmtgEEIIg9+7g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	         John 2:1-11</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>There was a marriage at Cana in Galilee, and the mother of Jesus was there; Jesus also was invited to the marriage, with his disciples.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>When the wine failed, the mother of Jesus said to him, “They have no wine.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus said to her, “O woman, what is that to you or to me? My hour has not yet come.” His mother said to the servants, “Do whatever he tells you.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Now six stone jars were standing there, for the Jewish rites of purification, each holding twenty or thirty gallons.  Jesus said to them, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Fill the jars with water.” And they filled them up to the brim. He said to them, “Now draw some out, and take it to the steward of the feast.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> So they took it. When the steward of the feast tasted the water now become wine, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and did not know where it came from (though the servants who had drawn the water knew), the steward of the feast called the bridegroom and said to him,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> “Every man serves the good wine first; and when men have drunk freely, then the poor wine; but you have kept the good wine until now.” </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>This, the first of his signs, Jesus did at Cana in Galilee, and manifested his glory; and his disciples believed in him.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"+wva+OhR7EmxSi102l9+nw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 6:17,20-26</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus came down with the Twelve and stood on a level place, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>with a great crowd of his disciples and a great multitude of people from all Judea and Jerusalem and the seacoast  of Tyre and Sidon, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> who came to hear him and to be healed of their diseases.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And he lifted up his eyes on his disciples and said:</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Blessed are you poor, for yours is the kingdom of God. “Blessed are you that hunger now,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> for you shall  be satisfied. “Blessed are you that weep now, for you shall laugh.
“Blessed are you when men hate you, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and when they exclude  you and revile you, and cast out your name as evil, on account of the Son of man!</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> Rejoice in that day, and leap for joy, for behold, your reward is great in heaven; for so their fathers did to the prophets.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>“But woe to you that are rich, for your have received your consolation.
“Woe to you that are full now, for you shall hunger.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>“Woe  to you that laugh now, for you shall mourn and weep.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>“Woe to you, when all men speak well of you, for so their fathers did to the false prophets.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"ULtRI1/QbUC7myInhRK7Wg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew	
	</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Again Jesus spoke to the chief priests and elders of the people, </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>in parables, saying, “The kingdom of heaven may be compared to a king who gave a marriage feast for his son,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> and sent his servants to call those who were invited to the marriage feast; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>but they would not come.  Again he sent other servants, saying, ‘Tell those who are invited, Behold, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>I have made ready may dinner, my oxen and my fat calves are killed, and everything is ready; come to the marriage feast.’</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>But they made light of it and went off, one to his farm, another to his business, while the rest seized his servants,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> treated them shamefully, and killed them. The king was angry, and he sent his troops and destroyed those murderers and burned their city.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Then he said to his servants, ‘The wedding is ready, but those invited were not worthy.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> 
Go therefore to the streets, and invited to the marriage feast as many as you find.’</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> And those servants went out into the streets and gathered all whom they found, both bad and good; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>so the wedding hall was filled with guests.“</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>But when the king came in to look at the guests, he saw there a man who had no wedding garment;</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> and he said to him, ‘Friend, how did you get in here without a wedding garment?’ And he was speechless.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Then the king said to the attendants, ‘Bind him hand and foot, and cast him into the outer darkness, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.’</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> For many were called, but few are chosen.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"HeqFLbijyUq2kWTlKUYp8w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	              Luke 24:35-48</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
The two disciples told what had happened on the road, and how Jesus was known to them in the breaking of the bread.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>As they were saying this, Jesus himself stood among them, and said to them, “Peace to you.” </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>But they were startled and frightened, and supposed that they saw a spirit.
And he said to them,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> “Why are you troubled, and why do questionings rise in your hearts? 
See my hands and my feet,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> that it is I myself; handle me, and see; for a spirit has not flesh and bones as you see that I have.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And when he had said this he showed them his hands and his feet.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And while they still disbelieved for joy, and wondered, he said to them, “Have you anything here to eat?”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>They gave him a piece of broiled fish, and he took it and ate before them.
Then he said to them, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>“These are my words which I spoke to you, while I was still with you,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> that everything written about me in the law of Moses and the prophets and the psalms must be fulfilled.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Then he opened their minds to understand the Scriptures, and said to them, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>“Thus it is written, that the Christ should suffer and on the third day rise from the dead,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> and that repentance and forgiveness of sins should be preached in his name to all nations,</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> beginning from Jerusalem.
You are witnesses of these things.”</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"8eSsYl3fM0yAKu5QuPJjIw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	              Mark 5:21-43</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>When Jesus had crossed in the boat to the other side of the Sea of Galilee, a great crowd gathered about him; and he was beside the sea.  </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Then came one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jairus by name; </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and seeing him, he fell at his feet, and begged him, saying, “My little daughter is at the point of death.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Come and lay your hands on  her, so that she may be made well, and live.” And he went with him.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And a great crowd followed him and thronged about him.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>  And there was a woman who had had a flow of blood for twelve years, and who had suffered much under many physicians,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> and had spent all that she had, and was no better but rather grew worse.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>  She had heard reports about Jesus, and came up behind him in the crowd and touched his garment.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>  For she said, “If I touch even his garments, I shall be made well.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> And immediately the hemorrhage ceased; and she felt in her body that she was healed of her disease.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus, perceiving in himself that power had gone forth from him, immediately turned about in the crowd,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> and said “Who touched my garments?”
And his disciples said to him, “You see the crowd pressing around you, and yet you say, ‘Who touched me.?’”</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>And he looked around to see who had done it.  But the woman, knowing what had been done to her, came in fear and trembling and fell down before him,</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> and told him the whole truth. And he said to her, “Daughter, your faith has made you well; go in peace, and be healed of your disease.”</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>While he was still speaking, there came from the ruler’s house some who said, “Your daughter is dead.  Why trouble the Teacher any further?”</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>But ignoring what they said, Jesus said to the ruler of the synagogue, “Do not fear, only believe.” </s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>And he allowed no one to follow him except Peter and James and John the brother of James.</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384> When they came to the house of the ruler of the synagogue, he saw a tumult, and people weeping and wailing loudly.</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>And when he had entered, he said to them, “Why do you make a tumult and weep? The child is not dead but sleeping.” And they laughed at him.</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>  But he put them all outside, and took the child’s father and mother and those who were with him, and went in where the child was.</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>Taking her by the hand he said to her, “Talitha cumi”; which means, “Little girl, I say to you, arise.’</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>And immediately the girl got up and walked; for she was twelve years old.  And immediately they were overcome with amazement.</s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384> And he strictly charged them that no one should know this, and told them to give her something to eat.</s>"},{ID:27,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"Iln/d0Rtq0aDJVRLY1c++w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew  		Matthew 2:1-12</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384> 
Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea in the days of Herod the king,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> behold, Wise Men from the East came to Jerusalem,</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384> saying, “Where is he who has been born king of the Jews? For we have seen his star in the East,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> and have come to worship him.” When Herod the king heard this, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him;</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and assembling all the chief priests and scribes of the people, he inquired of them where the Christ was to be born. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>They told him, “In Bethlehem Judea; for so it is written by the prophet:  ‘And you, O Bethlehem, in the land of Judah, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>are by no means least among the rulers of Judah; for from you shall come a ruler who will govern my people Israel.’”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Then Herod summoned the Wise Men secretly and ascertained from them what time the star appeared;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and he sent them to Bethlehem, saying, “Go and search diligently for the child, and when you have found him bring me word,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> that I too may come and worship him.” When they had heard the king they went their way; and behold,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> the star which they had seen in the East went before them, till it came to rest over the place where the child was.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> When they saw the star, they rejoiced exceedingly with great joy; and going into the house they saw the child with Mary his mother,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> and they fell down and worshipped him.  Then, opening their treasures, they offered him gifts,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> gold and frankincense and myrrh. And being warned in a dream not to return to Herod, they departed to their own country by another way.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"WSURL58+UEGoLlCy9ztLAg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Mark   		     Mark 1:21b-28</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>(In the city of Capernaum) on the Sabbath Jesus entered the synagogue and taught. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> And they were astonished at his teaching, for he taught them as one who had authority and not as the scribes.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> And immediately there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit; and he cried out, “What have you to do with us, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus of Nazareth? Have you come to destroy us?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>I know who you are, the Holy One of God.”
But Jesus rebuked him, saying, “Be silent, and come out of him!”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And the unclean spirit, convulsing him and crying with a loud voice, came out of him.  
And they were all amazed, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>so that they questioned among themselves, saying “What is this? </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>A new teaching!
With authority he commands even the unclean spirits, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>and they obey him.”
And at once his fame spread everywhere throughout all the surrounding region of Galilee.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"AvX4tI1v2kita0ZEPq7ZdA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John  	              John 10:11-18</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus said, “I am the good shepherd.
The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>He who is a hireling and not a shepherd, whose own the sheep are not, sees the wolf coming and leaves the sheep and flees;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and the wolf snatches them and scatters them.  He flees because he is a hireling and cares nothing for the sheep.
I am the good shepherd; </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>I know my own and my own know me, as the Father knows me and I know the Father; and I lay down my life for the sheep.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And I have other sheep, that are not of this fold; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>I must bring them also, and they will heed my voice.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>So there shall be one flock, one shepherd.
For this reason the Father loves me,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> because I lay down my life, that I may take it again.
No one takes it from me, but I lay it down of my own accord.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it again; this charge I have received from my Father.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"/C3BHXiuUEahL9IwwVPbvA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 6:41-51</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
The Jews murmured at Jesus, because he said, “I am the bread which came down from heaven.” </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>They said, “Is not this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How does he now say, ‘I have come down from heaven’?” </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus answered them, “Do not murmur among yourselves. No one can come to me unless the Father who sent me draws him; </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and I will raise him up at the last day.  It is written in the prophets, ‘And they shall all be taught by God.’</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Every one who has heard and learned from the Father comes to me.  
Not that any one has seen the Father except him who is from God;</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> he has seen the Father.  Truly, truly, I say to you, he who believes has eternal life.  I am the bread of life. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness, and they died.
This is the bread which comes down from heaven, that a man may eat of it and not die.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>I am the living bread which came down from heaven; if any one eats of this bread, he will live for ever;</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> and the bread which I shall give for the life of the world is my flesh.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"jDtvYXU4ikizewfIcD377w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke  	         Luke 2:16-21</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
The shepherds went with haste to Bethlehem, and found Mary and Joseph, and the baby lying in a manger. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> And when they saw it they made known the saying which had been told them concerning this child; </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and all who heard it wondered at what the shepherds told them.  But Mary kept all these things, pondering them in her heart.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all they had heard and seen, as it had been told them.
And at the end of eight days,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> when he was circumcised, he was called Jesus, the name given by the angel before he was conceived in the womb.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"Tjt5eBdae0aCK9MWC6brcg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	            Mark 8:27-35</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus went on with his disciples, to the villages of Caesarea Philipi; and on the way he asked his disciples, “Who do men say that I am?”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And they told him, “John the Baptist; and others say, Elijah; and others one of the prophets.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And he asked them, “But who do you say that I am?”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Peter answered him, “You are the Christ.”
And he charged them to tell no one about him.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And he began to teach them that the Son of man must suffer many things, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and be rejected by the elders and the chief priests and the scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again.And he said this plainly.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>And Peter took him, and began to rebuke him. But turning  and seeing his disciples,  he rebuked Peter,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> and said, “Get behind me, Satan! For you are not on the side of God but of men.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> And he called to him the multitude with his disciples, and said to them, “If any man would come after me,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>For whoever would save his life will lose it; and whoever loses his life for my sake and the Gospel will save it.”</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"yUyl6IcSb0ywv7almUV+Iw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 10: 27-30</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus said, “My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me; and I give them eternal life, and they shall never perish, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>, and no one shall snatch them out of my hand.  My Father, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>who has given them to me, is greater than all, and no one is able to snatch them out of the Father’s hand.  I and the Father are one.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"3D98voP7H0i6FsvYLHkmgQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The Passion of our Lord Jesus Christ according to Luke   	Luke 22:14-23,56</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>N. When the hour came, 
Jesus sat at table, and the apostles with him. 
And he said to them,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“I have earnestly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>for I tell you I shall not eat it until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he took a chalice, and when he had given thanks he said, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Take this, and divide it among yourselves; for I tell you that from now on I shall not drink of the fruit of the vine until the kingdom of God comes.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he took bread, and when he had given thanks he broke it and gave it to them, saying, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>“This is my body which is given for you.
Do this in remembrance of me.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>N. And likewise the chalice after supper, saying,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“This chalice which is poured out for you I the new covenant in my blood.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>But behold the hand of him who betrays me is with me on the table.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>For the Son of man goes as it has been determined; but woe to that man by whom he is betrayed!”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they began to question one another, which of them it was that would do this.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>A dispute also arose among them, which of them was to be regarded as the greatest.  
And he said to them, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>“The kings of the Gentiles exercise lordship over them;</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> and those in authority over them are called benefactors.
But not so with you;</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> rather let the greatest among you become as the youngest, and the leader as one who serves. </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>For which is the greater, one who sits at table, or one who serves?
Is it not the one who sits at table?</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> But I am among you as one who serves.  “You are those who have continued with me in my trials;</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> as my Father appointed a kingdom for me, </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>so do I appoint for you that you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>“Simon, Simon, behold, Satan demanded to have you, that he might sift you like wheat, but I have prayed for you that your faith may not fail; </s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>and when you have turned again, strengthen your brethren.”</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>N.  And he said to him, 
S. “Lord, I am ready to go with you to prison and to death.”</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>N. He said,
“I tell you, Peter, the cock will not crow this day, until you three times deny that you know me.”
N. And he said to them,</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>“When I sent you out with no purse or bag or sandals, did you lack anything?”</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>N. They said,
S. “Nothing.”
N. He said to them, “But now, let him who has a purse take it, and likewise a bag.</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>And let him who has no sword sell his cloak and buy one.  </s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>For I tell you that this Scripture must be fulfilled in me, ‘And he was reckoned with transgressors’;</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384> for what is written about me has its fulfilment.”</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they said,</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Look, Lord, here are two swords.”</s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he came out, and went, as was his custom, </s>"},{ID:27,
Text:"<s1384>to the Mount of Olives; and the disciples followed him. And when he came to the place he said to them, </s>"},{ID:27,
Text:"<s1384>“Pray that you may not enter into temptations.”</s>"},{ID:28,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he withdrew from them about a stone’s throw, and knelt down and prayed, </s>"},{ID:28,
Text:"<s1384>“Father, if you are willing, remove this chalice from me; nevertheless not my will, but yours, be done.”</s>"},{ID:29,
Text:"<s1384>N. And there appeared to him an angel from heaven, strengthening him.  And being in an agony he prayed more earnestly; </s>"},{ID:30,
Text:"<s1384>and his sweat became like great drops of blood falling down upon the ground.</s>"},{ID:31,
Text:"<s1384>And when he rose from prayer, he came to the disciples and found them sleeping for sorrow, </s>"},{ID:32,
Text:"<s1384>and he said to them, 
“Why do you sleep? Rise and pray that you may not enter into temptation.”</s>"},{ID:32,
Text:"<s1384>N. While he was still speaking, there came a crowd, and the man called Judas, one of the Twelve, </s>"},{ID:33,
Text:"<s1384>was leading them.  He drew near to Jesus to kiss him;</s>"},{ID:33,
Text:"<s1384> but Jesus said to him,“Judas, would you betray the Son of man with a kiss?”</s>"},{ID:34,
Text:"<s1384>N. And when those who were about him saw what would follow, they said,</s>"},{ID:35,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Lord, shall we strike with the sword?”</s>"},{ID:36,
Text:"<s1384>N.  And one of them struck the slave of the high priest and cut off his right ear.But Jesus said, “No more of this!”</s>"},{ID:37,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he touched his ear and healed him.
Then Jesus said to the chief priests and captains of the temple and elders, who had come out against him, </s>"},{ID:38,
Text:"<s1384>“Have you come out as against a robber, with swords and clubs? When I was with you day after day in temple, you did not lay hands on me.</s>"},{ID:39,
Text:"<s1384>But this is your hour, and the power of darkness.”</s>"},{ID:40,
Text:"<s1384>N. Then they seized him and led him away, bringing him into the high priest’s house.  Peter followed at a distance;</s>"},{ID:41,
Text:"<s1384> and when they had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard and sat down together,</s>"},{ID:42,
Text:"<s1384> Peter sat among them.  Then a maid, seeing him as he sat in the light and gazing at him, said, </s>"},{ID:42,
Text:"<s1384>S. “This man also was with him.”</s>"},{ID:43,
Text:"<s1384>N. But he denied it, saying,</s>"},{ID:44,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Woman, I do not know him.”</s>"},{ID:45,
Text:"<s1384>N. And a little later someone else saw him and said,</s>"},{ID:46,
Text:"<s1384>S. “You also are one of them.”</s>"},{ID:47,
Text:"<s1384>N.  But Peter said, </s>"},{ID:48,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Man, I am not.”</s>"},{ID:49,
Text:"<s1384>N. And after an interval of about an hour still another insisted, saying, </s>"},{ID:50,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Certainly this man also was with him; for he is a Galilean.”</s>"},{ID:51,
Text:"<s1384>N. But Peter said,</s>"},{ID:52,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Man, I do not know what you are saying.”</s>"},{ID:53,
Text:"<s1384>N.  And immediately, while he was still speaking, the cock crowed.</s>"},{ID:54,
Text:"<s1384>And the Lord turned and looked at Peter.  And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, </s>"},{ID:55,
Text:"<s1384>how he had said to him, “Before the cock crows today, you will deny me three times.”</s>"},{ID:56,
Text:"<s1384>And he went out and wept bitterly.
Now the men who were holding Jesus mocked him and beat him;</s>"},{ID:57,
Text:"<s1384> they also blindfolded him and asked him, </s>"},{ID:57,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Prophesy! Who is it that struck you?”</s>"},{ID:58,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they spoke many other words against him, reviling him.</s>"},{ID:59,
Text:"<s1384>When the day came, the assembly of the elders of the people gathered together, both chief priests and scribes;</s>"},{ID:60,
Text:"<s1384> and they led him away to their council, and they said, </s>"},{ID:60,
Text:"<s1384>S. “If you are Christ, tell us.”</s>"},{ID:61,
Text:"<s1384>N. But he said to them, </s>"},{ID:62,
Text:"<s1384>“If I tell you, you will not believe; and if I ask you, you will answer. </s>"},{ID:63,
Text:"<s1384>But from now on the Son of man shall be seated at the right hand of the power of God.”</s>"},{ID:63,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they all said,</s>"},{ID:64,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Are you the Son of God, then?”</s>"},{ID:65,
Text:"<s1384>N.  And he said to them, 
	“You say that I am.”</s>"},{ID:66,
Text:"<s1384>N.  And they said, </s>"},{ID:67,
Text:"<s1384>S. “What further testimony do we need? We have heard it ourselves from his own lips.”</s>"},{ID:68,
Text:"<s1384>N. Then the whole company of them arose, and brought him before Pilate. And they began to accuse him, saying, </s>"},{ID:69,
Text:"<s1384>S. “We found this man perverting our nation, and forbidding us to give tribute to Caesar, and saying that he himself is Christ a king.”</s>"},{ID:70,
Text:"<s1384>N. And Pilate asked him, </s>"},{ID:71,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Are you the King of the Jews?”</s>"},{ID:72,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he answered him,
	“You have said so.”</s>"},{ID:73,
Text:"<s1384>N.  And Pilate said to the chief priests and the multitudes, </s>"},{ID:74,
Text:"<s1384>S.  “I find no crime in this man.”</s>"},{ID:75,
Text:"<s1384>N. But they were urgent, saying, </s>"},{ID:76,
Text:"<s1384>S. “He stirs up the people, teaching throughout all Judea, from Galilee even to this place.”</s>"},{ID:77,
Text:"<s1384>N.  When Pilate heard this, he asked whether the man was a Galilean. </s>"},{ID:78,
Text:"<s1384> And when he learned that he belonged to Herod’s jurisdiction, he sent him over to Herod,</s>"},{ID:78,
Text:"<s1384> who was himself in Jerusalem at that time.
When Herod saw Jesus, </s>"},{ID:79,
Text:"<s1384>he was very glad, for he had long desired to see him, because he had heard about him,</s>"},{ID:79,
Text:"<s1384> and he was hoping to see some sign done by him. </s>"},{ID:80,
Text:"<s1384>So he questioned him at some length; but he made no answer.
The chief priests and the scribes stood by,</s>"},{ID:80,
Text:"<s1384> vehemently accusing him. And Herod with his soldiers treated him with contempt and mocked him; then, </s>"},{ID:81,
Text:"<s1384>clothing him in gorgeous apparel, he sent him back to Pilate.</s>"},{ID:81,
Text:"<s1384>And Herod and Pilate became friends with each other that very day, for before this they had been at enmity with each other.</s>"},{ID:82,
Text:"<s1384>Pilate then called together the chief priests and the rulers and the people, and said to them,</s>"},{ID:82,
Text:"<s1384>S. “You brought me this man as one who was perverting the people; and after examining him before you,</s>"},{ID:83,
Text:"<s1384> behold, I did not find this man guilty of any of your charges against him; neither did Herod,</s>"},{ID:84,
Text:"<s1384> for he sent him back to us.  Behold, nothing deserving death has been done by him; I will therefore chastise him and release him.”</s>"},{ID:85,
Text:"<s1384>N. But they all cried out together, </s>"},{ID:86,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Away with this man, and release to us Barabbas” – </s>"},{ID:87,
Text:"<s1384>N. a man who had been thrown into prison for an insurrection started in the city, and for murder.</s>"},{ID:88,
Text:"<s1384>Pilate addressed them once more, desiring to release Jesus; but they shouted out,</s>"},{ID:89,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Crucify, crucify him!”</s>"},{ID:90,
Text:"<s1384>N. A third time he said to them, </s>"},{ID:91,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Why, what evil has he done?
I have found in him no crime deserving death; I will therefore chastise him and release him.”</s>"},{ID:92,
Text:"<s1384>N. But they were urgent, demanding with loud cries that he should be crucified.</s>"},{ID:93,
Text:"<s1384>And their voices prevailed.  So Pilate gave sentence that their demand should be granted. </s>"},{ID:94,
Text:"<s1384> He released the man who had been thrown into prison for insurrection and murder, whom they asked for; but Jesus he delivered up to their will.</s>"},{ID:95,
Text:"<s1384>And as they led him away, they seized one Simon of Cyrene, who was coming in from the country, and laid on him the cross, to carry it behind Jesus.  </s>"},{ID:96,
Text:"<s1384>And there followed him a great multitude of the people, and of women who bewailed and lamented him.  But Jesus turning to them said, </s>"},{ID:97,
Text:"<s1384>“Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your children. For behold, the days are coming when they will say, </s>"},{ID:98,
Text:"<s1384>‘Blessed are the barren, and the womb that never bore, and the breasts that never nursed!”</s>"},{ID:99,
Text:"<s1384>Then they will begin to say to the mountains, ‘Fall on us’; and to the hills, ‘Cover us.’</s>"},{ID:100,
Text:"<s1384>For if they do this when the wood is green, what will happen when it is dry?”</s>"},{ID:101,
Text:"<s1384>N. Two others also, who were criminals, were led away to be put to death with him.  And when they came to the place which is called The Skull, there they crucified him, </s>"},{ID:102,
Text:"<s1384>and the criminals, one on the right and one on the left.  And Jesus said, 
“Father, forgive them; for they know not what they do.”
N. And they cast lots to divide his garments.</s>"},{ID:103,
Text:"<s1384>  And the people stood by, watching; but the rulers scoffed at him, saying, </s>"},{ID:104,
Text:"<s1384>S. “He saved others; let him save himself, if he is the Christ of God, his Chosen One!”</s>"},{ID:105,
Text:"<s1384>N. The soldiers also mocked him, coming up and offering him vinegar, and saying, </s>"},{ID:106,
Text:"<s1384>S. “If you are the King of the Jews, save yourself!”</s>"},{ID:107,
Text:"<s1384>N. There was also an inscription over him, “This is the King of the Jews.”One of the criminals who were hanged railed at him, saying, </s>"},{ID:108,
Text:"<s1384>S.  “Are you not the Christ?
Save yourself and us!”</s>"},{ID:109,
Text:"<s1384>N.  But the other rebuked him, saying, </s>"},{ID:110,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Do you not fear God, since you are under the same sentence of condemnation?</s>"},{ID:111,
Text:"<s1384>And we indeed justly; for we are receiving the due reward of our deeds; but this man has done nothing wrong.”</s>"},{ID:112,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he said,</s>"},{ID:113,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Jesus, remember me when you come in your kingly power.”</s>"},{ID:114,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he said to him,
 
“Truly, I say to you, today you will be with me in Paradise.”</s>"},{ID:115,
Text:"<s1384>N.  It was now about the sixth hour, and there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour, </s>"},{ID:116,
Text:"<s1384>while the sun’s light failed; and the curtain of the temple was torn two.   Then Jesus, crying with a loud voice, said, 
“Father, into your hands I commit my spirit!”</s>"},{ID:117,
Text:"<s1384>N. And having said this he breathed his last.
Now when the centurion saw what had taken place, he praised God, and said, </s>"},{ID:118,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Certainly this man was innocent!”</s>"},{ID:119,
Text:"<s1384>N. And all the multitudes who assembled to see the sight, when they saw what had taken place, returned home beating their breasts.</s>"},{ID:120,
Text:"<s1384>And all his acquaintances and the women who had followed him from Galilee stood at a distance and saw these things.</s>"},{ID:121,
Text:"<s1384>Now there was a man named Joseph from the Jewish town of Arimathea. He was a member of the council, a good and righteous man, who had not consented to their purpose and deed,</s>"},{ID:122,
Text:"<s1384> and he was looking for the kingdom of God.  This man went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus. </s>"},{ID:123,
Text:"<s1384>Then he took it down and wrapped it in a linen shroud, and laid him in a rock-hewn tomb, where no one had ever yet been laid.  It was the of Preparation, </s>"},{ID:124,
Text:"<s1384>and the Sabbath was beginning.  The women who had come with him from Galilee followed, and saw the tomb, </s>"},{ID:125,
Text:"<s1384>and how his body was laid; and they returned, and prepared spices and ointments.  On the Sabbath they rested according to the commandment.</s>"},{ID:126,
Text:"<s1384> The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF990000"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"rtAT6D9EWUeQPyesQ/IPBg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	           Mark 12:38-44</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
In his teaching Jesus said to the crowds, “Beware of the scribes, who like to go about in long robes, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and to have salutations in the market places and the best seats in the synagogues and the places of honour at feasts, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>who devour widows’ houses and for a pretence make long prayers.They will receive the greater condemnation.”
And he sat down opposite the treasury, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and watched the multitude putting money into the treasury. Many rich people put in large sums.  
And a poor widow came,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> and put in two copper coins, which make a penny. And he called his disciples to him, and said to them, “Truly, I say to you, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>this poor widow has put in more than all those who are contributing to the treasury. For they all contributed  out of their abundance;</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> but she out of her poverty has put in everything she had, her whole living.”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"z9MJyUAmHU+ZtuCEXEpJOg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John    	              John 15:9-17</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus said to his disciples, 
“As the Father has loved me, so have I loved you; abide in my love. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> If you keep my commandments, you will abide in my love.  </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>If you keep my commandments, you will abide in my love, just as I have kept my Father’s commandments and abide in his love.  </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>These things I have spoken to you, that my joy may be in you, and that your joy may be full.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“This is my commandment, that you love one another as I have loved you. 
Greater love has no man than this,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> that a man lay down his life for his friends.  You are my friends if you do what I command you.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>No longer do i call you servants, for the servant does not know what his master is doing; but I have called you friends, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>for all that I have heard from my Father I have made known to you.  You did not choose me,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> but I chose you and appointed you that you should go and bear fruit and that your fruit should abide; </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>so that whatever you ask the Father in my name he may give it to you.  This I command you, to love one another.” </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"wKCvwMSjf0iXDLESl3HILA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 20:19-31</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>On the evening of that day, the first day of the week, the doors being shut where the disciples were,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> for fear of the Jews, Jesus came and stood among them and said to them, “Peace be with you.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>When he had said this, he showed them his hands and his side.  Then the disciples were glad when they saw the Lord.  </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus said to them again, “Peace be with you.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>As the Father has sent me, even so I send you.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And when he had said this, he breathed on them, and said to them, “Receive the Holy Spirit.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>If you forgive the sins of any, they are forgiven; if you retain the sins of any, they are retained.”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Now Thomas, one of the Twelve, called the Twin, was not with them when Jesus came. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> So the other disciples told him, “We have seen the Lord.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>But he said to them, “Unless I see in his hands the print of the nails, and place my finger in the mark of the nails,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> and place my hand in his side, I will not believe.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Eight days later, his disciples were again in the house, and Thomas was with them.
The doors were shut,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> but Jesus came and stood among them, and said, “Peace be with you.”</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Then he said to Thomas, “Put your fingers here, and see my hands; and put out your hand, and place it in my side;</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> do not be faithless, but believing.”
Thomas answered him, “My Lord and my God!”</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus said to him, 
“You have believed because you have seen me.</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are those who have not seen and yet believe.”</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>Now Jesus did many other signs in the presence of the disciples, which are not written in this book; </s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>but these are written that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that believing you may have life in his name.</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"WXByaYRrWUO3Wcm1cXkFNw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 6:1-15</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus went to the other side of the Sea of Galilee, which is the Sea of Tiberias.  And a multitude followed him,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> because they saw the signs which he did on those who were diseased. Jesus went up into the hills, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and there sat down with his disciples.  Now the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was at hand. Lifting up his eyes,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> then, and seeing that a multitude was coming to him, Jesus said to Philip, “How are we to buy bread, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>so that these people may eat?” This he said to test him, for he himself knew what he would do.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Philip answered him, “Two hundred denarii would not buy enough bread for each of them to get a little.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> One of his disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter’s brother, said to him, “There is a lad here who has five barley loaves and two fish; </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>but what are they among so many?” Jesus said, “Make the people sit down.” Now there was much grass in the place;</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> so the men sat down, in number about five thousand. Jesus then took the loaves, and when he had given thanks,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> he distributed them to those who were seated; so also the fish, as much as they wanted.  </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>And when they had eaten their fill, he told his disciples, “Gather up the fragments left over,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> that nothing may be lost.” So they gathered them up and filled twelve baskets with fragments from the five barley loaves, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>left by those who had eaten. When the people saw the sign which he had done, they said,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> “This is indeed the prophet who is to come into the world.”</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Perceiving then that they were about to come and take him by force to make him king, Jesus withdrew again to the hills by himself.</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"lTk3Wmvi1EGR+K2htnTsSg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
A reading from the holy Gospel according to Mark   		     Mark 1:29-39</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Leaving the synagogue, Jesus entered the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Now Simon’s mother-in-law lay sick with a fever, and immediately they told him of her.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>  And he came and took her by the hand and lifted her up, and the fever left her; </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and she served them. That evening, at sundown, they brought to him all who were sick or possessed with demons.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>  And the whole city was gathered together about the door. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And he healed many who were sick with various diseases, and cast out many demons;</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> and he would not permit the demons to speak, because they knew him.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>And in the morning, a great while before day, he rose and went out to a lonely place, and there he prayed. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> And Simon and those who were with him followed him, and they found him and said to him, “Everyone is searching for you.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> And he said to them, “Let us go on to the next towns, that I may preach there also; for that is why I came out.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>And he went throughout all Galilee, preaching in their synagogues and casting out demons.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"6Wg2jblw60y/tn8+drboGQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	      Mark 10:17-30</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
As Jesus was setting out on his journey, a man ran up and knelt before him, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and asked, “Good Teacher, what must I do to inherit eternal life?”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus said to him, “Why do you call me good? No one is good but God alone.  You know the commandments:</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> ‘Do not kill, Do not commit adultery, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Do not defraud, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Honour you father and mother.’” 
And he said to him, “Teacher, all these I have observed from my youth.”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus looking upon him loved him, and said to him, 
You lack one thing; go, sell what you have, and give to the poor,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and you will have treasure in heaven; and come, follow me.” 
At that saying his countenance fell, and he went away sorrowful;</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> for he had great possessions.
And Jesus looked around and said to his disciples, “How hard it will be for those who have riches to enter the kingdom of God!”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>And the disciples were amazed at his words.  But Jesus said to them again, “Children, how hard it is for those who trust in riches to enter the kingdom of God! </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter the kingdom of God.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>And they were exceedingly astonished, and said to him, “Then who can be saved?”
Jesus looked at them and said,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> “With men it is impossible, but not with God; for all things are possible with God.”
Peter began to say to him, “Behold, we have left everything and followed you.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus said, “Truly, I say to you, there is no one who has left house or brothers or sisters or mother or father or children or lands,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> for my sake and for the Gospel, who will not receive a hundredfold  now in this time, houses and brothers and sisters and mothers and children and lands, </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>with persecutions, and in the age to come eternal life.”</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"o6lWrKMlbkaShm6GwFy20A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 6:24-35</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
When the people saw that Jesus was not there, nor his disciples, they themselves got into the boats and went to Capernaum, seeking Jesus.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>When they found him on the other side of the sea, they said to him, “Rabbi, when did you come here?”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus answered  them, “Truly, truly, I say to you, you seek me, not because you saw signs, but because you ate your fill of the loaves.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> Do not labour for the food which perishes, but for the food which endures to eternal life,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> which the Son of man will give to you; for on him has God the Father set his seal.”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Then they said to him, “What must we do, to be doing the works of God?”
Jesus answered them, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>“This is the works of God, that you believe in him whom he has sent.” So they said to him,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> “Then what sign do you do, that we may see, and believe you? What work do you perform? </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness; as it is written, ‘He gave them bread from heaven to eat.’”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus then said to them, “Truly, truly, I say to you, it was not Moses who gave you the bread from heaven; </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>my Father gives you the true bread from heaven.
For the bread of God is that which comes down from heaven, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>and gives life to the world.” They said to him, “Lord, give us this bread always.”
Jesus said to them, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>“I am the bread of life; he who comes to me shall not hunger, and he who believes in me shall never thirst.”</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"42z8TNrbwEGG2g5DdccvuA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 3:1-6</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>In the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being governor of Judea,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and Herod being tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip tetrarch of the region of Ituraea and Trachonitis,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and Lysanias tetrarch of Abilene, in the high-priesthood of Annas and Caiaphas, the word of God came to John the son of Zechariah in the wilderness; </s>"},{ID:6},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and he went into all the region about the Jordan, preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins.
  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>As it is written in the book of the words of Isaiah the prophet, 
“The voice of one crying in the wilderness; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.  Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be brought low, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>and the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough ways shall be made smooth; </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and all flesh shall see the salvation of God.”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"6HZiQfVjskqOCJGLrRV7Iw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	           Mark 13:24-32</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus said to his disciples, “In those days, after that (great) tribulation, the sun will be darkened, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and the moon will not give its light, and the stars will be falling from heaven,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and the powers in the heavens will be shaken. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> And then they will see the Son of man coming in clouds with great power and glory.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And then he will send out the angels, and gather his elect from the four winds, from the ends of the earth to the ends of heaven.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>“From the fig tree learn its lesson: as soon as its branch becomes tender and puts forth its leaves,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> you know that summer is near.  So also, when you see these things taking place, you know that he is near, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>at the very gates.Truly, I say to you, this generation will not pass away before all these things take place.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>“But of that day or that hour no one knows, not even the angels in heaven, nor the Son, but only the Father.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"fnUSyzH3kkOIR1cV++v7Xw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>  	         Luke 4:1-11</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
While the people pressed upon Jesus to hear the word of God, he was standing by the lake of Gennesaret.  </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And he saw two boats by the lake; but the fishermen had gone out of them and were washing their nets. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Getting into one of the boats, which was Simon’s, he asked him to put out a little from the land.  </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he sat down and taught the people from the boat. And when he had ceased speaking, he said to Simon,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> “Put out into the deep and let down your nets for a catch.” And Simon answered, “Master, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>we toiled all night and took nothing! But at your word I will let down the nets.” And when they had done this, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>they enclosed a great shoal of fish; and as their nets were breaking, they beckoned to their partners in the other boat to come and help them. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And they came and filled both the boats, so that they began to sink.  But when Simon Peter saw it,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> he fell down at Jesus’ knees, saying, “Depart from me, for I am a sinful man, O Lord.” For he was astonished, and all that were with him, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>at the catch of fish which they had taken; and so also were James and John, sons of Zebedee, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>who were partners with Simon.
And Jesus said to Simon, “Do not be afraid; henceforth you will be catching men.”</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>And when they had brought their boats to land, they left everything and followed him.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006600"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"aBUmo8K+pUOiuu3Q9I8Jjw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Luke  		Luke 3:15-16,21-22 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At the time: 
As the people were in expectation, and all men questioned in their hearts concerning John, whether perhaps he were the Christ,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> John answered them all, “I baptize you with water; but he who is mightier than I is coming, the thong of whose sandals I am not worthy to untie; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>he will baptize you with the Holy  Spirit and with fire.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Now when all the people were baptized, and when Jesus  also had been baptized and was praying, the  heaven was opened,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and the Holy  Spirit  descended upon him in bodily form,  as a dove, and a voice came from heaven, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“You are my beloved Son;  with you I am well pleased.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"M5t1IbNVe0+mbSiQchDTCg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	    Mark 7:1-8,14-15,21-23</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus returned from the region of Tyre, and went through Sidon to the Sea of Galilee, through the region of the Decapolis.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  And they brought to him a man who was deaf and had an impediment in his speech; and they begged him to lay his hand upon him.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>  And taking him aside from the multitude privately, and put his fingers into his ears, and he spat and touched his tongue:</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and looking up to heaven, he signed, and said to him, “Ephphatha,” that is, “Be opened.” And his ears were opened, his tongue was released, and he spoke plainly.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he charged them to tell no one; but the more he charged them, the more zealously they proclaimed it. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> And they were astonished beyond measure, saying, “He has done all things well; he even makes the deaf hear and the mute speak.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"h8eknYQED0KB/3ASeYA8eQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew  		Matthew 2:1-12 </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea in the days of Herod the king, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>behold, Wise Men from the East came to Jerusalem, saying, “Where is he who has been born king of the Jews?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> For we have seen his star in the East, and have come to worship him.” When Herod the king heard this,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him; and assembling all the chief priests and scribes of the people,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> he inquired of them where the Christ was to be born. They told him,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> “In Bethlehem  of Judea; for so it is written by the prophet:  ‘And you, O Bethlehem,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> in the land of Judah, are by no means least among the rulers of Judah; </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>for from you shall come a ruler who will govern my people Israel.’”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Then Herod summoned the Wise Men secretly and ascertained from them what time the star appeared; </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>and he sent them to Bethlehem, saying, “Go and search diligently for the child, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>and when you have found him bring me word, that I too may come and worship him.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> When they had heard the king they went their way; </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>and behold, the star which they had seen in the East went before them,</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> till it came to rest over the place where the child was. When they saw the star,</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> they rejoiced exceedingly with great joy; and going into the house they saw the child with Mary his mother,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384> and they fell down and worshipped him.  Then, opening their treasures,</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384> they offered him gifts, gold and frankincense and myrrh.</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384> And being warned in a dream not to return to Herod,</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384> they departed to their own country by another way.</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"a7M6pJsZcUCmIBX7saRBZw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	      Luke 15:1-3, 11-32</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
The tax collectors and sinners were all drawing near to hear Jesus.
And the Pharisees and the scribes murmured, saying, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“This man receives sinners and eats with them.” So he told them this parable: “There was a man who had two sons:</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and the younger of them said to his father, ‘Father, give me the share of property that falls to me.’ And he divided his living between them.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Not many days later, the younger son gathered all he had and took his journey into a far country, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and there he squandered his property in loose living. And when he had spent everything, a great famine arose in that country, and he began to be in want.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> So he went and joined himself to one of the citizens of that country, who sent him into his fields to feed swine. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And he would gladly have fed on the pods that the swine ate; and no one gave him anything.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>But when he came to himself he said, ‘How many of my father’s hired servants have bread enough and to spare, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>but I perish here with hunger! I will arise and go to my father, and I will say to him, “Father, I have sinned against heaven and before you;</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> I am no longer worthy to be called your son; treat me as one of your hired servants.”  “And he arose and came to his father. </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>But while he was yet at a distance, his father saw him and had compassion, and ran and embraced him and kissed him. And the son said to him,</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> ‘Father, I have sinned against heaven and before you; I am no longer worthy to be called your son.’ But the father said to his servants,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> ‘Bring quickly the best robe, and put it on him; and put a ring on his hand, and shoes on his feet; </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>and bring the fatted calf and kill it, and let us eat and make merry; for this my son was dead, and is alive again;</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> he was lost, and is found.’ And they began to make merry. “Now his elder son was in the field; </s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>and as he came and drew near to the house, he heard music and dancing.  And he called one of the servants and asked what this meant.  </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to him, ‘Your brother has come, and your father has killed the fatted calf, because he has received him safe and sound.’ But he was angry and refused to go in.</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384> His father came out and entreated him, but he answered his father, ‘Behold, these many years I have served you,</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>  and I never disobeyed your command; yet you never gave me a kid, that I might make merry with my friends.</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>  But when this son of yours came, who has devoured your living with harlots, you killed for him and fatted calf!’</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>“And he said to him, ‘Son, you are always with me, and all that is mine is yours.  It was fitting to make merry and be glad, </s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>for this your brother was dead, and is alive; he was lost, and is found.’”</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF6800D8"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"yoZuzN/Xa0qlgBJhz/l6fg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 25:14-30</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus told disciples this parable: </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“A man going on a journey called his servants and entrusted to them his property; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>to one he gave five talents, to another two,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> to another one, to each according to his ability.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Then he went away.
He who had received the five talents </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>went at once and traded with them; and he made five talents more. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> 
So also, he who had the two talents made two talents more. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> But he who had received the one talent went and dug in the ground and hid his master’s money.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Now after a long time the master of those servants came and settled accounts with them.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>  And he who had received the five talents came forward, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>bringing five talents more, saying, ‘Master,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> you delivered to me five talents; here I have made five talents more.’</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“His master said to him, ‘Well done, good and faithful servant; </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>you have been faithful over a little, I will set you over much; </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>enter into the joy of your master.’</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>“And he also who had the two talents came forward, saying, ‘Master, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>you delivered to me two talents; here I have made two talents more.’</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>“His master said to him, ‘Well done, good and faithful servant; </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>you have been faithful over a little, I will set you over much; </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>enter into the joy of your master.’</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>“He also who had received the one talent came forward, saying, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>‘Master, I knew you to be a hard man, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>reaping where you did not sow, and gathering where you did not winnow;</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> so I was afraid, and I went and hid your talent in the ground. </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> Here you have what is yours.’</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>“But his master answered him, </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>‘You wicked and slothful servant! You knew that I reap where I have not sowed, </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>and gather where I have not winnowed?</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>Then you ought to have invested my money with the bankers,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384> and at my coming I should have received what was my own with interest.</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384> So take the talent from him, </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>and give it to him who has the ten talents.</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384> For to every one who has will more be given, and he will have abundance; </s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>but from him who has not, even what he has will be taken away. </s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>And cast the worthless servant into the outer darkness,</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384> where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.’”</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"Jkh/Es0hd0SVbcfchPS8PA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Mark   		     Mark 9:2-10</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus took with him Peter and James and John,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and led them up a high mountain apart by themselves; and he was transfigured before them,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and his garments became glistening, intensely white, as no fuller on earth could bleach them.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>  And there appeared to them Elijah with Moses; and they were talking to Jesus.  And Peter said to Jesus, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Master, it is well that we are here; let us make three booths, one for you and one for Moses and one for Elijah.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> For he did not know what to say, for they were exceedingly afraid.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> And a cloud overshadowed them, and a voice came out of the cloud, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“This is my beloved Son; listen to him.” And suddenly looking around they no longer saw any one with them but Jesus only. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And as they were coming down the mountain, he charged them to tell no one what they had seen,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> until the Son of man should have risen from the dead. </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> So they kept the matter to themselves, questioning what the rising from the dead meant.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"1AgkqzyWLE2VuSo+RwCfbw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	      Luke 9:28b-36</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus took with him Peter and John and James, and went up on the mountain to pray.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And as he was praying, the appearance of his countenance was altered, and his clothing became dazzling white.  </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And behold, two men talked with him, Moses and Elijah, who appeared in glory and spoke of his exodus,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> which he was to accomplish at Jerusalem.  Now peter and those who were with him were heavy with sleep but kept awake,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> and they saw his glory and the two men who stood with him.  
And as the men were parting from him, Peter said to Jesus,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> “Master, it is well that we are here; let us make three booths, one for you and one for Moses and one for Elija” – not knowing what he said.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And he said this, a cloud came and overshadowed them; and they were afraid as they entered the cloud.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>  And a voice came out of the cloud, saying, “This is my Son, my Chosen; listen to him!”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And when the voice had spoken, Jesus was found alone. </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> And they kept silence and told no one in those days anything of what they had seen.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"jEDtN7Gei0OVuyT78oB+2Q",Verses:[{Style:{Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Luke   		Luke 1:26-38</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The angel Gabriel was sent from God to a city of Galilee named Nazareth,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> to a virgin betrothed to a man whose name was Joseph, of the house of David;</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and the virgin’s name was Mary. And he came to her and said, “Hail, full of grace, the Lord is with you!”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> But she was greatly troubled at the saying, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and considered in her mind what sort of greeting this might be.  And the angel said to her, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>“Do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favour with God. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> And behold, you will conceive in your womb and bear a son, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and you shall call his name Jesus.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>He will be great, and will be called the Son of the Most High;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and the Lord God will give to him the throne of his father David,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> and he will reign over the house of Jacob for ever;</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> and of his kingdom there will be no end.”
And Mary said to the angel, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“How will this be, since I do not know man?”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And the angel said to her,
“The Holy Spirit will come upon you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow you; </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>therefore the child to be born will be called holy, the Son of God.
And behold, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>your kinswoman Elizabeth in her old age has also conceived a son; </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>and this is the sixth month with her who was called barren.  For with God nothing will be impossible.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>And Mary said, “Behold, I am the handmaid of the Lord;</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> let it be to me according to your word.”
And the departed from her.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"MLys5xxNdkSUrgDybsAWAw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to John   		     John 3:14-21</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At the time:
Jesus said to Nicodemus, “As Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>so must the Son of man be lifted up, that whoever believes in him may have eternal life.”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For God so loved the world that he gave his only-begotten Son that whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life.  </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For God sent the Son into the world, not to condemn the world, but that the world might be saved through him. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> He who believes in him is not condemned; he who does not believe is condemned already, because he has not believed in the name of the only-begotten Son of God.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And this is the judgement, that the light has come into the world, and men love darkness rather than light, because their deeds were evil. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> For every one who does evil hates the light , and does not come to the light , lest his deeds should be exposed.  But he who does what is true comes to the light, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>that it may be clearly seen that his deeds have been wrought in God.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"5Ss0jkCwQUyL7j7i38ncXg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	              Mark 6:7-13</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus called to him the Twelve, and began to send them out two by two, and gave them authority over the unclean spirits. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> He charged them to take nothing for their journey except a staff; no bread, no bag, no money in their belts;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> but to wear sandals and not put on two tunics. And he said to them, “Where you enter a house, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>stay there until you leave the place.  And if any place will not receive you and they refuse to hear you,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> when you leave, shake off the dust that is on your feet for a testimony against them.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>So they went out and preached that men should repent. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And they cast our many demons, and anointed with oil many that were sick and healed them.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"xNUN0SQJw0Oydxms5EQZ5A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Mark   		     Mark 1:40-45</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
A leper came to Jesus begging him, and kneeling said to him, “If you will, you can make me clean.”</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Moved with pity, he stretched out his hand and touched him, and said to him, “I will; be clean.”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And immediately the leprosy left him, and he was made clean.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And he sternly charged him, and sent him away at once, and said to him, “See that you say nothing to any one;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> but go, show yourself to the priest, and offer for your cleansing what Moses commanded, for a proof to the people.”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>But he went out and began to talk freely about it, and to spread the news, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>so that Jesus could no longer openly enter a town, but was out in the country; and people came to him from every quarter.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"0XJKjDxehkWqhTN8IHPIXA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	      Luke 6:39-45</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus told his disciples a parable:
“Can a blind man lead a blind man? Will they not both fall into a pit? </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>A disciple is not above his teacher but every one when he is fully taught will be like his teacher.  </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Why do you see the speck that is in your brother’s eye, but do not notice the log that is in your own eye,’</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Or how can you say to your brother, ‘Brother, let me take out the speck that is in your eye,’ </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>when you yourself do not see the log that is in your own eye? You hypocrite, first take the log out of your own eye, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and then you will see clearly to take out the speck that is in your brother’s eye.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“For no good tree bears bad fruit, nor again does a bad tree bear good fruit; for each tree is known by its own fruit. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>For figs are not gathered from thorns, nor are grapes picked from a bramble bush. </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> The good man out of the good treasure of his heart produces good, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>and the evil man out of his evil treasure produces evil; for out the abundance of the heart his mouth speaks.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"j1bo0dAgU0SIHzJsloAKrw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	      Mark 10:35-45</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
James and John, the sons of Zebedee, came forward to Jesus, and said to him,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> “Teacher, we want you to do for us whatever we ask of you.” </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to them, “What do you want me to do for you?”And they said to him, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>“Grant us to sit, one at your right hand and one at your left, in your glory.”
But Jesus said to them, “You do not know what you are asking.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Are you able to drink the chalice that I drink, or to be baptized with the baptism with which I am baptized?”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And they said to him, “We are able.”
And Jesus said to them, “The chalice that I drink you will drink; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>and with the baptism with which I am baptized, you will be baptized; but to sit at my right hand or at my left is not mine to grant,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> but it is for those for whom it has been prepared.”And when the ten heard it, they began to be indignant at James and John.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>  And Jesus called them to him and said to them, “You know that those who are supposed to rule over the Gentiles lord it over them,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> and their great men exercise authority over them. But it shall not be so among you;</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> but whoever would be great among you must be your servant, and whoever would be first among you must be slave of all.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>  For the Son of man also came not to be served but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"qm48uQkGXkqkkaUfStBp9A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
A reading from the holy Gospel according to Mark   		Mark 13:33-37</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus said to his disciples, “Take heed, watch and pray; </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>for you do not know when the time will come.  It is like a man going on a journey, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>when he leaves home and puts his servants in charge, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>each with his work, and commands the doorkeeper to be on the watch. Watch therefore –</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> for you do not know when the master of the house will come, in the evening or at midnight, or at cockcrow, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>or in the morning – lest he come suddenly and find you asleep.  And what I say to you I say to all: Watch.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"550PK3cFJUGd+Yu0Q/hwUg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
A reading from the holy Gospel according to Mark   		Mark 1:1-8</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The beginning of the Gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>As it is written in Isaiah the prophet, 
“Behold, I send my messenger before your face, who shall prepare your way; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>the voice of one crying in the wilderness: 
Prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight –“</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>John the Baptist appeared in the wilderness, preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And there went out to him all the country of Judea, and all the people of Jerusalem; and they were baptized by him in the river Jordan,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> confessing their sins.
Now John was clothed with camel’s hair, and had a leather belt around his waist, and ate locusts and wild honey. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> And he preached, saying, “After me comes he who is mightier than I,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> the thong of whose sandals I am not worthy to stoop down and untie.  I have baptized you with water; </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>but he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"/79hjKDQL0K//UL/F+6vdw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John		John 15:26-27,16:12-15</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus said to his disciples,
“When the Counsellor comes,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> whom I shall send to you from the Father, even the Spirit of truth, who proceeds from the Father, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>he will bear witness to me; and you also are witnesses, because you have been with me from the beginning.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>“I have yet many things to say to you, but you cannot bear them now.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>  
When the Spirit of truth comes, he will guide you into all the truth; for he will not speak on his own authority, </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>but whatever he hears he will speak, and he will declare to you the things that are to come.</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>He will glorify me, for he will take what is mine and declare it to you.”</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"Clt1PRV27EasBpgy5/0bxA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 3:10-18</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>In those days 
Mary arose and went with haste into the hill country, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>to a city of Judah, and she entered the house of Zechariah and greeted Elizabeth.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And when Elizabeth heard the greeting of Mary, the child leaped in her womb; and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit and she exclaimed with a loud cry,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> “Blessed are you among women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb! And why is this granted me, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For behold, when the voice of your greeting came to my ears, the child in my womb leaped for joy.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And blessed is she who believed that there would be a fulfillment of what was spoken to her from the Lord.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"v2jk7V6Xf0eZKYiWAaEGyg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Mark 	Mark 1:7-11 </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At the time: 
John preached, saying, “After me comes he who is mightier than I,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> the thong of whose sandals I am not worthy to stoop down and untie.  I have baptised you with water; but he will baptise you with the Holy Spirit.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>In those days Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee and was baptized by John in the Jordan.
 
 And when he came up out of the water, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>immediately he saw the heavens opened and the Spirit descending upon him like a dove; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and a voice came from heaven, “You are my beloved Son; with you I am well pleased.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"zwlgBgzHiUaOpH+uyj1yeQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 4:21-30</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus began to say in the synagogue, “Today this Scripture has been fulfilled in your hearing.”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And all spoke well of him, and wondered at the gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth; and they said, “Is not this Joseph’s son?”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to them, “Doubtless you will quote to me this proverb, ‘Physician, heal yourself; </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>what we have heard you did at Capernaum, do here also in your own country.’</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>” And he said, “Truly, I say to you, no prophet is acceptable in his own country. But in truth, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>I tell you, there were many widows in Israel in the days of Elijah, when the heaven was shut up three years and six months, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>when there came a great famine over all the land; and Elijah was sent to none of them but only to Zarephath,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> in the land of Sidon, to a woman who was a widow. And there were many lepers in Israel in the time of the prophet Elisha;</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> and none of them was cleansed, but only Naaman the Syrian.”
When they heard this, all in the synagogue were filled with wrath.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>And they rose up and put him out of the city, and led him to the brow of the hill on which their city was built,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> that they might throw him down headlong. 
But passing through the midst of them he went away.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"zXK3/tz7VEuScbgnm50eNg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to John   		John1:6-8,19-28</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>There was a man sent from God, whose name was John.  He came for testimony,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> to bear witness to the light, that all might believe through him. He was not the light, but came to bear witness to the light.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And this is the testimony of John, when the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>“Who are you?
He confessed, he did not deny, but confessed, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>“I am not the Christ.”
And they asked him, “What then? Are you Elijah?”He said, “I am not.”
“Are you the prophet?”  and he answered, “No.”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>They said to him then, “Who are you?
Let us have an answer for those who sent us.  What do you say about yourself?”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>He said, “I am the voice of one crying in the wilderness, ‘Make straight the way of the Lord,’</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> as the prophet Isaiah said.”
Now they had been sent from the Pharisees. </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> They asked him, “Then why are you baptizing, if you are neither the Christ, nor Elijah, nor the prophet?”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>John answered them, “I baptize with water; but among you stands one whom you do not know, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>even he who comes after me, the thong of whose sandal I am not worthy to untie.”</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>This took place in Bethany beyond the Jordan, where John was baptizing.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"yB6+nUIpC06jQzqDhs1FjQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	            Mark 9:30-37</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus and his disciples went on from the mountain and passed through Galilee.
And he would not have any one know it;</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> for he was teaching his disciples, saying to them, “The Son of man will be delivered into the hands of men, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and they will kill him; and when he is killed, after three days he will rise.”
But they did not understand  the saying, and they were afraid to ask him.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And they came to Capernaum; and when he was in the house he asked them, “What were you discussing on the way?”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> But they were silent; for on the way they had discussed with one another who was the greatest.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he sat down and called the Twelve; and he said to them, “If anyone would be first, he must be last of all and servant of all.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And he took a child, and put him in the midst of them; and taking him in his arms, he said to them,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> “Whoever receives one such child in my name receives me; and whoever receives me, receives not me but him who sent me.”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"AHEKIzwWKEibYG69QqTF/A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 22:15-21</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
The Pharisees went and took counsel how to entangle Jesus in his talk.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> And they sent their disciples to him, along with the Herodians, saying,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> “Teacher, we know that you are true, and teach the way of God truthfully, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and care for no man; for you do not regard the position of men.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Tell us, then, what you think.  Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>But Jesus, aware of their malice, said, “Why put me to the test, you hypocrites?</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Show me the money for the tax.” And they brought him a coin. And Jesus said to them,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> “Whose likeness and inscription is this?”
They said, “Caesar’s Then he said to them,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> “Render therefore to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"I3xge5Uv3k2Gg/t5B+4bZw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	              Mark 6:1-6</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus came to his own country; and his disciples followed him.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And on the Sabbath he began to teach in the synagogue; and many who heard him were astonished, saying, “Where did this man get all this? </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>What is the wisdom given to him? 
What mighty works are wrought by his hands!</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mary and brother of James and Joses and Judas and Simon, and are not his sisters here with us?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And they took offence at him.
And Jesus said to them, 
“A prophet is not without honour,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> except in his own country, and among his own kin, and in his own house.”
And he could do no mighty work there,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> except that he laid his hands upon a few sick people and healed them.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>And he marveled because of their unbelief.  And he went about among the villages teaching.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"XKmi6BAJqUm+e3If4DnPvw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1}},
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 3:10-18</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
The multitudes asked John, “What then shall we do?”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And he answered them, “He who has two coats, let him share with him who has none; and he who has food, let him do likewise.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Tax collectors also came to be baptized, and said to him, “Teacher, what shall we do?”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to them, “Collect no more than is appointed you.”
Soldiers also asked him, “And we, what shall we do?”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to them, “Rob no one by violence or by false accusation, and be content with your wages.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>As the people were in expectation, and all men questioned in their hearts concerning John,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> whether perhaps he were the Christ, John answered them all, “I baptize you with water; </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>but he who is mightier than I is coming, the thong of whose sandals I am not worthy to untie;</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>His winnowing fork is in his hand, to clear his threshing floor, and to gather the wheat into his granary,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> but the chaff he will burn with unquenchable fire.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>So, with many other exhortations, he preached good news to the people.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"OcXey7XOaES8uVtumbfq2w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,Style:{Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	      Luke 6:27-38</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus said to his disciples, “I say to you that hear, Love your enemies, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>do good to those who hate you, bless those who curse you, pray for those who abuse you.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>To him who strikes you on the cheek, offer the other also; and from him who takes away your cloak do not withhold your coat as well.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>  Give to everyone who begs from you; and of him who takes away your goods do not ask them again.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And as you wish that men would do to you, do so to them. “If you love those who love you, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>what credit is that to you? For even sinners love those who love them.  And if you do good to those who do good to you, what credit is that to you? </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>For even sinners do the same. And if you lend to those from whom you hope to receive, what credit is that to you?  Even sinners lend to sinners,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> to receive as much again. But love your enemies, and do good, and lend, expecting nothing in return;</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> and your reward will be great, and you will be sons of the Most High; for he is kind to the ungrateful and the selfish.  Be merciful, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>even as you Father is merciful. “Judge not, and you will not be judged; condemn not, and you will be condemned;</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> forgive, and you will be forgiven; give, and it will be given to you; good measure, pressed down,</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> shaken together, running over, will be put into your lap. For the measure you give will be the measure you get back.”</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"j3H//6kVcUWpqvyS9mrYXg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	      Mark 10:46-52</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:As Jesus was leaving Jericho with his disciples and a great multitude, Bartimaeus, a blind beggar, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>the son of Timaeus, was sitting by the roadside.  And when he heard that it was Jesus of Nazareth, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>he began to cry out and say, “Jesus, Son of David, have mercy on me!” 
And many rebuked him,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> telling him to be silent; but he cried out all the more, “”Son of David, have mercy on me!”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus stopped and said, “Call him.” And they called the blind man, saying to him, “Take heart; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>rise, he is calling you.”And throwing off his cloak he sprang up and came to Jesus.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus said to him, “What do you want me to do for you?”
And the blind man said to him,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> “Master, let me receive my sight.”
And Jesus said to him, “Go your way; your faith has made you well.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And immediately he received his sight and followed him on the way.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"WbQEpFrQqU2xTyS2h1YOuw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 28:16-20 </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
The eleven disciples went to Galilee, to the mountain to which Jesus had directed them. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> 
And when they saw him they worshipped him; but some doubted.
And Jesus came and said to them,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> “All authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Go therefore and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>teaching them to observe aIl that I have commanded you; and behold, I am with you always, to the close of the age.”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"fgVrav7U/kq91b8gGZqINg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 20:1-9</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>On the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb early, while it was still dark,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and saw that the stone had been taken away from the tomb.  So she ran,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and went to Simon Peter and the other disciple, the one whom Jesus loved, and said to them, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>“They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him.”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Peter then came out with the other disciple, and they went toward the tomb.  They both ran, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>but the other disciple outran Peter and reached the tomb first; and stooping to look in, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>he saw the linen cloths lying there, but he did not go in.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Then Simon Peter came, following him, and went into the tomb; </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>he saw the linen cloths lying, and the napkin, which had been on his head,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> not lying with the linen cloths but rolled up in a place by itself.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Then the other disciple, who reached the tomb first, also went in, and he saw and believed;</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> for as yet they did not know the Scripture, that he must rise from the dead. </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"PsqlhfNcOU657vvZIipfoA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The Passion of our Lord Jesus Christ according to Mark   	Mark 14:1-15:47</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>N. It was two days before the Passover and the feast of Unleavened Bread.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And the chief priests and the scribes were seeking how to arrest Jesus by stealth, and kill him; for they said,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Not during the feast, lest there be a tumult of the people.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>N. And while he was at Bethany in the house of Simon the leper, as he sat at table,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> a woman came with an alabaster jar of ointment of pure nard, very costly, and she broke the jar and poured it over his head.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>But there were some who said to themselves indignantly, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Why was the ointment thus wasted? For this ointment might have been sold for more than three hundred denarii, and given to the poor.”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they reproached her.
But Jesus said, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>	“Let her alone; why do you trouble her? </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>She has done a beautiful thing to me.  For you always have the poor with you, and whenever you will,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> you can do good to them; but you will not always have me.  </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>She has done what she could; she has anointed my body beforehand for burying. 
And truly, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>I say to you, wherever the Gospel is preached in the whole world, what she has done will be told in memory of her.”</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>N. Then Judas Iscariot, who was one of the Twelve, went to the chief priests in order to betray him to them. </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> And when they heard it they were glad, and promised to give him money.  And he sought an opportunity to betray him. </s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384> 
And on the first day of Unleavened Bread, when they sacrificed the Passover Lamb, his disciples said to him, </s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Where will you have us go and prepare for you to eat the Passover?</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he sent two of his disciples, and said to them, </s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>* “Go into the city and a man carrying a jar of water will meet you; follow him, and wherever he enters, </s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>say to the householder,  ‘The Teacher says, Where is my guest room, where I am to eat the Passover with my disciples?’</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384> And he will show you a large upper room furnished and ready; there prepare for us.”</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>N. And the disciples set out and went to the city, and found it as he had told them; and they prepared the Passover.</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>And when it was evening he came with the Twelve.  And as they were at table eating, Jesus said, </s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>*”Truly, I say to you, one of you will betray me, one who is eating with me.” </s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384>N.  They began to be sorrowful, and to say to him one after another, </s>"},{ID:27,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Is it I?”
N. He said to them, </s>"},{ID:28,
Text:"<s1384>* “It is one of the Twelve, one who is dipping bread in the same dish with me.</s>"},{ID:29,
Text:"<s1384>  For the Son of man goes as it is written of him, but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed!</s>"},{ID:30,
Text:"<s1384>It would have been better for that man if he had not been born.”</s>"},{ID:31,
Text:"<s1384>N. And as they were eating, he took bread, and blessed, and broke it, and gave it to them, and said, </s>"},{ID:32,
Text:"<s1384>*”Take; this is my body.”
N. And he took a chalice, and when he had given thanks he gave it to them, and they all drank of it.  </s>"},{ID:33,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to them, 
* “This is my blood of the covenant, which is poured out for many.  </s>"},{ID:34,
Text:"<s1384>Truly, I say to you, I shall not drink again of the fruit of the vine until that day when I drink it new in the kingdom of God.”</s>"},{ID:35,
Text:"<s1384>N. And when they had sung a hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives. And Jesus said to them, </s>"},{ID:36,
Text:"<s1384>* “You will all fall away; for it is written, ‘I will strike the shepherd, and the sheep will be scattered.’ </s>"},{ID:37,
Text:"<s1384>But after I am raised up, I will go before you to Galilee.”</s>"},{ID:38,
Text:"<s1384>N. Peter said to him,
S. “Even though they all fall away, I will not.”</s>"},{ID:39,
Text:"<s1384>N. And Jesus said to him, 
* “Truly, I say to you, this very night, before the cock crows twice, you will deny me three times.”</s>"},{ID:40,
Text:"<s1384>N. But he said vehemently, 
S. “If I must die with you, I will not deny you.”</s>"},{ID:41,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they all said the same.
And they went to a place which was called Gethsemane; and he said to his disciples, 
* “Sit here, while I pray.”</s>"},{ID:42,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he took with him Peter and James and John, and began to be greatly distressed and troubled.  And he said to them, </s>"},{ID:43,
Text:"<s1384>* “My soul is very sorrowful even to death; remain here, and watch.”</s>"},{ID:44,
Text:"<s1384>N. And going a little farther he fell on the ground and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass from him.</s>"},{ID:45,
Text:"<s1384>And he said,
* “Abba, Father, all things are possible to you; remove this chalice from me; yet not what I will, but what you will.”</s>"},{ID:46,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he came and found them sleeping, and he said to Peter, </s>"},{ID:47,
Text:"<s1384>* “Simon, are you asleep? Could you not watch one hour? Watch and pray that you may not enter into temptation; </s>"},{ID:48,
Text:"<s1384>the spirit  indeed is willing, but the flesh is weak.”</s>"},{ID:49,
Text:"<s1384>N. And again he went away and prayed, saying the same words.  And again he came and found them sleeping,</s>"},{ID:50,
Text:"<s1384> for their eyes were very heavy; and they did not know what to answer him.  And he came the third time, and said to them, </s>"},{ID:51,
Text:"<s1384>* “Are you still sleeping and taking your rest? It is enough; the hour has come; </s>"},{ID:52,
Text:"<s1384>the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.  Rise, let us be going; see, my betrayer is at hand.”</s>"},{ID:53,
Text:"<s1384>N. And immediately, while he was still speaking, Judas came, one of the Twelve, </s>"},{ID:54,
Text:"<s1384>and with him a crowd with swords and clubs, from the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.</s>"},{ID:55,
Text:"<s1384> Now the betrayer had given them a sign, saying, </s>"},{ID:56,
Text:"<s1384>S. “The one I shall kiss is the man; seize him and lead him away safely.”</s>"},{ID:57,
Text:"<s1384>N. And when he came, , he went up to him at once, and said, </s>"},{ID:58,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Master!”
N. And he kissed him.
And they laid hands on him and seized him.
But one of those who stood by drew his sword, </s>"},{ID:59,
Text:"<s1384>and struck the slave of the high priests and cut off his ear. And Jesus said to them, </s>"},{ID:60,
Text:"<s1384>* “Have you come out as against a robber, with swords and clubs to capture me? </s>"},{ID:61,
Text:"<s1384>Day after day I was with you in the temple teaching, and you did not seize me.   But let the Scriptures be fulfilled.”</s>"},{ID:62,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they all deserted him and fled.
And a young man followed him, with nothing but a linen cloth about his body; </s>"},{ID:63,
Text:"<s1384>and they seized him, but he left the linen cloth and ran away naked.</s>"},{ID:64,
Text:"<s1384>And they led Jesus to the high priests; and all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes were assembled.  </s>"},{ID:65,
Text:"<s1384>And Peter had followed him at a distance, right into the courtyard of the high priest; </s>"},{ID:66,
Text:"<s1384>and he was sitting with the guards, and warming himself at the fire. </s>"},{ID:67,
Text:"<s1384> Now the chief priests and the whole council sought testimony against Jesus to put him to death; </s>"},{ID:68,
Text:"<s1384>but they found none. For many bore false witness against him, and their witness did not agree.</s>"},{ID:69,
Text:"<s1384>  And some stood up and bore false witness against him, saying, </s>"},{ID:70,
Text:"<s1384>S. “We heard him say, ‘I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and in three days I will build another, not made with hands.’”</s>"},{ID:71,
Text:"<s1384>N. Yet not even so did their testimony agree.</s>"},{ID:72,
Text:"<s1384>And the high priest stood up in their midst, and asked Jesus, </s>"},{ID:73,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Have you no answer to make? What is it that these men testify against you?</s>"},{ID:74,
Text:"<s1384>N. But he was silent and made no answer.   Again the high priest asked him, </s>"},{ID:75,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Are you the Christ, the Son of the Blessed?”</s>"},{ID:76,
Text:"<s1384>N. And Jesus said, 
* “I am; and you will see the Son of man sitting at the right hand of Power, and coming with the clouds of heaven.”</s>"},{ID:77,
Text:"<s1384>N. And the high priest tore his clothes, and said, </s>"},{ID:78,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Why do we still need witnesses? You have heard his blasphemy. What is your decision?</s>"},{ID:79,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they all condemned him as deserving death.  
And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to strike him, saying to him, </s>"},{ID:80,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Prophesy!”
N. And the guards received him with blows.
And as Peter was below in the courtyard,</s>"},{ID:81,
Text:"<s1384> one of the maids of the high priest came; and seeing Peter warming himself, she looked at him, and said, </s>"},{ID:82,
Text:"<s1384>S. “You also were with the Nazarene, Jesus.”</s>"},{ID:83,
Text:"<s1384>N. But he denied it, saying, 
S. “I neither know nor understand what you mean.”</s>"},{ID:84,
Text:"<s1384>N. And he went out into the gateway.
And the maid saw him, and began again to say to the bystanders, </s>"},{ID:85,
Text:"<s1384>S. “This man is one of them.”
N. But again he denied it.
And after a little while again the bystanders said to Peter, </s>"},{ID:86,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Certainly you are one of them; for you are a Galilean.”</s>"},{ID:87,
Text:"<s1384>N. But he began to invoke a curse on himself and to swear, </s>"},{ID:88,
Text:"<s1384>S. “I do not know this man of whom you speak.”</s>"},{ID:89,
Text:"<s1384>N. And immediately the cock crowed a second time.</s>"},{ID:90,
Text:"<s1384>And Peter remembered how Jesus had said to him, “Before the cock crows twice,</s>"},{ID:91,
Text:"<s1384> you will deny me three times.” And he broke down and wept.</s>"},{ID:92,
Text:"<s1384>And as soon as it was morning the chief priests, with the elders and scribes,</s>"},{ID:93,
Text:"<s1384> and the whole council held a consultation; and they bound Jesus and led him away and delivered him to Pilate.</s>"},{ID:94,
Text:"<s1384>And Pilate asked him, 
S. “Are you the King of the Jews?”
N. And he answered him, </s>"},{ID:95,
Text:"<s1384>* “You have said so.”
N. And the chief priests accused him of many things. And Pilate again asked him,</s>"},{ID:96,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Have you no answer to make?
See how many charges they bring against you.”</s>"},{ID:97,
Text:"<s1384>N. But Jesus made no further answer, so that Pilate wondered.</s>"},{ID:98,
Text:"<s1384>Now at the feast he used to release for them one prisoner for whom they asked. </s>"},{ID:99,
Text:"<s1384> 
And among the revels in prison, who had committed murder in the insurrection, there was a man called Barabbas.</s>"},{ID:100,
Text:"<s1384> And the crowd came up and began to ask Pilate to do as he always did for them. And he answered them, </s>"},{ID:101,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Do you want me to release for you the King of the Jews?</s>"},{ID:102,
Text:"<s1384>N. For he perceived that it was out of envy that the chief priests had delivered him up.</s>"},{ID:103,
Text:"<s1384>  But the chief priests stirred up the crowd to have him release for them Barabbas instead. </s>"},{ID:104,
Text:"<s1384>And Pilate again said to them, </s>"},{ID:105,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Then what shall I do with the man whom you call the King of the Jews?</s>"},{ID:106,
Text:"<s1384>N. And they cried out again, 
S. “Crucify him.”</s>"},{ID:107,
Text:"<s1384>N. And Pilate said to them, 
S. “Why, what evil has he done?”</s>"},{ID:108,
Text:"<s1384>N. But they shouted all the more, 
S. “Crucify him.”</s>"},{ID:109,
Text:"<s1384>N. So Pilate, wishing to satisfy the crowd, released for them Barabbas; </s>"},{ID:110,
Text:"<s1384>and having scoured Jesus, he delivered him to be crucified.</s>"},{ID:111,
Text:"<s1384>And the soldiers led him away inside the palace (that is, the praetorium); </s>"},{ID:112,
Text:"<s1384>and they called together the whole battalion.  </s>"},{ID:113,
Text:"<s1384> And they clothed him in a purple cloak, and plaiting a crown of thorns they put it on him. </s>"},{ID:114,
Text:"<s1384> And they began to salute him, 
S. “Hail, King of the Jews!”</s>"},{ID:115,
Text:"<s1384>N, And they struck his head with a reed, and spat upon him, and they knelt down in homage to him.</s>"},{ID:116,
Text:"<s1384>And when they had mocked him, they stripped him of the purple cloak, </s>"},{ID:117,
Text:"<s1384>and put his own clothes on him.  And they led him out to crucify him.</s>"},{ID:118,
Text:"<s1384>And they compelled a passer-by, Simon of Cyrene, </s>"},{ID:119,
Text:"<s1384>who was coming in from the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to carry his cross.</s>"},{ID:120,
Text:"<s1384>And they brought him to the place called Golgotha (which means the place of a skull).  </s>"},{ID:121,
Text:"<s1384> And they offered him wine mingled with myrrh; but he did not take it.</s>"},{ID:122,
Text:"<s1384>And they crucified him, and divided his garments among them, casting lots for them, to decide what each should take.</s>"},{ID:123,
Text:"<s1384>  And it was the third hour, when they crucified him.  </s>"},{ID:124,
Text:"<s1384>And the inscription of the charge against him read, “The King of the Jews.” And with him they crucified two robbers, </s>"},{ID:125,
Text:"<s1384>one on his right and one on his left. And those who passed by derided him, shaking their heads and saying,</s>"},{ID:126,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Aha! You who would destroy the temple and build it in three days, save yourself, and come down from the cross!”</s>"},{ID:127,
Text:"<s1384>N. So also the chief priests mocked him to one another with the scribes, saying,</s>"},{ID:128,
Text:"<s1384>S. “He saved others; he cannot save himself. </s>"},{ID:129,
Text:"<s1384>Let the Christ, the King of Israel, come down now from the cross, that we may see and believe.”</s>"},{ID:130,
Text:"<s1384>N. Those who were crucified with him also reviled him.</s>"},{ID:131,
Text:"<s1384>And when the sixth hour had come there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.</s>"},{ID:132,
Text:"<s1384> And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, </s>"},{ID:133,
Text:"<s1384>* “Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani?”
N. which means,</s>"},{ID:134,
Text:"<s1384>* “My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?”</s>"},{ID:135,
Text:"<s1384>N. And some of the bystanders hearing it said, 
S. “Behold, he is calling Elijah.”
N. And one ran and, filling a sponge full of vinegar,</s>"},{ID:136,
Text:"<s1384> put it on a reed and gave it to him to drink, saying.</s>"},{ID:137,
Text:"<s1384>S. “Wait, let us see whether Elijah will come to take him down.”</s>"},{ID:138,
Text:"<s1384>N. And Jesus uttered a loud cry, and breathed his last.  </s>"},{ID:139,
Text:"<s1384>And the curtain of the temple was torn in two, from top to bottom. </s>"},{ID:140,
Text:"<s1384>And when the centurion, who stood facing him, saw that he thus breathed his last, he said, </s>"},{ID:141,
Text:"<s1384>S.  “Truly this man was the Son of God!”
N. There were also women looking on from afar, among whom were Mary Magdalene,</s>"},{ID:142,
Text:"<s1384> and Mary the mother James the younger and of Joses, and Salome, </s>"},{ID:143,
Text:"<s1384>who, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered to him; </s>"},{ID:144,
Text:"<s1384>and also many other women who came up with him to Jerusalem.</s>"},{ID:145,
Text:"<s1384>And when evening had come, since it was the day of Preparation, that is, the day before the Sabbath, </s>"},{ID:146,
Text:"<s1384>Joseph of Arimathea, a respected member of the council, who was also himself looking for the kingdom of God, took courage and went to Pilate, </s>"},{ID:147,
Text:"<s1384>and asked for the body of Jesus.  
And Pilate wondered  if he were already dead;</s>"},{ID:148,
Text:"<s1384> and summoning the centurion, he asked him whether he was already dead. </s>"},{ID:149,
Text:"<s1384>And when he learned from the centurion that he was dead, he granted the body to Joseph.</s>"},{ID:150,
Text:"<s1384>And he bought a linen shroud, and taking him down, </s>"},{ID:151,
Text:"<s1384>wrapped him in the linen shroud, and laid him in a tomb which had been hewn out of the rock; </s>"},{ID:152,
Text:"<s1384>and he rolled a stone against the door of the tomb. </s>"},{ID:153,
Text:"<s1384> Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses saw where he was laid.</s>"},{ID:154,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"l4OCgzwiZEGoh0xh1Df/Ig",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Matthew 		Matthew 13:54-58</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Coming to his own country, Jesus taught them in their synagogue, so that they were astonished, and said,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> “Where did this man get this wisdom and these mighty works? Is not this the carpenter’s son? Is not his mother called Mary?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> And are not his brethren James and Joseph and Simon and Judas? </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And are not all his sisters with us? Where then did this man get all this?
” </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And they took offence at him.  But Jesus said to them, “A prophet is not without honour except in his own country and in his own house.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> 
And he did not do many mighty works there, because of their unbelief.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"CYQpyg22wUaeStO3ZLifEA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 23:1-12</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus said to the crowds and to his disciples, “The scribes and the Pharisees sit on Moses’ seat; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>so practice and observe whatever they tell you, but not what they do; for they preach, but do not practice. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> They bind heavy burdens, hard to bear, and lay them on men’s shoulders;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> but they themselves will not move them with their finger.  </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>They do all their deeds to be seen by men; for they make their phylacteries broad and their fringes long, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>and they love the place of honour at feasts and the best seats in the synagogues,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> and salutations in the market places, and being called rabbi by men.  </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>But you are not to be called rabbi, for you have one teacher, and you are all brethren. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>And call no man your father on earth, who is in heaven. Neither be called masters, for you have one master,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> the Christ.  He who is greatest among you shall be your servant; </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>whoever exalts himself will be humbled, and whoever humbles himself will be exalted.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"1DWfcvN6/0GfM1WvuDP2OA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	    Mark 7:1-8,14-15,21-23</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
When the Pharisees gathered together to Jesus with some of the scribes, who had come from Jerusalem,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> they saw that some of his disciples ate with hands defiled, that is unwashed.
(For the Pharisees,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and all the Jews, do not eat unless they wash their hands, observing the tradition of the elders; </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and when they come from the market place, they do not eat unless they purify themselves; and there are many other traditions which they observe,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> the washing of cups and pots and vessels of bronze.) And the Pharisees and the scribes asked him, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Why do your disciples not live according to the tradition of the elders, but eat with hands defiled?” </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to them, “Well did Isaiah prophesy of you hypocrites, as it is written, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>‘This people honours me with their lips, but their heart is far from me; in vain do they worship me, teaching as doctrines the precepts of men.’ </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>You leave the commandment of God, and hold fast the tradition of men.”
And he called the people to him again, and said to them, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>“Hear me, all of you, and understand: there is nothing outside a man which by going into him can defile him; </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>but the things which come out of a man are what defile him.
“For from within, out of the heart of man, come evil thoughts, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>fornication, theft, murder, adultery, coveting, wickedness, deceit, licentiousness, envy, slander, pride, foolishness.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>All these evil things come from within, and they defile a man.”</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"HnjIVhRddk+jbad2rq2Lxg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 20:1-9</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>On the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb early, while it was still dark, and saw that the stone had been taken away from the tomb.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  So she ran, and went to Simon Peter and the other disciple, the one whom Jesus loved, and said to them,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> “They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him.” Peter then came out with the other disciple,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and they went toward the tomb.  They both ran, but the other disciple outran Peter and reached the tomb first; and stooping to look in,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> he saw the linen cloths lying there, but he did not go in.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Then Simon Peter came, following him, and went into the tomb; he saw the linen cloths lying, and the napkin, which had been on his head,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> not lying with the linen cloths but rolled up in a place by itself.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Then the other disciple, who reached the tomb first, also went in, and he saw and believed;</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> for as yet they did not know the Scripture, that he must rise from the dead. </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"nshYJ5OGkEauPUqV7mx1ZA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	      John 8:1-11</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus went to the Mount of Olives.  Early in the morning he came again to the temple; all the people came to him, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and he sat down and taught them.  The scribes and the Pharisees brought a woman who had been caught in adultery,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and placing her in their midst they said to him, “Teacher, this woman has been caught in the act of adultery. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Now in the law Moses commanded us to stone such.  What do you say about her?”
This they said to test him,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> that they might have some charge to bring against him.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus bent down and wrote with his finger on the ground.  And as they continued to ask him, he stood up and said to them, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>“Let him who is without sin among you be the first to throw a stone at her.” And once more he bent down and wrote with his finger on the ground.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>  But when they heard it, they went away, one by one, beginning with the eldest, and Jesus was left alone with the woman standing before him.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus looked up and said to her, “Woman, where are they? Has no one condemned you?” She said, “No one, Lord.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>And Jesus said, “Neither do I condemn you; go, and do not sin again.” </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"xGnXeTXTz06hwiD46hyl7g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Mark   	              Mark 6:30-34</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
The apostles returned to Jesus, and told him all that they had done and taught.  
And he said to them,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> “Come away by yourselves to a lonely place, and rest a while.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For many were coming and going, and they had no leisure even to eat.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And they went away in the boat to a lonely place by themselves.
Now many saw them going, and knew them,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> and they ran there on foot from all the towns, and got there ahead  of them.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>As he landed he saw a great throng, and he had compassion on them,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> because they were like sheep without a shepherd; and he began to teach them many things.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"oifcd/OXf0C4gY/q0+r4yA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1076>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1846>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 25:31-46</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1846>At that time: 
Jesus said to his disciples, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1846>“When the Son of man comes in his glory,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1846> and all the angels with him, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1846>then he will sit on his glorious throne.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1846> Before him will be gathered all the nations,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1846> and he will separate them one from another </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1846>as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1846> and he will place the sheep at his right hand, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1846>but the goats at the left.
“Then the King will say to those at his right hand, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1846>‘Come, O blessed of my Father, inherit the kingdom </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1846>prepared for you from the foundation of the world;</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1846> for I was hungry and you gave me food, I was thirsty and you gave me drink,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1846> I was a stranger and you welcomed me,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1846> I was naked and you clothed me, I was sick and you visited me, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1846>I was in prison and you came to me.’</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1846>“Then the righteous will answer him, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1846>‘Lord, when did we see you hungry and feed you, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1846>or thirsty and give you drink?</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1846> And when did we see you a stranger and welcome you,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1846> or naked and clothe you? </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1846>And when did we see you sick or in prison and visit you?</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1846>“And the King will answer them, ‘Truly, I say to you, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1846>as you did it to one of the least of these my brethren, you did it to me.’</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1846>Then he will say to those at his left hand, ‘Depart from me, you cursed,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1846> into the eternal fire prepared for the devil and his angels; </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1846>for I was hungry and you gave me no food, I was thirsty and you gave me no drink,</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1846> I was a stranger and you did not welcome me, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1846>naked and you did not clothe me,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1846> sick and in prison and you did not visit me.’</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1846>“Then they also will answer, </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1846>‘Lord, when did we see you hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1846> and did not minister to you?</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1846>“Then he will answer them, ‘Truly,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1846> I say to you, as you did it not to one of the least of these,</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1846> you did it not to me.’</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1846>“And they will go away into eternal punishment, </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1846>but the righteous into eternal life.”</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1846>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"XbqrZ+Vq80aGMZBAhLFxgg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 21: 1-19</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus revealed himself again to the disciples by the Sea of Tiberias; and he revealed himself in this way. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Simon Peter, Thomas called the Twin, Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, the sons of Zebedee, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and two others of his disciples were together.  Simon Peter said to them, “I am going fishing.” </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>They said to him, “We will go with you.” They went out and got into the boat; but that night they caught nothing.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Just as day was breaking, Jesus stood on the beach; yet the disciples did not know that it was Jesus. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus said to them, “Children, have you any fish?”They answered him, “No.”  He said to them, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>“Cast the net on the right side of the boat, and you will find some.” So they cast it, and now they were not able to haul it in, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>for the quantity of fish.  That disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, “It is the Lord!”
When Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> he put on his clothes, for he was stripped for work, and sprang into the sea. But the other disciples came in the boat,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> dragging the net full of fish, for they were not far from the land, but about a hundred yards off.
When they got out on land, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>they saw a charcoal fire there, with fish lying on it, and bread. Jesus said to them, “Bring some of the fish that you have just caught.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> So Simon Peter went aboard and hauled the net ashore, full of large fish, a hundred and fifty-three of them; </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>and although there were so many, the net was not torn.  Jesus said to them, “Come and have breakfast.”</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> Now none of the disciples dared to ask him, “Who are you?” They knew it was the Lord.  Jesus came and took the bread and gave it to them,</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> and so with the fish.  This was now the third time that Jesus was revealed to the disciples after he was raised from the dead.  </s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>When they had finished breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, “Simon, son of John, do you love me more than these?” He said to him, </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>“Yes, Lord; you know that I love you.” He said to him, “Feed my lambs.” A second time he said to him, “Simon, son of John,</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384> do you love me?” He said to him, “Yes, Lord; you know that I love you.”</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>He said to him, “Tend my sheep.” He said to him the third time, “Simon, son of John, do you love me?”</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384> Peter was grieved because he said to him the third time, “Do you love me?” And he said to him, “Lord, you know everything; you know that I love you.”</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384> Jesus said to him, “Feed my sheep.  Truly, truly, I say to you, when you were young, you fastened your own belt and walked where you would;</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384> but when you are old, you will stretch out your hands, and another will fasten your belt for you and bring you where you do not wish to go.” </s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>(This he said to show by what death he was to glorify God.) And after this he said to him, “Follow me.”</s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"og3M/LlJv02xdQ/YoJg9vA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to John.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>at that time:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Many of the Jews who had come with Mary
and had seen what Jesus did, believed in him;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>but some of them went to the Pharisees
and told them what Jesus had done.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>So the chief priests and the Pharisees
Gathered the council, and said. “What are we to do?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For this man performs many signs
If we let him go on like this, everyone will believe in him,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and the Romans will come
And destroy both our holy place and our nation.”But one of them, Caiaphas, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>who was high priest that year, said to them. “You know nothis at all;</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>You do not understand that it is expedient for youThat one man should die for the people
And that the whole nation should not perish.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>He did not say this of his own accord,
But being high priest that year
He prophesied that Jesus should die for the nation,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>And not for the nation only,But to gather into oneThe children of God who are scattered abroad.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>So from that day onThey took counsel about how to put him to death.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus therefore no longer went about openly among the Jews,
But went from there to the country near the wilderness,</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>To a town called Ephraim;And there he stayed with the disciples.Now the Passover of the Jews was at hand,</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>And many went up from the country to JerusalemBefore the Passover,To purify themselves.</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>They were looking for Jesus
And saying to one another as they stood in the temple,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>“what do you think?That he will not come to the feast?”Now the chief priests and the Pharisees had given ordersThat if anyone knew where he was,</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>He should let them know, so that they might arrest him.</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"gbF0NwN7QEuHZgVYAqmehA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	      Luke 4:1-13</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, returned from the Jordan, and was led by the Spirit for forty days in the wilderness, tempted by the devil.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And he ate nothing in those days; and when they were ended, he was hungry.
The devil said to him, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>“If you are the Son of God, command this stone to become bread.” And Jesus answered him,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> “It is written, ‘Man shall not live by bread alone.’”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And the devil took him up, and showed him all the kingdoms of the world in a moment of time, and said to him,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> “To you I will give all this authority and their glory; for it has been delivered to me, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and I give it to whom I will. If you, then, will worship me, it shall all be yours.” And Jesus answered him, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“It is written, ‘You shall worship the Lord your God, and him only shall you serve.” And he took him to Jerusalem, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>and set him on the pinnacle of the temple, and said to him, “If you are the Son of God, throw yourself down from here; for it is written,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> ‘He will give his angels charge of you, to guard you,’ and ‘On their hands they will bear you up, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>lest you strike you foot against a stone.’” And Jesus answered him, “It is said, ‘You shall not tempt the Lord your God.’” </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>And when the devil had ended every temptation, he departed from him until an opportune time.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"DVItyvLfjky8a4tAYEbCxA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	         Luke 6:17,20-26</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
Jesus came down with the Twelve and stood on a level place, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>with a great crowd of his disciples and a great multitude of people from all Judea and Jerusalem and the seacoast  of Tyre and Sidon, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> who came to hear him and to be healed of their diseases.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And he lifted up his eyes on his disciples and said:</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Blessed are you poor, for yours is the kingdom of God. “Blessed are you that hunger now,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> for you shall  be satisfied. “Blessed are you that weep now, for you shall laugh.
“Blessed are you when men hate you,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> and when they exclude  you and revile you, and cast out your name as evil,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> on account of the Son of man! Rejoice in that day, and leap for joy,</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> for behold, your reward is great in heaven; for so their fathers did to the prophets.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>“But woe to you that are rich, for your have received your consolation.
“Woe to you that are full now, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>for you shall hunger.
“Woe  to you that laugh now, for you shall mourn and weep.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>“Woe to you, when all men speak well of you, for so their fathers did to the false prophets.”</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"Mis9mUzI50K6TtRpXp6nrw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL
     John 1:35-42</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to John  		 </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time: 
John was standing with two of his disciples; and he looked at Jesus as he walked, and said, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“Behold, the Lamb of God!”
The two disciples heard him say this, and they followed Jesus.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus turned, and saw them following, and said to them, “What do you seek?”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And they said to him, “Rabbi” (which means Teacher), “where are you staying?”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>He said to them, “Come and see.”
They came and saw where he was staying; and they stayed with him that day, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>for it was about the tenth hour.
One of the two who heard John speak, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and followed him, was Andrew, Simon Peter’s brother.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He first found his brother Simon, and said to him, “We have found the Messiah” (which means Christ).</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>He brought him to Jesus.
Jesus looked at him, and said, “So you are Simon the son of John?</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>You shall be called Cephas” (which means Peter).</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"lQNJ6lhID0CgLQzZGSno/g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	           John 18:33b-37</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
Pilate said to Jesus, “Are you the King of the Jews?”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus answered, “Do you say this of your own accord,  or did others say it to you about me?”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Pilate answered, “Am I a Jew?
Your own nation and the chief priests have handed you over to me; </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>what have you done?”
Jesus answered, “My kingship is not  of this world; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>if my kingship were of this world, my servants would fight, that I might not be handed over to the Jews;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> but my kingship is not from the world.”
Pilate said to him, “So you are a king?”
Jesus answered, “You say that I am a king. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>For this I was born, and for this I have come into the world, to bear witness to the truth.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Every one who is of the truth hears my voice.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"KIysKoHo50ajX8OPoHxbBQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	      John 13:31-33a,34-35</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>When Judas had gone out (from the upper room,)
Jesus said,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“Now is the Son of man glorified, and in him God is glorified;  if God is glorified  in him,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>  God will also glorify him in himself, and glorify him at once.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Little children, yet a little while I am with you.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“A new commandment I give to you, that you love one another even as I have loved you, that you also love one another.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>By this all men will know that you are my disciples, if you have love for one another.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"3JRf4N9dPkm8vytj8mNHxQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to Luke   	      Luke 13:1-9</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>There were some present at that very time who told Jesus of the Galileans whose blood pilate had mingled with their sacrifices. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> And he answered them. “Do you think that these Galileans were worse sinners than all the other Galileans, because they suffered thus?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>I tell you, No; but unless you repent you will all likewise perish.  Or those eighteen upon whom the tower in Siloam fell and killed them,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> do you think that they were worse offenders that all the others who dwelt in Jerusalem?
I tell you,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> No; but unless you repent you will all likewise perish.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And he told this parable:
“A man had a fig tree planted in his vineyard; and he came seeking fruit on it and found none.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to the vinedresser, ‘Behold, these three years I have come seeking fruit on this fig tree, and I find none.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Cut it down; why should it use up the ground?’
“And he answered him, ‘Let it alone, sir, this year also, till I dig about it and put on manure.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> And if it bears fruit next year, well and good; but if not, you can cut it down.’”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"fZ9aufRPc06gkZt5i1y0uA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the holy Gospel according to Matthew		Matthew 22:34-40</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>At that time:
When the Pharisees heard that Jesus had silenced the Sadducees, they came together.  And one of them, a lawyer, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>asked him a question, to test him. “Teacher, which is the great commandment in the law?”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And he said to him, 
“You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>This is the great and first commandment. And a second is like it, You shall love your neighbor as yourself. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> On these two commandments depend all the law and the prophets.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"UWHcNQRLWkacP6TooRhQgA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Holy Gospel according to John   	              John 20:19-31</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>On the evening of that day, the first day of the week, the doors being shut where the disciples were, for fear of the Jews, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus came and stood among them and said to them, “Peace be with you.” When he had said this, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>he showed them his hands and his side.  Then the disciples were glad when they saw the Lord. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus said to them again, “Peace be with you.  As the Father has sent me even so I send you.” </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And when he had said this, he breathed on them, and said to them, “Receive the Holy Spirit.  If you forgive the sins of any, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>they are forgiven; if you retain the sins of any, they are retained.” Now Thomas, one of the Twelve, called the Twin,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> was not with them when Jesus came. So the other disciples told him, “We have seen the Lord.” But he said to them, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“Unless I see in his hands the print of the nails, and place my finger in the mark of the nails, and place my hand in his side, I will not believe.”  Eight days later, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>his disciples were again in the house, and Thomas was with them.  The doors were shut, but Jesus came and stood among them, and said, “Peace be with you.”</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> Then he said to Thomas, “Put your finger here, and see my hands; and put out your hand, and place it in my side; do not be faithless, but believing.” </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> Thomas answered him, “My Lord and my God!”  Jesus said to him, “You have believed because you have seen me.  Blessed are those who have not seen and yet believe.”</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>  Now Jesus did many other signs in the presence of the disciples, which are not written in this book;</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> but these are written that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that believing you may have life in his name.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>The Gospel of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GOSPEL
"},{Guid:"NY6hPH1Kj0iXtR6dJFEEDQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GŨTHOMA INJIRI  YA MŨTHURE LUKA:</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>Na matukũ mao na gũtherio thutha wa gũciara maahinga, o ta ũrĩa gwaathanirũo nĩ Musa-rĩ (Maria na Joseph) </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>makĩambata Jerusalem magakanengere Mwathani, o ta ũrĩa kwandĩkĩtwo Maandĩko-inĩ  ma irĩra cia Mwathani atĩrĩ,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> O kahĩĩ karĩa gakarigithathwo gagatuwo kaana gatheru ka Mwathani, na ningĩ marute ihaki o ta ũrĩa gũtuĩtwo Maandĩko-inĩ ma irĩra cia Mwathani atĩrĩ,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> Nĩ ndirahũgĩ igĩrĩ, kana ndutura igĩrĩ.  Na rĩrĩ, nĩ kwarĩ  mũndũ watũire Jerusalem wetagwo Simeoni;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> nake aarĩ mũthingu na mũigua- Ngai, na nĩ aatanyĩte hindĩ ĩrĩa Israeli makanyamarũrũo:</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> na Muoyo Mũtheru aarĩ hamwe nake.  Na mũndũ ũcio nĩ aaguũrĩirio ni Muoyo Mũtheru atĩ ndagakua atonete Kristũ ũrĩa wa Mwathani. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Nake agĩtonya hekarũ ya Ngai  arĩ na Muoyo Mũtheru: na rĩrĩa aciari a kaana kau, Yesu,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> maagatwarire hekarũ ya Ngai thĩinĩ, nĩ getha magageke kũringana na mũtugo  wa watho-rĩ, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>hindĩ ĩo Simeoni agĩkaiyũkia moko-inĩ make, akĩgatha Ngai akiuga atĩrĩ: “ Rĩu Mwathani nĩ hindĩ ũkũnjugĩra ũhoro, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>niĩ ngombo yaku, ‘ thiĩ na thayũ o ta ũrĩa wanjĩrire; nĩ gũkorũo maitho makwa nũ monete ũhonokio waku, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>ũrĩa wathondekire mbere ya irĩndĩ ciothe; nĩguo ũtheri wa kũguũrĩrio andũ a Ndũrĩrĩ, o na riri wa andũ aku Israeli”.  </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Nao ithe na nyina nĩ maagegaga nĩ ũndũ wa maũndũ marĩa maaririo nĩ ũndũ wake; nake Simeoni akĩmarathima,</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> akĩĩra Maria, nyina, Atĩrĩrĩ, kaana gaka nĩ gatuĩtwo ga kũgũithia o na gũũkĩria andũ aingĩ a Israeli;</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> ningĩ gatuĩke kĩmenyithia kĩrĩa kĩrĩtendagwo; o na rĩrĩ, rũhiũ rũa mbaara nĩ rũgagũtũrĩkia ngoro wee mwene , </s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>nĩguo meciria ma ngoro nyingĩ maguũke.  
Na nĩ kwarĩ mũtumia mũnabii wetago Anna, mwarĩ wa Fanueli, wa mũhĩrĩga wa Asher, nake aarĩ mũkũrũ mũno;</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> aaikarire na mũthuriwe mĩaka mũgwanja kuuma ahika, na nĩ aatũire arĩ wa  ndigwa mĩaka ĩngĩ mĩrongo ĩnana na ĩna; mũtumia ũcio-rĩ, ndoimaga hekarũ,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384> no aatũire aturagiria NGai ndu akamũhoyaga ũtukũ na mũthenya akĩĩhingaga kũrĩa irio, na akĩmũthaithaga.  Nake agĩkinya  oro hindĩ ĩo,</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384> akĩgatha Ngai, akĩheana ũhoro wa kaana kau kũrĩ arĩa othe maatũire matanyaga hindĩ ĩrĩa Jerusalem gũgakũũrũo. </s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384> Nao maahingia maũndũ marĩa mothe maathanĩtwo irĩra-inĩ cia Mwathani, magĩcoka Galilea, makĩinũka itũũra rĩao rĩa Nazareth. </s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384> Nako kaana kau gagĩkũra, gakĩgĩa na hinya , gakĩiyũrũo nĩ ũũgĩ; naguo Wega wa Ngai watũire nako.
  
Injiri theru ya Mwathani</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"},Transition:0}},
Text:"GŨTHOMA INJIRI"},{Guid:"OO3+bfWy+0qU3uI+7sWhQQ",Verses:[],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"GŨTHOMA INJIRI "},{Guid:"Vpk508IyZkOFvKvDw8XwVQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>GŨTHOMA KUUMA IBUKU RĨA THIMO:</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>Mũtumia mũkinyanĩru angĩoneka nũ? Nĩ amu goro wake nĩ ũkĩrĩte mũno wa ruru ĩrĩa ndune.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>  Ngoro ya mũthuriwe nĩwe ĩĩhokete, na mũthuri ũcio ndarĩkĩagaga kuona thũgũri.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  Mũtumia ũyũ matukũ mothe ma muoyo wake no wega amwĩkaga, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>ndangĩmwĩka ũũru.  Eyethagĩra guoya wa ng’ondu o na ndigi cia ũguta, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>agagĩcirutithagia wĩra na moko make arĩ o na  mwĩendero.  Agwatagĩrĩra mũtĩ ũrĩa wa kuogothithia uuthi,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> nakĩo gĩcũni agakĩnyita na hĩ.  Akumbatũragĩria andũ arĩa athĩni rũhĩ, ĩĩ-ni,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> arĩa aagi agakĩmatambũrũkagĩria moko.  Ngoga nĩ cia kũhenania, naguo ũthaka nĩ wa tũhũ, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>ĩndĩ mũtumia ũrĩa mwĩtigĩri Mwathani-rĩ, nĩwe wa gũkumagio.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>  Mũhei ũrĩmi wa moko make, namo mawĩra make marotũma akumagĩrio thome-inĩ.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Ciugo cia Mwathani</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"GŨTHOMA kia mbere"},{Guid:"dVZcbk8A002sI7Ag+evgKg",Verses:[{
