Text:"Pokea zawadi "},{Guid:"2BETmNdqlEOHpAYcynvqAw",Verses:[{Style:{Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000099"}}},
Text:"<s1384>We stand before You, Holy Spirit, as we gather together in Your name.
With You alone to guide us,</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384> make Yourself at home in our hearts; Teach us the way we must go and how we are to pursue it.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>We are weak and sinful; do not let us promote disorder.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> Do not let ignorance lead us down the wrong path nor partiality influence our actions.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Let us find in You our unity so that we may journey together to eternal life and not stray from the way of truth and what is right.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>All this we ask of You, who are at work in every place and time, in the communion of the Father and the Son, forever and ever. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Amen.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000099"}}},
Text:"prayer for synod"},{Guid:"wpahh1JSkEG4NvwsMbt1Yg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>PRAYER TO ST. JOSEPH</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>Hail, Guardian of the Redeemer, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>To you God entrusted his only Son; in you Mary placed her trust; with you Christ became man.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed Joseph, to us too, show yourself a father and guide us in the path of life.
  
Obtain for us grace, mercy and courage, and defend us from every evil.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Amen.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"PRAYER TO ST. JOSEPH
"},{Guid:"yCxZZxocUE6WThKQe2bnYg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>PRAYER TO ST. JOSEPH</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>Hail, Guardian of the Redeemer, Spouse of the Blessed Virgin Mary.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>To you God entrusted his only Son; in you Mary placed her trust; with you  Christ  became man.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed Joseph, to us too, show yourself a father and guide us in the path of life. 
Obtain for us grace, mercy and courage, and defend us from every evil.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Amen.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"PRAYER TO ST. JOSEPH
"},{Guid:"FmsJq+FBy0atf0A+msQaHQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>   R/ These are the people who seek your face, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord's is the earth and its fullness,
the world, and all who dwell in it.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>It is he who set it on the seas;
on the rivers he made it firm.R/</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>   R/ These are the people who seek your face, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Who shall climb the mountain of the Lord?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>who shall stand in his holy place?</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The clean of hands and pure of heart,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>whose soul is not set on vain things.R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>   R/ These are the people who seek your face, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Blessings from the Lord shall he receive,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and right reward from the God who saves him.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Such are the people who seek him,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>who seek the face of the God of Jacob.R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>   R/ These are the people who seek your face, O Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"psalm"},{Guid:"2e2ItMMNA0GKzUBztzF1pQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>Dear Brethren, through the Paschal Mystery we have been buried with Christ 
in baptism </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>that we may walk with him in newness of life.  
And so let us renew the promises of Holy Baptism, </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>which we once renounced Satan and his works and 
promised to serve God in the Holy Catholic Church.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Do you reject sin, so as to live in the freedom of the children of God?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Do you reject all the lure of evil, that is, theft, corruption, fraud, bribery,
 </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and all the evils that dehumanize and degrade the children of God, 
so that sin may have no mastery over you?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Do you reject Satan the author and prince of sin, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>so that you may obey the commandments of God without fail?</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Do you believe in God the Father Almighty and commit yourself 
to live by His commandments which you took in the new life of baptism?</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Are you ready to choose God and live, rather than choose the evil actions of corruption and loose the blessings and friendship with God?</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I am</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Christ is our light, are you ready to give witness as light and salt of the world, 
and to suffer by refusing to bribe or accept any sort of bribes?</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I am</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Inspired by the Holy Spirit do you commit yourself to follow the law of God and all licit laws for love of God and neighbor?</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Guided by the Church are  you ready to be a disciple sent to change
 our society that is rotten</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384> because of corruption 
and clean it through our sacrifices of totally refusing any invitation to corruption?</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I am</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Do you believe in God the Father, Creator of heaven and earth, the Lord of all creation?</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Do you believe in Jesus Christ his son and was born of the Virgin Mary, 
suffered and crucified,</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384> through the corrupt acts of Judas and the leaders, </s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384>died  to redeem us from the corruption of sin and rose on the third day from the dead to conquer sin, and overcome evil?</s>"},{ID:27,
Text:"<s1384>All: I do</s>"},{ID:28,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant:  Do you believe in
the Holyspirit ,paraclete and the giver
of life,</s>"},{ID:29,
Text:"<s1384>with whose power we are sent to renew the face of the world
uproot evil and make it holy?</s>"},{ID:30,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:31,
Text:"<s1384>Celebrant: 	Do you believe in the Holy Catholic Church,</s>"},{ID:32,
Text:"<s1384> the communion of saints, the forgiveness of sins including those of corruption,
 the resurrection of the body and life everlasting?</s>"},{ID:33,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		I do</s>"},{ID:34,
Text:"<s1384>The celebrant concludes:</s>"},{ID:35,
Text:"<s1384>And may Almighty God, the Father, 
our Lord Jesus Christ who has given us new birth by water and Holy Spirit</s>"},{ID:36,
Text:"<s1384> and bestowed on us forgiveness of our sins,
 keep us by his grace, in Christ Jesus our Lord , for eternal life.</s>"},{ID:37,
Text:"<s1384>All: 		Amen.</s>"},{ID:38,
Text:"<s1384>I stand Against Corruption</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RENEWAL OF BAPTISMAL PROMISES"},{Guid:"pTzZslg5zESa3hBH7Q60Ew",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM          Psalm 104:1ab and 24ac. 29bc-30, 31 and 34 (R. 30)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Lord, send forth your Spirit, and renew the face of the earth.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Bless the Lord, O my soul!
O Lord my God, how great you are.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>How many are your works, O Lord!
The earth is full of your creatures. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Lord, send forth your Spirit, and renew the face of the earth.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>You take away their breath, they die,
returning to the dust from which they came.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>You send forth your spirit, and they are created,
and you renew the face of the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Lord, send forth your Spirit, and renew the face of the earth.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>May the glory of the Lord last for ever!
May the Lord rejoice in his works!</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>May my thoughts be pleasing to him.
I will rejoice in the Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Lord, send forth your Spirit, and renew the face of the earth.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSAL"},{Guid:"v17cYFTWDEydvrlNmUTIQQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                   Psalm 23:1-2a,2b-3,5,6(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is my shepherd;
there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Fresh and green are the pastures
where he gives me repose. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Near restful waters he leads me; 
he revives my soul.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He guides me along the right path, 
for the sake of his name. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>You have prepared a table before me  
in the sight of my foes.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>My head you have anointed with oil; 
my cup is overflowing  R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me 
all the day of my life.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>In the Lord’s own house shall I dwell 
for length of days unending.R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"ONThwNBl9Uu8KjBUMBLSTw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                    Psalm 71:1-2,3-4a,5-6ab,15ab and 17(R.15ab)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My mouth will tell of your salvation, Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>In you, O Lord, I take refuge; 
let me never be put to shame.
In your justice, rescue me, free me; 
incline your ear to me and save me. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My mouth will tell of your salvation, Lord</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Be my rock, my constant refuge, 
a mighty stronghold to save me,
for you are my rock, my stronghold.
My God, free me from the hand of the wicked. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My mouth will tell of your salvation, Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>It is you, O Lord, who are my hope, 
my trust, O Lord, from my youth.
On you I have leaned from my birth; 
from my mother’s womb, you have been my help. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My mouth will tell of your salvation, Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>My mouth will tell of your justice, 
and all the day long of your salvation.
O God, you have taught me from my youth, 
and I proclaim your wonders still.  R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My mouth will tell of your salvation, Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"uRksem7VC0in7Mlp6fw8Zg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                Psalm 90:2,3-4,12-13,14 and 16 (R 17c)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Give success to the work of our hands, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Before the mountains were born, 
or the earth or the world were brought forth, 
you are God, from age to age. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Give success to the work of our hands, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>You turn man back to dust, 
and say, “Return, O children of men.”
To your eyes a thousand years 
are like yesterday, come and gone, 
or like a watch in the night. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Then teach us to number our days, 
that we may gain wisdom of heart.  
Turn back, O Lord! How long? 
Show pity to your servants. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>At dawn, fill us with your merciful love; 
we shall exult and rejoice all our days. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Let our deed be seen by your servants,  
and your glorious power by their children. R/</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"ss5imCnKKEOZnk5DeY7k6w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                          Psalm 118:1 and 8-9:21- 23,26,28-29 (R22)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; 
his mercy endures for ever.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>It is better to take refuge in the Lord 
than to trust in man; </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>it is better to take refuge in the Lord 
than to trust in princes. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>I will thank you, for you have answered, 
and you are my savior.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The stone that the builders rejected 
has become the cornerstone.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>By the Lord has this been done,
a marvel in our eyes.  R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Blest is he who comes 
in the name of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>We bless you from the house of the Lord.
You are my God, I praise you.
My God, I exalt you.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; 
his mercy endures for ever. R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"y8RgngdHC0ujRFZDeTxPwA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                     Psalm 146:6c-7,8-9a,9bc-10(R.35:4)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Lord who preserves fidelity for ever, who does justice to those  who are oppressed.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>It is he who gives bread to the hungry, 
the Lord who sets prisoners free. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Lord who opens the eyes of the blind, the Lord who raises up those who are bowed down.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Lord who loves the just, 
the Lord who protects the stranger. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord upholds the orphan and the widow, but thwarts the path of the wicked.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord will reign for ever, 
the God of Sion from age to age. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"kdsatiBm802ZLZh50qiHaA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                              Psalm 27:1,7-8b,8c-9abc,13-14(R. 1a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The Lord is my light and my salvation</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is my light and my salvation;
whom shall I fear?
The Lord is the stronghold of my life; 
whom should I dread R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The Lord is my light and my salvation</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, hear my voice when I call; 
have mercy and answer me. 
Of you my heart has spoken, “Seek his face.” R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The Lord is my light and my salvation</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>It is your face, O Lord, that I seek; 
hide not your face from me.  
Dismiss not your servant in anger; 
you have been my help.
Do not abandon or forsake me. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The Lord is my light and my salvation</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>I believe I shall see the Lord’s goodness
in the land of the living.
Wait for the Lord; be strong; 
be stouthearted, and wait for the Lord! R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The Lord is my light and my salvation</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"n6RnM1bKykKYlfNUYAgDbg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 67:2-3,5,6 and 8(R.2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, be gracious and bless us.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O God, be gracious and bless us 
and let your face shed its light upon us.
So will your ways be known upon earth 
and all nations learn your salvation. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, be gracious and bless us.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Let the nations be glad and shout for joy, 
with uprightness you rule the peoples; 
you guide the nations on earth. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, be gracious and bless us.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Let the peoples praise you, O God; 
let all the peoples praise you.
May God still give us his blessing 
that all the ends of the earth may revere him. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, be gracious and bless us.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"ycxhwbyWlEWNs1NXMhvCOQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 84:2-3,5-6,9-10,11 (R.5a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed  are they who dwell in your house, O Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>How lovely is your dwelling place, 
O Lord of hosts.
My soul is longing and yearning 
for the courts of the Lord.
My heart and my flesh cry out
to the living God. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed  are they who dwell in your house, O Lord</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are they who dwell in your house, 
for ever singing your praise.
Blessed is the man whose strength  is in you, 
whose heart is set on pilgrim ways. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed  are they who dwell in your house, O Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord God of hosts, hear my prayer; 
give ear, O God of Jacob.
Turn your eyes, O God, our shield; 
look on the face of your anointed. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed  are they who dwell in your house, O Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>One day within your courts
is better than a thousand elsewhere.
The threshold of the house of God
I prefer to the dwellings of the wicked.R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed  are they who dwell in your house, O Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"5spiOWAqYkSzzUV2uIVezA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                   Psalm 54:3-4,5,6 and 8(R. See 6b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Behold, the Lord is the upholder of my life</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O God, save me by your name;
by your power, defend my cause.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>O God, hear my prayer; 
give ear to the words of my mouth. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Behold, the Lord is the upholder of my life</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For the proud have risen against me, 
and the ruthless seek my life.
They have no regard for God. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Behold, the Lord is the upholder of my life</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>See, I have God for my help.
The Lord sustains my soul.
I will sacrifice to you with willing heart,
and praise your name, for it is good. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Behold, the Lord is the upholder of my life</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"wFG8AaAP2kmcOiBfV/XjNw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 80:2ac and 3b,15-16a,18-19 (R.4)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O shepherd of Israel, hear us, 
enthroned on the cherubim, shine forth.
Rouse up your might and come to save us. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>God of hosts, turn again, we implore; 
look down from heaven and see.
Visit this vine and protect it, 
the vine your right hand has planted. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>May your hand be on the man at your right hand, 
the son of man you have confirmed as your own.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And we shall never forsake you again; 
give us life that we may call upon your name. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"ivOhf8g4HUqgxjAh1MFQkQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                     Psalm 128:1-2,3,4-5(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are all who fear the Lord, 
and walk in his ways!</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>By the labour of your hands you shall eat.
You will be blessed and prosper. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Your wife like a fruitful vine
 in the heart of your house; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>your children like shoots of the olive 
around your table. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Indeed thus shall be blessed 
the man who fears the Lord.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>May the Lord bless you from Sion.
May you see Jerusalem prosper 
all the days of your life! R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"0LcvIflUrE6Z6pkgLRCjpA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                              Psalm 34:2-3, 4-5,6-7(R. 9a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will bless the Lord at all times, 
praise of him is always in my mouth.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>In the Lord my soul shall make its boast; 
the humble shall hear and be glad. R/</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Glorify the Lord with me; 
together let us praise his name.
I sought the Lord, and he answered me; 
from all my terrors he set me free. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Look towards him and be radiant; 
let your faces not be abashed.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>This lowly one called; the Lord heard, 
and rescued him from all his distress R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"YW0dfFX/UE2+LDrTUex/Cw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                    Psalm 100:1-2, 3,5 (R.3c)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
We are his people, the sheep of his flock.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Cry out with joy to the Lord, all the earth. 
Serve the Lord with gladness.
Come before him, singing for joy. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	We are his people, the sheep of his flock.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Know that he, the Lord, is God.
He made us; we belong to him.
We are his people, the sheep of his flock.  R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	We are his people, the sheep of his flock.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Indeed, how good is the Lord, 
eternal his merciful love.  
He is faithful from age to age. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	We are his people, the sheep of his flock.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"WNHq0OqE0kaSYUs49CA9XA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 85:9ab and 10, 11-12, 13-14 (R.8)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will hear what the Lord God speaks; 
he speaks of peace for his people and his faithful.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>His salvation is near for those who fear him, 
and his glory will dwell in our land. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Merciful love and faithfulness have met; 
justice and peace have kissed.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Faithfulness shall spring from the earth, 
and justice look down from heaven. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Also the Lord will bestow his bounty, 
and our earth shall yield its increase.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Justice will march before him, 
and guide his steps on the way. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"InL62gjl00+phMW1GVQ+DA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                       Psalm 4:2,4,7,9 (R.7b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lift up the light of your face on us, O Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I called, the God of justice gave me answer; 
from anguish you released me, have mercy and hear me! R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lift up the light of your face on us, O Lord</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Know that the Lord works wonders for his faithful one; 
the Lord will hear me whenever I call him.  R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lift up the light of your face on us, O Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“What can bring us happiness?” many say.
Lift up the light of your face on us, O Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lift up the light of your face on us, O Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>In peace I will lie down and fall asleep, 
for you alone, O Lord, make me dwell in safety. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lift up the light of your face on us, O Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"dFOP9uVwnkWsn4KapJw0Og",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM 		         Ps. 116:12-13,15 and 16bc, 17-18 (R13)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/
The cup of salvation I will raise; I will call on the name of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>How can I repay the Lord 
for all his goodness to me?
The cup of salvation I will raise;
I will call on the name of the Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R
The cup of salvation I will raise;I will call on the name of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>How precious in the eyes of the Lord 
is the death of his faithful.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Your servant am I, the son of your handmaid; 
you have loosened my bonds. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
The cup of salvation I will raise; I will call on the name of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>A thanksgiving sacrifice I make;
I will call on the name of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>My vows to the Lord I will fulfill 
before all his people. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
The cup of salvation I will raise; I will call on the name of the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"sUGE5BNu4k6Wf5SuNbtsog",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                Psalm 138:1-2a, 2bcd-3, 4-5,7c-8(R.1c)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/In the presence of the angels I praise you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I thank you, Lord, with all my heart; 
you have heard the words of my mouth.
In the presence of the angels I praise you.
I bow down toward your holy temple. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/In the presence of the angels I praise you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>I give thanks to your name 
for your merciful love and your faithfulness.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>You have exalted your name and your promise over all.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>On the day I called, you answered me; 
you increased the strength of my soul. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/In the presence of the angels I praise you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>All earth’s kings shall thank you, O Lord, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>when they hear the words of your month.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>They shall sing of the ways of the Lord, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“How great is the glory of the Lord!” R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/In the presence of the angels I praise you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>With your right hand you save me; 
the Lord will accomplish this for me.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, your merciful love is eternal; 
discard not the work of your hands.  R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/In the presence of the angels I praise you, O Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"E+eMNbWNmEqYpZrpICKUkA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                         Psalm 118:2-4,22-24,25-27a(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Let the house of Israel say,
“His mercy endures for ever.”
Let the house of Aaron say,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“His mercy endures for ever.”
Let those who fear the Lord say,
“His mercy endures for ever.”R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The stone that the builders rejected 
has become the cornerstone.
By the Lord has this been done, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>a marvel in our eyes.
This is the day the Lord has made; 
let us rejoice in it and be glad.  R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, grant salvation;
O Lord, grant success.
Blest is he who comes 
in the name of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>We bless you from the house of the Lord; 
the Lord is God, and has given us light. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"6GBGjvGwH0q0v1u3BZ5ZVg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                         Psalm 118:1-2,15c-17,22-23(R.24)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; 
his mercy endures for ever.
Let the house of Israel say, 
“His mercy endures for ever.”R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>“The Lord’s right hand has done mighty deeds; 
his right hand is exalted.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord’s right hand has done mighty deeds.”
I shall not die, I shall live 
and recount the deeds of the Lord.  R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The stone that the builders rejected 
has become the cornerstone.
By the Lord has this been done, 
a marvel in our eyes. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"1MWYj0GvPUm4WX1XYSdx5g",Verses:[{
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM                         Psalm 96:1and 3, 4-5,7-8,9-10a and c(R.7b)"},{ID:2,
Text:"R/ 	Give the Lord glory and power."},{ID:3,
Text:"O sing a new song to the LORD; 
sing to the LORD, all the earth.
Tell among the nations his glory, 
and his wonders among all the peoples. R/"},{ID:4,
Text:"R/ 	Give the Lord glory and power."},{ID:5,
Text:"For the LORD is great and highly to be praised, 
to be feared above all gods.
For the gods of the nations are naught. 
It was the LORD who made the heavens. R/"},{ID:6,
Text:"R/ 	Give the Lord glory and power."},{ID:7,
Text:"Give the LORD, you families of peoples, 
give the LORD glory and power;
give the LORD the glory of his name.
Bring an offering and enter his courts.R/"},{ID:8,
Text:"R/ 	Give the Lord glory and power."},{ID:9,
Text:"Worship the LORD in holy splendor. 
O tremble before him, all the earth.
Say to the nations, “The LORD is king.”
He will judge the peoples in faireness. R/"},{ID:10,
Text:"R/ 	Give the Lord glory and power."}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"s1slwRBayUasA4FTBQpcvg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                         Psalm 90:12-13,14-15,16-17(R.14)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Fill us with your merciful love, O Lord, and we shall exult.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Teach us to number our days, 
that we may gain wisdom of heart.
Turn back, O Lord! How long?
Show pity to your servants. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Fill us with your merciful love, O Lord, and we shall exult.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>At dawn, fill us with your merciful love; we shall exult and rejoice all our days.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Give us joy for the days of our affliction, for the years when we looked upon evil. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Fill us with your merciful love, O Lord, and we shall exult.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Let your deed be seen by your servants, and your glorious power by their children.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Let the favour of the Lord our God be upon us; give success to the work of our hands. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>O give success to the work of our hands. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R  Fill us with your merciful love, O Lord, and we shall exult.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"NyD7gYoygE2PtQMZPneDcw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                Psalm 1:1-2,3,4 and 6(R.Ps. 40:5ab)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed indeed is the man 
who follows not the counsel of the wicked, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>nor stands in the path with sinners, 
nor abides in the company of scorners, 
but whose delight is the law of the Lord, 
and who ponders his law day and night. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He is like a tree that is planted 
beside the flowing waters, 
that yields its fruit in due season, 
and whose leaves shall never fade; 
and all that he does shall prosper. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Not so are the wicked, not so!
For they, like winnowed chaff, 
shall be driven away by the wind.
For the Lord knows the way of the just, 
but the way of the wicked will perish. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"ouc/PR4+7kuk0awwm9yyCQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                           Psalm 19:8,9,10,15 (R. John 6:63c)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Your words, O Lord, are Spirit and life</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The law of the Lord is perfect;
it revives the soul.
The decrees of the Lord are steadfast; 
they give wisdom to the simple. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Your words, O Lord, are Spirit and life</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>The precepts of the Lord are right; 
they gladden the heart.
The command of the Lord is clear; 
it gives light to the eyes. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Your words, O Lord, are Spirit and life</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The fear of the Lord is pure, 
abiding for ever.
The judgments of the Lord are true;
they are, all of them, just. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Your words, O Lord, are Spirit and life</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>May the spoken words of my mouth, 
the thoughts of my heart, 
win favour in your sight, O Lord, 
my rock and my redeemer! R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Your words, O Lord, are Spirit and life</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"QpeJViiyt0C8xv4VjiKL7w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                 Psalm 98:1,2-3ab,3cd-4(R2)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord has shown his deliverance to the nations</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O sing a new song to the Lord, 
for he has worked wonders.  
His right hand and his holy arm 
have brought salvation. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord has shown his deliverance to the nations</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord has made known his salvation, 
has shown his deliverance to the nations. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> 
He has remembered his merciful love 
and his truth for the house of  Israel. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord has shown his deliverance to the nations</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>All the ends of the earth have seen
the salvation of our God.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Shout to the Lord, all the earth;
break forth into joyous song, 
and sing out your praise. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord has shown his deliverance to the nations</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"sk87MC8FGEC9sFr2pOvurg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                         Psalm 18:2-3a,3bc-4,47,and 51ab(R.2)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R   /I love you, Lord, my strength.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I love you, Lord, my strength; 
O LORD, my rock, my fortress, my savior. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I love you, Lord, my strength.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>My God, my rock where I take refuge; </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>my shield, my saving strength, my stronghold.
I cry out, “Praised be the LORD!”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and see, I am saved from my foes. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I love you, Lord, my strength.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The LORD lives, and blest be my Rock!</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>May the God of my salvation be exalted.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The LORD gives great victories to his king,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>and shows merciful love for his anointed. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I love you, Lord, my strength.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"A9mfp1ZIIUqc247e8CUNmQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                     Psalm 16:5 and 8, 9-10,11(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Preserve me, O God, for in you I take refuge</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, it is you who are my portion and cup; you yourself who secure my lot.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>I keep the Lord before me always; 
with him at my right hand, I shall not be moved. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Preserve me, O God, for in you I take refuge</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And so, my heart rejoices, my soul is glad; even my flesh shall rest in hope.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For you will not abandon my soul to hell, 
nor let your holy one see corruption. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Preserve me, O God, for in you I take refuge</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>You will show me the path of life, 
the fullness of joy in your presence,
at your right hand, bliss for ever. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ Preserve me, O God, for in you I take refuge</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM"},{Guid:"AwIB2RhX9EKIE0bUzeWNxg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                       </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>chorus :In the Lord’s own house shall I dwell for length of days unending.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is my shepherd; 
there is nothing I shall want.
Fresh and green are the pastures 
where he gives me repose.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Near restful waters he leads me; 
he revives my soul. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>chorus :	In the Lord’s own house shall I dwell for length of days unending.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He guides me along the right path, 
for the sake of his name.
Though I should walk in the valley of the shadow of death, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>no evil would I fear, for you are with me.
Your crook and your staff will give me comfort. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>chorus :	In the Lord’s own house shall I dwell for length of days unending.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>You have prepared a table before me
 in the sight of my foes.
My head you have anointed with oil; 
my cup is overflowing. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>chorus :	In the Lord’s own house shall I dwell for length of days unending.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me 
all the days of my life.
In the LORD’s own house shall I dwell
for length of days unending. R/</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>chorus :	In the Lord’s own house shall I dwell for length of days unending.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>	</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"pHJJezyDbUCr2vuTY7uc4w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                        Psalm 72:1-2,7-8,10-11,12-13 and 29 (R 11)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O God, give your judgment to the king, 
to a king’s son your justice, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>that he may judge your people in justice, 
and your poor in right judgment. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>In his days shall justice flourish, 
and great peace till the moon is no more.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>He shall rule from sea to sea, 
from the River to the bounds of the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Kings of Tarshish and the islands 
shall pay him tribute.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The kings of Sheba and Seba 
shall bring him gifts.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Before him all kings shall fall prostrate, 
all nations shall serve him.   R/</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>For he shall save the needy when they cry, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>the poor, and those who are helpless.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>  
He will have pity on the weak and the needy,
and save the lives of the needy.   R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"vbEwR9xuVE6XIAhiWR2R7A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 107:23-24,25-26,28-29,30-31(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
O give thanks to the Lord for he is good; for his mercy endures for ever!</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Some went down to the sea in ships, 
to trade on the mighty waters.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>These have seen the deeds of the Lord, 
the wonders he does in the deep. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
O give thanks to the Lord for he is good; for his mercy endures for ever!</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For he spoke and raised up the storm-wind, 
tossing high the waves of the sea </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>that surged to heaven and dropped to the depths.
Their souls melted away in their distress. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
O give thanks to the Lord for he is good; for his mercy endures for ever!</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Then they cried to the Lord in their need, 
and he rescued them from their distress.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He stilled the storm to a whisper, 
and the waves of the sea were hushed. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
O give thanks to the Lord for he is good; for his mercy endures for ever!</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>They rejoiced because of the calm, 
and he led them to the haven they desired.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Let them thank the Lord for his mercy, 
his wonders for the children of men. R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
O give thanks to the Lord for he is good; for his mercy endures for ever!</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"CoQ3ACmP4keq8h72LYm5Qw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                Psalm 1:1-2,3,4 and 6(R.Ps. 40:5ab)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed indeed is the man 
who follows not the counsel of the wicked, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>nor stands in the path with sinners, 
nor abides in the company of scorners, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>but whose delight is the law of the Lord, 
and who ponders his law day and night. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He is like a tree that is planted beside the flowing waters, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>that yields its fruit in due season, and whose leaves shall never fade; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>and all that he does shall prosper. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Not so are the wicked, not so!For they, like winnowed chaff, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>shall be driven away by the wind.For the Lord knows the way of the just, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>but the way of the wicked will perish. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the man who has placed his trust in the Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"WJG6xpzBSEqSmDD7xe1kEg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 22:8-9,17-18a,19-20,23-24(R.2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>All who see me deride me; 
they curl their lips, they toss their heads:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“He trusted in the Lord, let him save him;  
let him release him, for in him he delights. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For dogs have surrounded me; 
a band of the wicked besets me.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>They tear holes in my hands and my feet;
 I can count every one of my bones. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>They divide my clothing among them, 
they cast lots for my robe.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>But you, O Lord, do not stay afar off; 
my strength, make haste to help me! R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>I will tell of your name to my kin, 
and praise you in the midst of the assembly;</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>“You who fear the Lord, give him praise; 
all descendants of Jacob, give him glory; 
revere him, all you descendants of Israel.” R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"bkOOLeCw4UitP0smJVvZeg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 51:3-4,12-13,14-15(R.12a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Create a pure heart for me, O God</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Have mercy on me, O God, 
according to your merciful love; 
according to your great compassion,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>blot out my transgressions.
Wash me completely from my iniquity, 
and cleanse me from my sin. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Create a pure heart for me, O God</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Create a pure heart for me, O God; 
renew a steadfast spirit within me.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>  
Do not cast me away from your presence; 
take not your holy spirit from me. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Create a pure heart for me, O God</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Restore in me the joy of your salvation;
sustain in me a willing spirit.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>I will teach transgressors your ways,
that sinners may return to you. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Create a pure heart for me, O God</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"JBRgRcyvQEKBeY//mdRFKQ",Verses:[{
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                Psalm 90:2,3-4,12-13,14 and 16 (R 17c)"},{ID:2,
Text:"R/ 	Give success to the work of our hands, O Lord."},{ID:3,
Text:"Before the mountains were born, 
or the earth or the world were brought forth, 
you are God, from age to age. R/"},{ID:4,
Text:"R/ 	Give success to the work of our hands, O Lord."},{ID:5,
Text:"You turn man back to dust, 
and say, “Return, O children of men.”
To your eyes a thousand years 
are like yesterday, come and gone, 
or like a watch in the night. R/"},{ID:6,
Text:"Then teach us to number our days, 
that we may gain wisdom of heart.  
Turn back, O Lord! How long? 
Show pity to your servants. R/"},{ID:7,
Text:"At dawn, fill us with your merciful love; 
we shall exult and rejoice all our days. 
Let our deed be seen by your servants,  
and your glorious power by their children. R/"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"3LilXdK1W0C2Tb4P9saQdw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                         Psalm 118:1-2,15c-17,22-23(R.24)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; 
his mercy endures for ever.
Let the house of Israel say, 
“His mercy endures for ever.”R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>“The Lord’s right hand has done mighty deeds; 
his right hand is exalted.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord’s right hand has done mighty deeds.”
I shall not die, I shall live 
and recount the deeds of the Lord.  R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The stone that the builders rejected 
has become the cornerstone.
By the Lord has this been done, 
a marvel in our eyes. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	This is the day the Lord has made; let us rejoice in it and be glad</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"fEbalc8GfU+K6XffmVaKCQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 147:1-2,3-4,5-6(R.3a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Praise the Lord who heals the brokenhearted</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>How good to sing psalms to our God; 
how pleasant to chant fitting praise! </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord builds up Jerusalem 
and brings back Israel’s exiles. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Praise the Lord who heals the brokenhearted</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He heals the broken-hearted; 
he binds up all their wounds.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>He counts out the number of the stars;
he calls each one by its name. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Praise the Lord who heals the brokenhearted</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Our Lord is great and almighty; 
his wisdom can never be measured.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord lifts up the lowly; 
he casts down the wicked to the ground. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Praise the Lord who heals the brokenhearted</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"yyLySB5XikiGpb1xrvbkkw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                    Psalm 63:2,3-4,5-6,7-8(R)2</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	For you my soul is thirsting, O Lord, my God</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O God, you are my God; at down I seek you;</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>for you my soul is thirsting.
For you my flesh is pining,
 
like a dry, weary land without water. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	For you my soul is thirsting, O Lord, my God</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>I have come before you in the sanctuary, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>to behold your strength and your glory.
Your loving mercy is better than life;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> my lips will speak your praise. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	For you my soul is thirsting, O Lord, my God</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>I will bless you all my life; 
in your name I will lift up my hands. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>My soul shall be filled as with a banquet; </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>with joyful lips, my mouth shall praise you.  R/</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	For you my soul is thirsting, O Lord, my God</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>When I remember you upon my bed, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>I muse on you through the watches of the night.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>For you have been my strength; </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>in the shadow of your wings I rejoice.</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>R/ For you my soul is thirsting, O Lord, my God</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"24CEhNy2mky8y/wO+9GE5g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 23:1-3a, 3bc-4, 5, 6 (R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is my shepherd; 
there is nothing I shall want.
Fresh and green are the</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> pastures where he gives me repose.
Near restful waters he leads me; 
he revives my soul. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>He guides me along the right path, 
for the sake of his name.  
Though I should walk in the valley of the shadow of death, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>no evil would I fear, for you are with me.
your crook and your staff will give me comfort R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>You have prepared a table before me 
in the sight of my foes.
My head you have anointed with oil; 
my cup is overflowing. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me 
all the days of my life.
In the Lord’s own house shall I dwell for length of days unending. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is my shepherd; there is nothing I shall want.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"WxAj6U3vH0il1Gs/Vs+oPg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 22:8-9,17-18a,19-20,23-24(R.2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>All who see me deride me; 
they curl their lips, they toss their heads:
“He trusted in the Lord,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> let him save him;  
let him release him, for in him he delights. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For dogs have surrounded me; 
a band of the wicked besets me.
They tear holes in my hands and my feet;
 I can count every one of my bones. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>They divide my clothing among them, 
they cast lots for my robe.
But you, O Lord, do not stay afar off; 
my strength, make haste to help me! R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>I will tell of your name to my kin, 
and praise you in the midst of the assembly;
“You who fear the Lord, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>give him praise; 
all descendants of Jacob, give him glory; 
revere him, all you descendants of Israel.” R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF990000"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"o71yZnwXW0mP+TxLWnLJSQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 123:1-2ab,2cdef, 3-4(R.2ef)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Our eyes are on the Lord our God, till he show us his mercy.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>To you have I lifted up my eyes, 
you who dwell in the heavens.
Behold, like the eyes of the slaves 
on the hand of their lords. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Our eyes are on the Lord our God, till he show us his mercy.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Like the eyes of a servant 
on the hand of her mistress, 
so our eyes are on the Lord our God,
till he show us his mercy. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Our eyes are on the Lord our God, till he show us his mercy.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Have mercy on us, Lord, have mercy.
We are filled with contempt.
Indeed, all too full is our soul 
with the scorn of the arrogant, 
the disdain of the proud. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Our eyes are on the Lord our God, till he show us his mercy.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"gT61A40gJk2/ruMT3fvqbg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                              Psalm 126:1-ab, 2cd-3, 4-5,6 (R.3)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>When the Lord brought back the exiles of Sion,we thought we were dreaming.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Then was our mouth filled with laughter; 
on our tongues, songs of joy. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Then the nations themselves said, “What great deedsthe Lord worked for them!”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>What great deeds the Lord worked for us! 
Indeed, we were glad. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Bring back our exiles, O Lord, 
as streams in the south.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Those who are sowing in tears 
will sing when they reap. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>They go out, they go out, full of tears, 
bearing seed for the sowing;</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>they come back, they come back with a song, bearing their sheaves. R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
