Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"plzRXLFPy0a/VlonpNwL1w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                      Psalm 92:2-13-14,15-16(R.2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is a good to give thanks to you, o Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>It is good to give thanks to the Lord, 
to make music to your name, O Most High, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>to proclaim your loving mercy in the morning,  
and your truth in the watches of the night. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is a good to give thanks to you, o Lord.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The just will flourish like the palm tree, 
and grow like a Lebanon cedar.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Planted in the house of the Lord, 
they will flourish in the courts of our God. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is a good to give thanks to you, o Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>They will still bear fruit when they are old, 
still full of sap, still green, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>to proclaim that the Lord is upright.
In him, my rock, there is no wrong. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is a good to give thanks to you, oLord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"7fUqSXrhmUOXKQrQuNWxfg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 116:10 and15;16-17,18-19(R.9)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I trusted, even when I said,
 “I am sorely afflicted.”</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>How precious in the eyes of the Lord 
is the death of his faithful. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Your servant, Lord, your servant am I,
the son of your handmaid;
you have loosened my bonds.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>A thanksgiving sacrifice I make;
I will call on the name of the Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>My vows to the Lord I will fulfil 
before all his people, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>in the courts of the house of the Lord, 
in your midst, O Jerusalem. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"+3IAfHkbgUKPHjnMAOunEQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 25:4-5ab, 6 and 7bc, 8-9(R.4a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, make me know your ways</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, make me know your ways.
Teach me your paths.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Guide me in your truth, and teach me; 
for you are the God of my salvation. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, make me know your ways</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Remember your compassion, O Lord, 
and your merciful love, 
for they are from of old.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>In your merciful love remember me, 
because of your goodness, O Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, make me know your ways</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Good and upright is the Lord; 
he shows the way to sinners.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He guides the humble in right judgment;
to the humble he teaches his way. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, make me know your ways</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"A0fXJlZLk0OOeHmq4KzJ+A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                     Psalm 25:4-5ab, 8-9,10 and 14(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	To you, O Lord, I lift up my soul</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, make me know your ways.Teach me your paths.
Guide me in your truth,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and teach me; for you are the God of my salvation. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	To you, O Lord, I lift up my soul</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Good and upright is the Lord; 
he shows the way to sinners.
He guides the humble in right judgment; 
to the humble he teaches his way. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	To you, O Lord, I lift up my soul</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>All the Lord’s paths are mercy and faithfulness, for those who keep his covenant and commands.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord’s secret is for those who fear him; to them he reveals his covenant. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	To you, O Lord, I lift up my soul</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"X1lxQSLsyUeX8PF5yULFkQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                              Psalm 45:10, 11,12,16(R.10b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
On your right stands the queen in gold of Ophir.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The daughters of Kings are those whom you favour. On your right stands the queen in gold of Ophir. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
On your right stands the queen in gold of Ophir.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Listen, O daughter; pay heed and give ear: 
forget your own people and your father’s house R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
On your right stands the queen in gold of Ophir.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>So will the king desire your beauty.
He is your lord, pay homage to him. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
On your right stands the queen in gold of Ophir.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>They are escorted amid gladness and joy; 
They pass within the palace of the king. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
On your right stands the queen in gold of Ophir.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"QPwsaOSfeESFeygaFMdEvA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                            Isaiah 12:2-3, 4bcd,5-6(R 3)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	With joy you will draw water from the wells of salvation.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>“Behold, God is my salvation;
I will trust, and will not be afraid; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>for the Lord God is my strength and my song, 
and he has become my salvation.”</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>With joy you will draw water from the wells of salvation. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	With joy you will draw water from the wells of salvation.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“Give thanks to the Lord  
call upon his name; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>make known his deeds among the nations, 
proclaim that his name is exalted” R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	With joy you will draw water from the wells of salvation.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>“Sing praises to the Lord, for he has done gloriously; </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>let this be known in all the earth.
Shout, and sing for joy, O inhabitant of Zion, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>for great in your midst is the Holy one of Israel.” R/</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	With joy you will draw water from the wells of salvation.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"VybffmZV0U+CUidBNBkfKw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                        Psalm 30:2 and 4, 5-6,11-12a and 13b(R.2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up, 
and have not let my enemies rejoice over me.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, you have lifted up my soul from the grave, 
restored me to life from those who sink into the pit. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Sing psalms to the Lord, you faithful ones; give thanks to his holy name.
His anger lasts a moment;</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> his favour all through life. At night there are tears, but at dawn comes joy.  R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Hear, O Lord, and have mercy on me; 
be my helper, O Lord.You have changed my mourning into dancing.  O Lord my God, I will thank you for ever. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"2+o2afxIkEKS/D1k3UFLXg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                      Psalm 145:10-11,15-16,17-18(R.16)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ You open your hand, Lord, and you satisfy us.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>All your works shall thank you, O Lord, and all your faithful ones bless you.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>They shall speak of the glory of your reign, and declare your mighty deeds. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ You open your hand, Lord, and you satisfy us.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>The eyes of all look to you, 
and you give them their food in due season.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>You open your hand and satisfy the desire of every living thing. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ You open your hand, Lord, and you satisfy us.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is just in all his ways, and holy in all his deeds.
  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is close to all who call him,who call on him in truth. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ You open your hand, Lord, and you satisfy us.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"iii4A2pu0kSsRe4wV8PRFQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                     Psalm 93:1abc,1d-2,5(R.1a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
The Lord is king, with majesty enrobed.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is king, with majesty enrobed.
The Lord has robed himself with might; 
he has girded himself with power.R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
The Lord is king, with majesty enrobed.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>The world you made firm, not to be moved; your throne has stood firm from of old.From all eternity, o Lord, you are. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
The Lord is king, with majesty enrobed.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Truly your decrees are to be trusted.
Holiness is fitting to your house, 
O Lord, until the end of time. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
The Lord is king, with majesty enrobed.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"WRWF11B09UeLNGh9J0NHxQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                     Psalm 126:1-2ab,2cd-3,4-5,6(R.3)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>When the Lord brought back the exiles of Sion, we thought we were dreaming.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Then was our mouth filled with laughter;
on our tongues, songs of joy. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Then the nations themselves said, “What great deeds the Lord worked for them!</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>What great deeds the Lord worked for us! 
Indeed, we were glad. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Bring back our exiles, O Lord, 
as streams in the south.
Those who are sowing in tears 
will sing when they reap. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>They go out, they go out, full of tears, 
bearing seed for the sowing;</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>they come back, they come back with a song, bearing their sheaves. /R</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>R/ What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"FRSlkDM1mEmd8KdruhPFGw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM 		 Ps. 33:4-5,6 and 9, 18-19,20 and 22 (R12b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the people the Lord has chosen as his heritage</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The word of the Lord is faithful, 
and all his works to be trusted.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord loves justice and right, 
and his merciful love fills the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the people the Lord has chosen as his heritage</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>By the word of the Lord the heavens were made, 
by the breath of his mouth all their host.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He spoke, and it came to be.
He commanded; it stood in place. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the people the Lord has chosen as his heritage</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Yes, Lord’s eyes are on those who fear him, 
who hope in his merciful love, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>to rescue their souls from death, 
to keep them alive in famine. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the people the Lord has chosen as his heritage</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Our soul is waiting for the Lord.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He is our help and our shield.
May your merciful love be upon us, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>as we hope in you, O Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed the people the Lord has chosen as his heritage</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"JG+mRDV06UK2bxEhSer90Q",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                         Ps. 40:2 and 4ab,7-8a,8b-9,10(R.8a and 9a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	See, I have come Lord, to do your will</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I waited, I waited for the Lord, 
and he stooped down to me;
he heard my cry. 
He put a new song into my mouth, 
praise of our God R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	See, I have come Lord, to do your will</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>You delight not in sacrifice and offerings,
but in an open ear.
You do not ask for holocaust and victim.
Then I said, “See, I have come.” R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	See, I have come Lord, to do your will</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>In the scroll of the book it stands written of me:
“I delight to do your will, O my God; 
your instruction lies deeps within me.” R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	See, I have come Lord, to do your will</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Your justice I have proclaimed 
in the great assembly.
My lips I have not sealed;
you know it, O Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	See, I have come Lord, to do your will</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"egh6j4xvCEyuKC0gvDTcdA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                         Psalm 145:8-9, 10-11,12-13b(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will bless your name for ever, my king and my God.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is kind and full of compassion, 
slow to anger, abounding in mercy.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>How good is the Lord to all,
compassionate to all his creatures. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will bless your name for ever, my king and my God.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>All your works shall thank you, o Lord, 
and all your faithful ones bless you.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>They shall speak of the glory of your reign, 
and declare your mighty deeds.  R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will bless your name for ever, my king and my God.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>They shall make known your might to the children of men,and the glorious splendor of your reign.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom; 
your rule endures for all generations. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will bless your name for ever, my king and my God.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM "},{Guid:"07g6YLkeB0SPeC2oll4sew",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 34:2-3,4-5,6-7,8-9(R.9a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/
Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will bless the Lord at all times, praise of him is always in my mouth.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>In the Lord my soul shall make its boast;the humble shall hear and be glad. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Glorify the Lord with me;
together let us praise his name.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>I sought the Lord, and he answered me; from all my terrors he set me free. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Look towards him and be radiant;let your faces not be abashed.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>This lowly one called; the Lord heard, and rescued him from all his distress. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The angel of the Lord is encamped around those who fear him, to rescue them.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Taste and see that the Lord is good.Blessed the man who seeks refuge in him. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"Y71FQ7c2Y064lR25KneCgA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                        Psalm 1:46-48,49-50,53-54(R.Isaiah 61:10b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My soul shall exult in my God</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>My soul magnifies the Lord, 
and my spirit rejoices in God my Saviour, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>for he has regarded the low estate of his handmaiden.
For behold, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>henceforth all generations will call me blessed. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My soul shall exult in my God</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For he who is mighty has done great things for me, 
and holy is his name. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>And his mercy is on those who fear him from generation to generation. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My soul shall exult in my God</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He has filled the hungry with good things,And the rich he has sent empty away.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>He has helped his servant Israel, in remembrance of his mercy. R/</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	My soul shall exult in my God</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"VSdyVf+mK02g3poz2LEw7A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                     Psalm 33:4-5,18-19,20 and 22(R.22)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ May your merciful love be upon us, as we hope in you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The word of the Lord is faithful, 
and all his works to be trusted. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord loves justice and right, 
and his merciful love fills the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ May your merciful love be upon us, as we hope in you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Yes, the Lord’s eyes are on those who fear him, who hope in his merciful love, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>to rescue their souls from death, 
to keep them alive in famine. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ May your merciful love be upon us, as we hope in you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Our soul is waiting for the Lord.  
He is our help and our shield.
  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>May your merciful love be upon us, as we hope in you, O Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ May your merciful love be upon us, as we hope in you, O Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"Fd3RUAbbskq0Nk/D4TItcg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                          Psalm 85:9ab and 10,11-12,13-14(R.8)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will hear what the Lord God speaks; 
he speaks of peace for his people and his faithful.
His salvation is near for those who fear him, 
and his glory will dwell in our land. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Merciful love and faithfulness have met; 
justice and peace have kissed.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Faithfulness shall spring from the earth, 
and justice look down from heaven. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Also the Lord will bestow his bounty, 
and our earth shall yield its increase.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Justice will march before him, 
and guide his steps on the way. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"EMDRlIP+10WJPjpI390lpg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                     Psalm 128:1-2,3,4-5(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are all who fear the Lord, 
and walk in his ways!</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>By the labour of your hands you shall eat.
You will be blessed and prosper. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Your wife like a fruitful vine
 in the heart of your house; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>your children like shoots of the olive 
around your table. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Indeed thus shall be blessed 
the man who fears the Lord.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>May the Lord bless you from Sion.
May you see Jerusalem prosper 
all the days of your life! R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"e5BQhX2zDEy52BDIMQ6VCw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                             Psalm 18:2-3a,3bc-4,47 and 5 51ab(R.2)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I love you, Lord, my strength</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I love you, Lord, my strength;
O Lord, my rock, my fortress, my saviour R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I love you, Lord, my strength</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>My God, my rock where I take refuge;
my shield, my saving strength, my stronghold.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>I cry out, “Praised be the Lord!” 
and see, I am saved from my foes. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I love you, Lord, my strength</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord lives, and blest be my Rock!May the God of my salvation be exalted.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord gives great victories to his king, 
and shows merciful love for his anointed. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I love you, Lord, my strength</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"/xyb68JTiEuIuZ2WUiTjrA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                             Psalm 131:1,2,3</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Keep my soul in peace at your side, O Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, my heart is not proud, 
nor haughty my eyes.
I have not gone after things too great, 
nor marvels beyond me.R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Keep my soul in peace at your side, O Lord</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Truly, I have set my soul 
in tranquility and silence.
As a weaned child on its mother, 
as a weaned child is my soul within me.R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Keep my soul in peace at your side, O Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>O Israel, wait for the LORD, 
both now and for ever. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Keep my soul in peace at your side, O Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"TRT0B3jo80aS/ATYafTskw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                        Psalm 126:1-2ab,2cd-3, 4-5,6(R.3)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>When the Lord brought back the exiles of Sion, 
we thought we were dreaming.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Then was our mouth filled with laughter; 
on our tongues, songs of joy. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Then the nations themselves said, “What great deeds 
the Lord worked for them!”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>What great deeds the Lord worked for us!
Indeed, we were glad. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Bring  back our exiles, O Lord, 
as streams in the south.
Those who were sowing in tears 
will sing when they reap. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>They go out, they go out, full of tears, 
bearing seed for the sowing;</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>they come back, they come back with a song, 
bearing their sheaves. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	What great deeds the Lord worked for us! Indeed, we were glad</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"efYb1e3FYky0vIuxX0hrqA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                    Psalm 104:1b-2, 3-4,24-25,27-28,29-30(R1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Bless the Lord, O my soul! O Lord my God, how great you are!</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord my God, how great you are, 
clothed in majesty and honour, 
wrapped in light as with a robe! 
You stretch out the heavens like a tent. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Bless the Lord, O my soul! O Lord my God, how great you are!</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>On the waters you establish your dwelling.
You make the clouds your chariot; 
you ride on the wings of the wind, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>You make the winds your messengers,
 flame and fire your servants. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Bless the Lord, O my soul! O Lord my God, how great you are!</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>How many are your works, O Lord!
In wisdom you have made them all.
The earth is full of your creatures.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Vast and wide is the span of the sea, 
with its creeping things past counting,
living things great and small. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Bless the Lord, O my soul! O Lord my God, how great you are!</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>All of these look to you 
to give them their food in due season.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>You give it, they gather it up; 
you open wide your hand, they are well filled. R/</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Bless the Lord, O my soul! O Lord my God, how great you are!</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>You hide your face, they are dismayed;
you take away their breath, they die, </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>returning to the dust from which they came.
You send forth your spirit, and they are created,
and you renew the face of the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Bless the Lord, O my soul! O Lord my God, how great you are!</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"pHTEETeCzk2CQM480vJsWw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                        Psalm 34: 2-3,16-17,18-19,20-21,22-23(R.9a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will bless the Lord at all times, 
praise of him is always in my mouth.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>In the Lord my soul shall make its boast;
the humble shall hear and be glad. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord turns his eyes to the just,
and his ears are open to their cry.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord turns his face against the wicked to destroy their remembrance from the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>When the just cry out, the Lord hears, 
and rescues them in all their distress.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is close to the broken-hearted; 
those whose spirit is crushed he will save. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Many are the trials of the just man, 
but from them all the Lord will rescue him.  </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He will keep guard over all his bones; 
not one of his bones shall be broken. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Evil brings death to the wicked; 
those who hate the just man are doomed</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord ransoms the souls of his servants.All who trust in him shall not be condemned. R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Taste and see that the Lord is good</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"TOzrjwajrEuqVaiDJNwS9Q",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 78:3,4bc,23-24,25 and 54(R.24b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord gave them bread from heaven</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The things we have heard and understood, the things our fathers have told us,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>we will tell them to the next generation: the glories of the Lord and his might. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord gave them bread from heaven</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Yet he commanded the clouds above, and opened the gates of heaven.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He rained down manna to eat, and gave them bread from heaven. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord gave them bread from heaven</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Man ate the bread of angels.
He sent them abundance of food. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>So he brought them to his holy land,to the mountain his right hand had won. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord gave them bread from heaven</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"So4IU7eb2ECGcVprnLehbw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                    Psalm 128:1-2,3,4-5(R.1a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are all who fear the Lord, 
and walk in his ways!</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>By the labour of your hands you shall eat.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>You will be blessed and prosper R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Your wife like a fruitful vine in
the heart of your house:</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Your children like shoots of the olive 
around your table. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Indeed thus shall be blessed 
the man who fears the Lord.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>May the Lord bless you from Sion.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>May you see Jerusalem prosper 
all the days of your life!  R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"8cWnau95V0SLf/NgIiEqEw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                   Psalm 19:8,10,12-13,14(R. See 9ab)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The precepts of the Lord are right; they gladden the heart.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The law of the Lord is perfect;
it revives the soul.
The decrees of the Lord are steadfast; 
they give wisdom to the simple. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The precepts of the Lord are right; they gladden the heart.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>The fear of the Lord is pure, 
abiding for ever.
The judgements of the Lord are true;
they are, all of them, just. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The precepts of the Lord are right; they gladden the heart.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>So in them your servant finds instruction; 
great reward is in their keeping.
But who can detect their own errors?
From hidden faults acquit me. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The precepts of the Lord are right; they gladden the heart.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>From presumption restrain your servant; 
may it not rule me.
Then shall I be blameless, 
clean from grave sin.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ The precepts of the Lord are right; they gladden the heart.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"ppGGKQHKikmnouBofF+y8g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 19:8,9,10,11 (R. see John 6:68c)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lord, you have the words of eternal life.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The law of the Lord is perfect;
it revives the soul </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>The decrees of the Lord are steadfast; 
they give wisdom to the simple. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lord, you have the words of eternal life.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The precepts of the Lord are right; 
they gladden the heart.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The command of the Lord is clear; 
it gives light to the eyes. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lord, you have the words of eternal life.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The fear of the Lord is pure, 
abiding for ever.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The judgements of the Lord are true; 
they are, all of them, just, R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lord, you have the words of eternal life.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>They are more to be desired than gold, 
than quantities of gold.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>And sweeter are they than honey, 
than honey flowing from the comb. R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Lord, you have the words of eternal life.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"dKwMV3lIu0yHc4+VJsz37A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                  Isaiah 12:2-3,4bcde,5-6(R.6)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Shout, and sing for joy, for great in your midst is the Holy One of Israel.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>“Behold, God is my salvation; 
I will trust, and will not be afraid; 
for the Lord god is my strength and my song, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and he has become my salvation.”
With joy you will draw water from the wells of salvation. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Shout, and sing for joy, for great in your midst is the Holy One of Israel.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>“Give thanks to the Lord, 
call upon his name; make known his deeds among the nations, proclaim that his name is exalted.” R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Shout, and sing for joy, for great in your midst is the Holy One of Israel.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>“Sing praises to the Lord, for he has done gloriously; let this be known in all the earth.Shout, and sing for joy,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> O inhabitant of Zion, for great in your midst is the holy One of Israel.” R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Shout, and sing for joy, for great in your midst is the Holy One of Israel.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"MQXLN9rWCU22YkeFcgfsMA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                              Psalm 91:1-2,10-11,12-13,14-15(R. 15b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Be with me, oh Lord, when I am in distress</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>He  who  dwells in the shelter of the Most High, 
and abides in the shade of the Almighty, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>says to the Lord, “My refuge, 
my stronghold, my God in whom I trust!” R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Be with me, oh Lord, when I am in distress</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Upon you no evil shall fall, 
no plague approach your tent.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For you has he commanded his angels 
to keep you in all your ways. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Be with me, oh Lord, when I am in distress</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>They shall bear you upon their hands, 
lest you strike your foot against a stone.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>On the lion and the viper you will tread,
and trample the young lion and the serpent. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Be with me, oh Lord, when I am in distress</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Since he clings to me in love, I will free him, 
protect him, for he knows my name. </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>When he calls on me, I will answer him; 
I will be with him in distress; 
I will deliver him, and give him glory. R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Be with me, oh Lord, when I am in distress</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"v2sqjLerFkWk8WZhAb+GUw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                              Psalm 15:2-3a,3bc-4ab,5(R.1a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, who may abide in your tent?</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Whoever walks without fault; 
what does what is just, 
and speaks the truth from his heart.
Who does not slander with his tongue. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, who may abide in your tent?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Who does no wrong  to a neighbor, 
who casts no slur on a friend, 
who looks with scorn on the wicked, 
but honours those who fear the Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, who may abide in your tent?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Who lends no money at interest, 
and accepts no bribes against the innocent.
Such a one shall never be shaken. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O Lord, who may abide in your tent?</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"VHMX71CuQUSTelSFO7aLig",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                       Psalm 30:2 and 4, 5-6,11-12a and 13b(R.2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up, 
and have not let my enemies rejoice over me.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, you have lifted up my soul from the grave, 
restored me to life from those who sink into the pit. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Sing psalms to the Lord, you faithful ones; 
give thanks to his holy name.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>His anger lasts a moment; his favour all through life.
At night there are tears, but at dawn comes joy. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Hear, O Lord, and have mercy on me; 
be my helper, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>You have changed my mourning into dancing.
O Lord my God, I will thank you for ever. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will extol you, Lord, for you have raised me up.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"VjIH1kMlk0aOeoP6zejiyw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                   Psalm 1466c-7,8-9a, 9bc-10(R.see Isaiah 35:4)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Lord who preserves fidelity for ever, 
who does justice to those who are oppressed.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>It is he who gives bread to the hungry, 
the Lord who sets prisoners free. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Lord who opens the eyes of the blind, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>the Lord who raises up those who are bowed down.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Lord who loves the just, 
the Lord who protects the stranger. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord upholds the orphan and the widow,
but thwarts the path of the wicked.
The Lord will reign for ever,
the God of Sion from age to age. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Come, Lord, and save us</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"vIWyDqoMbU6X+vGcAD1JjA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                   Psalm 116:1-2,3-4,5-6,8-9(R.9)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I love the Lord, for he has heard 
my voice, my appeal;
for he has turned his ear to me 
whenever I call. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>They surrounded me, the snares of the death;
the anguish of the grave has found me;
anguish and sorrow I found.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>I called on the name of the Lord: 
“Deliver my soul, O Lord!” R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>How gracious is the Lord, and just; 
our God has compassion.
The Lord protects the simple; 
I was brought low, and he saved me. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He has kept my soul from death, 
my eyes from tears, 
and my feet from stumbling.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>I will walk in the presence of the Lord
in the land of the living. R/</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will walk in the presence of the Lord in the land of the living</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
