Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                        Psalm 72:1-2,7-8,10-11,12-13 and 29 (R 11)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O God, give your judgment to the king, 
to a king’s son your justice,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> 
that he may judge your people in justice, 
and your poor in right judgment. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>In his days shall justice flourish, 
and great peace till the moon is no more.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>He shall rule from sea to sea, 
from the River to the bounds of the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The Kings of Tarshish and the islands 
shall pay him tribute.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The kings of Sheba and Seba 
shall bring him gifts.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Before him all kings shall fall prostrate, 
all nations shall serve him.   R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>For he shall save the needy when they cry, 
the poor, and those who are helpless.  </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>He will have pity on the weak and the needy,and save the lives of the needy.   R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	All nations on earth shall fall prostrate before you, O Lord.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
