Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                       Psalm 118:2-4,15c-16b and 17-18,22-24(R.1)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Let the house of Israel say, 
“His mercy endures for ever.”
Let the house of Aaron say,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“His mercy endures for ever.”
Let those who fear the Lord say, 
“His mercy endures forever R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>“The Lord’s right hand has done mighty deeds; 
his right hand is exalted.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord’s right hand has done mighty deeds.”
I shall not die, I shall live 
and recount the deeds of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord punished me, punished me severely, 
but did not hand me over to death.  R/</s>"},{ID:9},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The stone that the builders rejected 
has become the cornerstone.
By the Lord has this been done, </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>a marvel in our eyes.
This is the day the Lord has made; 
let us rejoice in it and be glad. R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
Give praise to the Lord, for he is good; his mercy endures for ever.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
