Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 95:1-2,6-7abc,7d-9(R.7d,8a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O that today you would listen to his voice! Harden not your hearts</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Come, let us ring out our joy to the Lord; 
hail the rock who saves us.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Let us come into his presence, 
giving thanks; let us hail him with a song of praise. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O that today you would listen to his voice! Harden not your hearts</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>O come let usbow and bendlow
let us kneel before the God who made us,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>for he is our God and we the people who belong to his pasture the flock that is led by his hand. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O that today you would listen to his voice! Harden not your hearts</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>O that today you would listen to his voice! Harden not your hearts asat meribah as on that day </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>at massah inthe desert when your forebears put me to the test;when they tried me,though they saw my work.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O that today you would listen to his voice! Harden not your hearts</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"Sj87nQ7x00WyJgA38CmcPA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                              Psalm 103:1-2,3-4,6-7, 8 and 11(R. 8a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
The Lord is compassionate and gracious.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Bless the Lord, O my soul, 
and all within me, his holy name.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Bless the Lord, O my soul, 
and never forget all his benefits. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	
The Lord is compassionate and gracious.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>It is the Lord who forgives all your sins, 
who heals every one of your ills, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>who redeems your life from the grave, 
who crowns  you with mercy and compassion. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is compassionate and gracious.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord does just deeds, 
gives full justice to all who are oppressed.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>He made known his ways to Moses, 
and his deeds to the children of Israel. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is compassionate and gracious.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord is compassionate and gracious, slow to anger and rich in mercy.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>For as the heavens are high above the earth, so strong his mercy for those who fear him. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	The Lord is compassionate and gracious.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM  "},{Guid:"l8swsDLsxEWkmmCUJ8OgHw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                              Psalm 92:2-3, 13-14, 15-16(R. 2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is good to give thanks to you, O Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>It is good to give thanks to the Lord, 
to make music to your name, O Most High, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>to proclaim your loving mercy in the morning, 
and your truth in the watches of the night. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is good to give thanks to you, O Lord</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>The just will flourish like the palm tree, 
and grow like a Lebanon cedar.
Planted in the house of the Lord, 
they will flourish in the courts of our God. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is good to give thanks to you, O Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>They will still bear fruit when they are old, still full of sap,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> still green,to proclaim that the lord is upright.  In him, my rock, there is no wrong. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	It is good to give thanks to you, O Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
