Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                         Psalm 96:1and 3, 4-5,7-8,9-10a and c(R.7b)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/Give the Lord glory and power.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O sing a new song to the LORD; 
sing to the LORD, all the earth.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Tell among the nations his glory, 
and his wonders among all the peoples. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 
Give the Lord glory and power.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For the LORD is great and highly to be praised, 
to be feared above all gods.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For the gods of the nations are naught. 
It was the LORD who made the heavens. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/Give the Lord glory and power.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Give the LORD, you families of peoples, 
give the LORD glory and power;</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>give the LORD the glory of his name.
Bring an offering and enter his courts.R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/Give the Lord glory and power.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Worship the LORD in holy splendor. 
O tremble before him, all the earth.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Say to the nations, “The LORD is king.”
He will judge the peoples in faireness. R/</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Give the Lord glory and power.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"sEKxXKkOyEeUmARR+E1Lew",Verses:[{
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM                              Psalm 103:1-2,3-4, 8 and 10,12-13(R. 8a)"},{ID:2,
Text:"R/ 	The Lord is compassionate and gracious"},{ID:3,
Text:"Bless the Lord, O my soul, 
and all within me, his holy name.
Bless the Lord, O my soul, 
and never forget all his benefits. R/"},{ID:4,
Text:"It is the Lord who forgives all your sins, 
who heals  every one of your ills, 
who redeems your life from the grave, 
who crowns you with mercy and compassion. R/"},{ID:5,
Text:"The Lord is compassionate and gracious, 
slow to anger and rich in mercy.
He does not treat us according to our sins, 
nor repay us according to our faults. R/"},{ID:6,
Text:"As far as the east is from the west, 
so far from us does he remove our transgressions.
As a father has compassion on his children,
the Lord’s compassion is on those who fear him. R/"}],
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"oBuxmuR740GmGUy4rGf3TA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 25:4-5ab, 6 and 7bc, 8-9(R.10)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ All your paths, O Lord, are mercy and faithfulness, for those who keep your covenant</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O Lord, make me know your ways.  
Teach me your paths.
Guide me in your truth, and teach me; 
for you are the God of my salvation. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ All your paths, O Lord, are mercy and faithfulness, for those who keep your covenant</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Remember your compassion, O Lord, 
and your merciful love, 
for they are from of old.
In your merciful love remember me, 
because of your goodness, O Lord. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ All your paths, O Lord, are mercy and faithfulness, for those who keep your covenant</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Good and upright is the Lord; 
he shows the way to sinners.
He guides the humble in right judgment; 
to the humble he teaches his way. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ All your paths, O Lord, are mercy and faithfulness, for those who keep your covenant</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"VTwhXP+baEW/ReuLs+sSVw",Verses:[{
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                                     Psalm 128:1-2,3,4-5(R.1)"},{ID:2,
Text:"R/ 	Blessed are all who fear the Lord, and walk in his ways"},{ID:3,
Text:"Blessed are all who fear the Lord, 
and walk in his ways!"},{ID:4,
Text:"By the labour of your hands you shall eat.
You will be blessed and prosper. R/"},{ID:5,
Text:"Your wife like a fruitful vine
 in the heart of your house; "},{ID:6,
Text:"your children like shoots of the olive 
around your table. R/"},{ID:7,
Text:"Indeed thus shall be blessed 
the man who fears the Lord."},{ID:8,
Text:"May the Lord bless you from Sion.
May you see Jerusalem prosper 
all the days of your life! R/"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"8AZkxj1+/EGmBT9vj2sb+Q",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 32:1-2,5,11(R.7)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	You are a hiding place for me; you surround me with cries of deliverance</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed is he whose transgression is forgiven, 
whose sin is remitted.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed the man to whom the Lord imputes no guilt, 
in whose spirit is no guile. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	You are a hiding place for me; you surround me with cries of deliverance</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>To you I have acknowledged my sin; 
my guilt I did not hide. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>I said, “I will confess my transgression to the Lord.”
And you have forgiven the guilt of my sin. R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ You are a hiding place for me; you surround me with cries of deliverance</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Rejoice in the Lord, exult you just!
Ring out your joy, all you upright of heart! R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ You are a hiding place for me; you surround me with cries of deliverance</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"MmMggv6B+E6ro5LEo+gh9g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                          Psalm 80:2ac and 3b,15-16a,18-19(R.4)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O shepherd of Israel, hear us, 
enthroned on the cherubim, shine forth. 
Rouse up your might and come to save us. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>God of hosts, turn again, we implore; 
look down from heaven and see.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Visit this vine and protect it, 
the vine your right hand has planted. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>May your hand be on the man at your right hand, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>the son of man you have confirmed as your own.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>And we shall never forsake you again;  
give us life that we may call upon your </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O God, bring us back; let your face shine on us, and we shall be saved</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"GzJyROVnw0OhIdVnhT0g4w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                           Psalm 96:1-2a,2b-3,7-8a,9-10a and c (R.3)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Tell among all the peoples the wonders of the Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>O sing a new song to the Lord; 
song to the Lord, all the earth.
O sing to the Lord; bless his name. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Tell among all the peoples the wonders of the Lord</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Proclaim his salvation day by day.
Tell among the nations his glory,
and his wonders among all the peoples. R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Tell among all the peoples the wonders of the Lord</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Give the Lord, you families of peoples,
give the Lord glory and power; 
give the Lord the glory of his name. R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Tell among all the peoples the wonders of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Worship the Lord in holy splendor.
O tremble before him, all the earth.
Say to the nations, “The Lord is king.”
He will judge the peoples in fairness. R/</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	Tell among all the peoples the wonders of the Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"keJbD7ummk2U1jlqUEXgzA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                        Psalm 89:2-3,4-5,27 and 29 (R 2a)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will sing for ever of your mercies, O Lord</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I will sing for ever of your mercies, O Lord; 
through all ages my mouth will proclaim your fidelity.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>I have declared your mercy is established for ever; 
your fidelity stands firm as the heavens. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will sing for ever of your mercies, O Lord</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>“With my chosen one I have made a covenant; 
I have sworn to David my servant:</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>I will establish your descendants for ever, 
and set up your throne through all ages.”  R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will sing for ever of your mercies, O Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>“He will call out to me, ‘You are my father, 
my God, the rock of my salvation.’</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>I will keep my faithful love for him always; 
with him my covenant shall last.” R/</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	I will sing for ever of your mercies, O Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM   "},{Guid:"Yb2nItJu3kGRxhIiHBtrfg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM                               Psalm 137:1-2,3,4-5,6(R.6ab)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O let my tongue cleave to my palate if I remember you not.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>By the rivers of Babylon  
there we sat and wept, 
remembering Sion; 
on the poplars that grew there 
we hung up our harps. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O let my tongue cleave to my palate if I remember you not.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For it was there that they asked us, 
our captors, for songs, 
our oppressors, for joy.  
“Sing to us,” they said, 
“One of Sion’s songs.” R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O let my tongue cleave to my palate if I remember you not.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>O how could we sing
 the song of the Lord on foreign soil? 
If I forget you, Jerusalem, 
let my right hand wither! R/</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O let my tongue cleave to my palate if I remember you not.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>O let my tongue  
cleave to my palate 
if I remember you not, 
if I prize not Jerusalem 
as the first of my joys!  R/</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	O let my tongue cleave to my palate if I remember you not.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM    "},{Guid:"McY0CilD1kuUybOKy+qIwg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	May the Lord bless us all the days of our lives</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are all who fear the Lord, 
and walk in his ways!</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>By the labour of your hands you shall eat.
You will be blessed and prosper. R/</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	May the Lord bless us all the days of our lives</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Your wife like a fruitful vine 
in the heart of your house;
your children like shoots of the olive
around your table. R/</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	May the Lord bless us all the days of our lives</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Indeed thus shall be blessed 
the man who fears the Lord.
May the Lord bless you from Sion.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> 
May you see Jerusalem prosper 
all the days of your life! R/</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	May the Lord bless us all the days of our lives</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>May you see your children’s children.
On Israel, Peace!</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	May the Lord bless us all the days of our lives</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"RESPONSORIAL PSALM                                         "},{Guid:"tD97SbXAtEqOuKDpfCNbJg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>RESPONSORIAL PSALM 		Psalm 47: 2-3,6-7,8-9 (R) 6</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>R/ 	God goes up with shouts of joy.The Lord goes up with trumpet blast.	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>All peoples, clap your hands.
Cry to God with shouts of joy!</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For the Lord, the Most High, is awesome,
the great king over all the earth. R/</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>R/ God goes up with shouts of joy.The Lord goes up with trumpet blast.	</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>God goes up with shouts of joy.
The Lord goes up with trumpet blast.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Sing praise for God; sing praise!
Sing praise to our king; sing praise! R/</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>R/ God goes up with shouts of joy.The Lord goes up with trumpet blast.	</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>God is king of all the earth.
Sing praise with all your skill.</s>"},{ID:8,
