Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						 1 Corinthians 7:32-35</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I want you to be free from anxieties.  The unmarried man is anxious about the affairs of the Lord, how to please the Lord; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>but the married man is anxious about worldly affairs, how to please his wife, and his interests are divided. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> And the unmarried woman or virgin is anxious about the affairs of the Lord, how to be holy in body and spirit; </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>but the married woman is anxious about worldly affairs, how to please her husband.  I say this for your own benefit, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>not to lay any restraint upon you, but to promote good order and to secure your undivided devotion to the Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Matthew 4:16</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>The people who sat in darkness have seen a great light, and for those who sat in the region and shadow of death light has dawned.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"imtkbMJwGUGOvgKt6G00+A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             Colossians 3:1-4</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Colossians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
If you have been raised with Christ, seek the things that are above, where Christ is, seated at the right hand of God. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Set your minds on things that are above, not on things that are on earth.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For you have died, and your life is hidden with Christ in God. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>When Christ who is our life appears, then you also will appear with him in glory.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>SEQUENCE (Prose text)
To the Paschal Victim let Christians offer a sacrifice of praise.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>The Lamb redeemed the sheep.
Christ, sinless, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>reconciled sinners to the Father.
Death and life were locked together in a unique struggle.
Life’s captain died;</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> now he reigns, never more to die.
Tell us, Mary, </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>“What did you see on the way?”
“I saw angels who gave witness;
 
the cloths too which once had covered head and limbs.
“Christ my hope has arisen. </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>He will go before his own into Galilee.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>”
We know that Christ has indeed risen from the dead.
Do you, conqueror and king,
 have mercy on us.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Amen. Alleluia.</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>					
SEQUENCE (Poetic text)</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>Christians, to the Paschal Victim 
Offer your thankful praises!
A Lamb the sheep redeems:</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384> Christ, who only is sinless, 
Reconciles sinners to the Father.
Death and life have contended in that combat stupendous:The Prince of life, who died, reigns immortal.</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>Speak, Mary, declaring
What you saw, wayfaring.
“The tomb of Christ, who is living,
The glory of Jesus ‘resurrection;</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384>Bright angels attesting, 
The shroud and napkin resting.
Yes, Christ my hop is arisen:
To Galilee he goes before you.”</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>Christ indeed from death is risen, our new life obtaining.
Have mercy, Victor King, ever reigning!
Amen. </s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>1 Corinthians 5:7b,8a</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>Christ, our Paschal Lamb, has been sacrificed; let us, therefore, celebrate the festival in the Lord.</s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"Kj1vCpd/jEOoFIzaYoweWA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING					 1 Thessalonians 1:5c-10</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The beginning of the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
You know what kind of men we proved to be among you for your sake.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  And you became imitators of us and of the Lord, for you  received the word in much affliction,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> with joy inspired by the Holy Spirit; so that you became an example to all the believers in Macedonia and in Achaia.  </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For not only has the word of the Lord sounded forth from you in Macedonia and Achaia, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>but your faith in God has gone forth everywhere, so that we need not say anything.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>  For they themselves report concerning us what a welcome we had among you, and how you turned to God from Idols, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>to serve a living and true God, and to wait for his Son from heaven,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> whom he raised from the dead, Jesus who delivers us from the wrath to come.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          
Alleluia.  Alleluia.							</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>If a man loves me, he will keep my words, says the Lord; and my Father will love him, and we will come to him.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"3Sd0nf3QzEOLsMRK/rthcA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                      Rev. 1:9-11a,12-13,17-19</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Book of Revelation	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>	
I John, your brother, who share with you in Jesus the tribulation and the kingdom and the patient endurance, </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>was on the island called Patmos on account of the word of God and the testimony of Jesus.  I was in the Spirit on the Lord’s day,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and I heard behind me a loud voice like  a trumpet saying, “Write what you see in a book and send it to the seven churches.” </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Then I turned to see the voice that was speaking to me, and on turning I saw seven golden lampstands,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and in the midst of the lampstands one like a Son of man, clothed with a long robe and with a golden sash across his chest.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>When I saw him, I fell at his feet as though dead. But he laid his right hand upon me, saying, “Fear not, I am the first and last, and the living one;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>I died, and behold I am alive for evermore, and I have the keys of Death and Hades. Now write what you see, what is and  what is to take place hereafter.”  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia									John 20:29</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>You believed, Thomas, because you have seen me, says the Lord; blessed are those who have not seen and yet believe.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"fjaJhmQVi0+ix6HtinCsJQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Hebrews 9:24-28 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Christ has entered, not into a sanctuary made with hands, a copy of the true one, but into heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of God on our behalf.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Nor was it to offer himself repeatedly, as the high priests enters the Holy Place yearly with blood not his own;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> for then he would have had to suffer repeatedly since the foundation of the world.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>But as it is, he has appeared once for all at the end of the age to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself. And just as it is appointed for men to die once, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and after that comes judgment, so Christ, having been offered once to bear the sins of many, will appear a second time, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>not to deal with sin but to save those who are eagerly waiting for him.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               Mathew 5:3</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are the poor in spirit, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"Eg0M9tYRj0uCZZGB8peebg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                   1 Corinthians. 10:1-6,10-12 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I want you to know, brethren, that our fathers were all under the cloud,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and all passed through the sea, and all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and all ate the same supernatural food and all drank  the same supernatural drink.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For they drank from the supernatural Rock which followed them, and the Rock was Christ.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Nevertheless with most of them God was not pleased; for they were overthrown in the wilderness.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Now these things are warnings for us, not to desire evil as they did, nor grumble, as some of them did and were destroyed by the Destroyer.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Now these things happened to them as a warning, but they were written down for our instruction, upon whom   the end of the ages has come.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore let any one who thinks that he stands take heed lest he fall.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>VERSE BEFORE THE GOSPEL					Matthew 4:17</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Glory and praise to you, O Christ
Glory and praise to you, O Christ</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Repent, says the Lord, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Glory and praise to you, O Christ</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"0o1fwzJAAE+gH1frld/xtQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     1 Thesalonians 3:12-4:2 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
May the Lord make you increase and abound in love to one another and to all men, as we do to you,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> so that he may establish your hearts unblamable in holiness before our God and Father,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> at the coming of our Lord Jesus with all his saints.Finally, brethren, we beg and exhort you in the Lord Jesus, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>that as you learned  from us how you ought to walk and to please God, just as you are doing, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>you do so more and more.
For you know what instructions we gave you through the Lord Jesus.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						              </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"1AlSk0GAw02F4Op7KKq2mg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                         2 Corinthians 5:14 -17</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the second Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
The love of Christ urges us on, because we are convinced that one has died for all; therefore all have died.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And he died for all, that those who live might live no longer for themselves but for him who for their sake died and was raised.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>From now on, therefore, we regard no one according to the flesh;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> even though we once regarded Christ according to the flesh, we regard him thus no longer. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Therefore, if any one is in Christ, he is a new creation; the old has passed away, behold, the new has come.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>         Luke 7:16</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>A great prophet has arisen among us, and God has visited his people.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"iNVOvtnR2Uq6IKpUdzGGNQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                            Hebrews 5:7-9 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>In the days of his flesh, Jesus offered up prayers and supplications, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>with loud cries and tears, to him who was able to save him from death, and he was heard for his godly fear.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> Although he was a Son, he learned obedience through what he suffered;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and being made perfect he became the source of eternal salvation to all who obey him.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>    
Verse Before the Gospel								John 12:26</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>.
If any one serves me, he must follow me, says the Lord; and where I am, there shall my servant be also.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"qkmavNqzIE6Fl8Aymznh+Q",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						 1 Corinthians 7:29-31</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I mean, brethren, the appointed time has grown very short;</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> from now on, let those who have wives live as though they had none, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and those who mourn as though they were not mourning,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and those who rejoice as though they were not rejoicing,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> and those who buy as though they had no goods, and those who deal with the world,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> as though they had no dealing with it.  For the form of this world is passing away. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Mark 1:15</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The kingdom of God is at hand; repent, and believe in the Gospel.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"62UUkk1kakCUkAN1ddlI0g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						 Titus 2: 11-14; 3:4-7</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to Titus		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved:
For the grace of God has appeared for the salvation of all men, training us to renounce irreligion and worldly passions, and to live sober, upright</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and godly lives in this world, awaiting our blessed hope, the appearing of the glory of our great God and Saviour Jesus Christ,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> who gave himself for us to redeem us from all iniquity and to purify for himself a people of his own who are zealous for good deeds.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>But when the goodness and loving kindness of God our Saviour appeared, he saved us, not because of deeds done by us in righteousness, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>but in virtue of his own mercy, by the washing of regeneration and renewal in the Holy Spirit, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>which he poured out upon us richly through Jesus Christ our Saviour, so that we might be justified by his grace and become heirs in hope of eternal life.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								Luke 3:16</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>John said: He who is coming is mightier than I; he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"Ln01x56+WkWXJYrRBbWB2g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING Thessalonians 1:1-5b</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The beginning of the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, 
To the Church of the Thessalonnians in God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Grace to you and peace.
We give thanks to God always for you all, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>constantly mentioning you in our prayers,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> remembering before our God and Father your work of faith and labour of love and steadfastness of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For we know, brethren beloved by God, that he has chosen you; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>for our Gospel came to you not only in word, but also in power and in the Holy Spirit and with full conviction.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          
Alleluia.  Alleluia.							
</s>Verse 11"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>You will shine as lights in the world, holding fast the word of life.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"FqqXQfD58EOLa3rH8jK0nA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              1 John3:1-2,21-24 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint John</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved: 
See what love the Father has given us, that we should be called children of God; and so we are.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>The reason why the world does not know us is that it did not know him.  Beloved, we are God’s children now;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> it does not yet appear what we shall be ,but we know that when he appears we shall be like him, for we shall see him as he is.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved, if our hearts do not condemn us, we have confidence before God; and we receive from him whatever we ask,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> because we keep his commandments and do what pleases him. And this is his commandment,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> that we should believe in the name of his Son Jesus Christ and love one another, just as he has commanded us.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>  All who keep his commandments abide in him, and he in them. And by this we know that he abides in us, by the Spirit which he has given us.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               Acts  16:14b</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Open our hearts, o Lord, that we may give heed to the words of your Son.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"FAKtYbxGNkKc9dBi/a00Ig",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						Roman 8:14-17</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Romans			</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
All who are led by the Spirit of God are sons of God. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> 
For you did not receive the spirit of slavery to fall back into fear, but you have received the spirit of sonship.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>When we cry, “Abba! Father!” it is the Spirit himself bearing witness with our spirit that we are children of God,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> and if children, then heirs, heirs of God and fellow heirs with Christ, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>provided we suffer with him in order that we may also be glorified with him. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								Revelation 1:8
			
Alleluia.  Alleluia.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit: to God who is, who was, and who is to come.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"cdgpoPvCMUWdwT1FTIZIjg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                   2 Corinthians. 5:17-21 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the second Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthian</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
If any one is in Christ, he is a new creation; the old has passed away, behold, the new has come.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  All this is from God, who through Christ reconciled us to himself and gave us the ministry of reconciliation;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> that is, in Christ God was reconciling the world to himself, not counting their trespasses against them, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and entrusting to us the message of reconciliation. So we are ambassadors for Christ,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> God making his appeal through us.  We beg you on behalf of Christ, be reconciled to God. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> For our sake he made him to be sin  who knew no sin, so that in him we might become the righteousness of God.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>I will arise and go to my father and I will say to him: 
Father, I have sinned against heaven and before you.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"bmEzJgvvWkC4xzFL8Rq3rA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             1John 4:7-10</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint John		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved, let us love one another; for love is of God, and he who loves is born of God and knows God. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> He who does not love does not know God; for God is love.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>In this the love of God was made manifest among us, that God sent his only-begotten Son into the world, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>so that we might live through him. In this is love, not that we loved God but that he loved us and sent his son to be expiation for our sins.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>John 14:23
Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>If a man loves me, he will keep my word, says the Lord; and my Father will love him, and we will come to him.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"aPNcWe9j3E2XzmBPmGAljQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             Colossians 3:1-4</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Colossians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
If you have been raised with Christ, seek the things that are above, where Christ is, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>seated at the right hand of God. Set your minds on things that are above, not on things that are on earth.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For you have died, and your life is hidden with Christ in God. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>When Christ who is our life appears, then you also will appear with him in glory.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"/2qA9rOw0EK/OgNcD8Rqpg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Galatians 4:4-7</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Galatians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
When the time had fully, God sent forth his Son, born of woman, born under the law, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>to redeem those who were under the law, so that we might receive adoption as sons.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And because you are sons, God has sent the Spirit of his Son into our hearts, crying, “Abba! Father!” </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>So through God you are no longer a slave but a son, and if a son then an heir.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 							        Hebrews 1:1-2				               </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>In many and various ways God spoke of old to our fathers by the prophets; but in these last days he has spoken to us by a Son.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING"},{Guid:"kDOUnN4Ts0a3q9WGia2uYQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						 Romans 16:25-27</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Romans 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
To him who is able to strengthen you according to my Gospel and the preaching of Jesus Christ,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> according to the revelation of the mystery which was kept secret for long ages </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>but is now disclosed and through the prophetic writings is made known to all nations, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>according to the command of the eternal God, to bring about the obedience of faith</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> – to the only wise God be glory for evermore through Jesus Christ! Amen.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Luke 1:38</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Behold, I am the handmaid of the Lord; let it be to me according to your word.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"Fjx49afSvk29VC4pwRjbZA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						 Ephesians 3:2-3a,5-6</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
I assume that you have heard of the stewardship of God’s grace that was given to me for you, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>how the mystery was made known to me by revelation,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> which was not made known to the sons of men in other generations as it has now</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit; that is, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>how the Gentiles are fellow heirs, members of the same body, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>and partakers of the promise in Christ Jesus through the Gospel.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Matthew 2:2</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>We have seen his star in the east, and have come to worship the Lord</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"MbWNo6ztME6zO/3UEW2+Wg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						     1 Corinthians 1:3-9</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>I give thanks to God always for you because of the grace of God which was given you in Christ Jesus,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> that in every way you were enriched in him with all speech and all knowledge –</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> even as the testimony to Christ was confirmed among you – so that you are not lacking in any spiritual gift,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> as you wait for the revealing of our Lord Jesus Christ; who will sustain you to the end, guiltless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>God is faithful, by whom you were called into the fellowship of his Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Psalm 85:8</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Let us see, O Lord, your mercy, and grant us your salvation.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"+fORzoBm1kaUnBVo++pQWg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING		Ephesians. 1: 17-23</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians 				</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
May the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>give you a spirit of wisdom and of revelation in the knowledge of him, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>having the eyes of your hearts enlightened, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>that you may know what is the hope to which he has called you,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> what are the riches of his glorious inheritance in the saints,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> and what is the immeasurable greatness of his power in us who believe,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> according to the working of his great might which he accomplished in Christ when he raised him from the dead </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and made him sit at his right hand in the heavenly places, far above all rule and authority</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> and power and dominion and above every name that is named, not only in this age but also in that which is to come</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>and he has put all things under his feet and has made him the head over all things for the Church,</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> which is his body, the fullness of him who fills all in all.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								Matthew. 28:19a, 20b
			
Alleluia.  Alleluia.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Go and make disciples of all nations, says the Lord; I am with you always, to the close of the age.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"oEmzv17Vx0awJnNc3+4Vnw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING					 Philippians 4:12-14,19-20</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Philippians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
I know how to be abased, and I know how to abound; in any and all circumstances I have learned the secret of facing plenty and hunger, abundance and want.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>I can do all things in him who strengthens me.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Yet it was kind of you to share my trouble. And my God will supply every need of yours according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>To our God and Father be glory for ever and ever. Amen</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          
Alleluia.  Alleluia.							</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>May the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ enlighten the eyes of our hearts that we might know what is the hope to which he has called us.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"NLU0pP6WakyRITfVK7Ashw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						     2 Peter 3:8-14</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Second Letter of Saint Peter		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Do not ignore this one fact, beloved, that with the Lord one day is as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  The Lord is not slow about his promise as some count slowness, but is forbearing toward you,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> not wishing that any should perish, but that all should reach repentance.  But the day of the Lord will come like a thief, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and then the heaven will pass away with a loud noise, and the elements will be dissolved with fire, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and the earth and the works that are upon it will be burned up.
Since all these things are thus to be dissolved,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> what sort of persons ought you to be  in lives of holiness and godliness, waiting for and hastening the coming of the day of God,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> because of which the heavens will be kindled and dissolved,  and the elements will melt with fire! </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>But according to his promise we wait for new heavens and a new earth in which righteousness dwells.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore, beloved, since you wait for these, be zealous to be found by him without spot or blemish, and at peace.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Luke 3:4,6</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Prepare the way for the Lord, make his paths straight; all flesh shall see the salvation of God.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"8PJx5CZa+EyuRUvnjC3Xng",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                         1 Corinthians 15:45-49 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>“The first man Adam became a living soul”; the last Adam became a life-giving spirit. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>But it is not the spiritual which is first but the physical, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and then the spiritual.
The first man was from the earth, a man of dust; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>the second man is from heaven.
As was the man of dust, so are those who are of the dust;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and as is the man of heaven, so are those who are of heaven.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Just as we have borne the image of the man of dust, we shall also bear the image of the man of heaven.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                John 13:34</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>A new commandment I give to you, says the Lord, that you love one another, even as I have loved you.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"},Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"pDv8/mUoH02akhniD32B9w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     Ephesians 4:1-6</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethen:
I, a prisoner for the Lord, beg you to walk in a manner worthy of the calling to which you have been called, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>with all lowliness and meekness, with patience, forbearing one another in love, eager to maintain the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> 
There is one body and one Spirit, just as you were called to the one hope that belongs to your call, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>one Lord, one faith, one baptism, one God and Father of us all, who is above all and through all and in all.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                        Luke 7:16</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>A great prophet has arisen among us, and God has visited his people.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"BwtKbcdYs02LDYxiQcwsNA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                         Romans 4:13, 16-18,22</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Romans		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
The promise to Abraham and his descendants, that they should inherit the world, did not come through the law but through the righteousness of faith.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>That is why all depends on faith, in order that the promise may rest on grace  and be guaranteed to all his descendants –</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> not only to the adherents of the law but also to those who share the faith of Abraham, for he is the father of us all, as it is written, “</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>I have made you the father of many nations” – in the presence of the God in whom he believed, who gives life to the dead and calls into existence the things that do not exist.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>  In hope he believed against hope, that he should become the father of many nations; as he had been told,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> “So shall your descendants be.” That is why his faith was “reckoned to him as righteousness.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Psalm 68:20
Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Day after day, may the Lord be blest.  He bears our burdens; God is our Saviour.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"SXt3UXhB9EitGnlNl+F50g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             1John 3:1-2</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint John		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved: 
See what love the Father has given us, that we should be called children of God; and so we are.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>The reason why the world does not know us is that it did not know him.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved, we are God’s children now; it does not yet appear what we shall be,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> but we know that when he appears we shall be like him, for we shall see him as he is.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>         John 10:14</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>I am the good shepherd, says the Lord; I know my own, and my own know me.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"9ifv0RmX4ESu5Stp7fIKVw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						    1 Cor. 6:13c-15a,17-20</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
The body is not meant for immorality, but for the Lord, and the Lord for the body.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>And God raised the Lord and will also raise us up by his power.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Do you not know that your bodies are members of Christ?</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>But he who is united to the Lord becomes one spirit with him.  </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Shun immorality.
Every other sin which a man commits is outside the body; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>but the immoral man sins against his own body.
Do you not know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit within you, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>which you have from God?
You are not your own; you were bought with a price. </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>So glorify God in your body.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          John 1:41,17b</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>We have found the Messiah, who is Christ; grace and truth came through him.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"LI1/dSPBGE63l8IkRPLZOQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     James 2:1-5</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint James	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>My brethren show no partiality as you hold the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For if a man with gold rings and in fine clothing comes into your assembly, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and a poor man in shabby clothing also comes in, and you pay attention to the one who wears the fine clothing and say, “Have a seat here, please,” </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>while you say to the poor man, “Stand there, “or, “Sit at my feet,” have you not made distinctions among yourselves,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and become judges with evil thoughts?
Listen, my beloved brethren. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Has not God chosen those who are poor in the world to be rich in faith and heirs of the kingdom which he has promised to those who love him?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                        Mathew 4:23</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus was preaching the Gospel of the kingdom, healing every disease and every infirmity among the people.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"fbMVvm9sjEyfsGyJ2eWLOg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                           Revelation 1:5-8</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Book of Revelation	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Jesus Christ is the faithful witness, the first-born of the dead, and the ruler of kings on earth.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>To him who loves us and has freed us from our sings by his blood and made us a kingdom, priests to his God and Father,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> to him be glory and dominion for ever and ever. Amen. Behold, he is coming with the clouds,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and every eye will see him, every one who pierced him; and all tribes of the earth will wail on account of him. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Even so. Amen.“I am the Alpha and the Omega,” says the Lord God, who is and who was and who is to come, the Almighty.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 			</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord! Blessed is the kingdom of our father David that is coming!</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"2V4MhSOp3UmWrX4BrZutyg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     Philippians 1:4-6,8-11 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Philippians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
Always in every prayer of mine for you all I make my prayer with joy,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> thankful for your partnership in the Gospel from the first day until now.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And I am sure that he who began a good work in you will bring it to completion at the day of Jesus Christ.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For God is my witness, how I yearn for you all with the affection of Christ Jesus.  And it is my prayer that your love may abound more and more,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> with knowledge and all discernment so that you may approve what is excellent, and may be pure and blameless for the day of Christ,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> filled with the fruits of righteousness which come through Jesus Christ, to the glory and praise of God.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               Luke 3:4,6</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight: all flesh shall see the salvation of God.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"rnML4Qli9ECmLdpRhA3Gbg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Hebrews 7:23-28 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>The priest (of the former covenant) were many in number, because they were prevented by death from continuing in office; </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>but Christ holds his priesthood permanently, because he continues for ever. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Consequently he is able for all time to save those who draw near to God through him,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> since he always lives to make intercession for them.For it was fitting that we should have such a high priest, holy, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>blameless, unstained, separated from sinners, exalted above the heavens. He has no need,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> like those high priests, to offer sacrifices daily, first for his own sins and then for those of the people; </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>he did this once for all when he offered up himself. Indeed, the law appoints men in their weakness as high priests, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>but the word of the oath, which came later than the law, appoints a Son who has been made perfect for ever.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>  The Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               John 14:23</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>If a man loves me, he will keep my word, says the Lord; and my Father will love him, and we will come to him.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"2T0pR0cglEO6UntmRFLmHA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Hebrews 5:1-6 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Every high priest chosen from among men is appointed to act on behalf of men in relation to God, to offer gifts and sacrifices for sins.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>He can deal gently with the ignorant and wayward, since he himself is beset with weakness.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>  Because of this he is bound to offer sacrifice for his own sins as well as for those of the people.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And one does not take the honour upon himself, but he is called by God just as Aaron was.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>So also Christ did not exalt himself to be made a high priest, but was appointed by him who said to him, “You are my Son, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>today I have begotten you”; as he says also in another place, “You are a priest  for ever, according to the order of Melchizedek.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               See 2 Timothy 1:10</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Our Saviour Christ Jesus abolished death and brought life and immortality to light through the Gospel.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"GLdAqVUrK0m6dNEYh3zyQQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                   Philippians 3: 8-14 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Philippians </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
I count everything as loss because of the surpassing worth of knowing Christ Jesus my Lord. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For his sake I have suffered the loss of all things, and count them as refuse, in order that I may gain Christ and be found in him, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>not having a righteousness of my own, based on law, but that which is through faith in Christ, the righteousness from God that depends on faith;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> that I may know him and the power of his resurrection, and may share his sufferings, becoming like him in his death,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> that if possible I may attain the resurrection from the dead.
Not that I have already obtained this or am already perfect; </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>but I press on to make it my own, because Christ Jesus has made me his own.  Brethren, I do not consider that I have made it my own;</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> but one thing I do, forgetting what lies behind and straining forward to what lies ahead,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> I press on toward the goal for the prize of the upward call of God in Christ Jesus.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>VERSE BEFORE THE GOSPEL					                Joel 2:12-13</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Even now, say the Lord, return to me with all your heart, for I am gracious and merciful.</s>"}],Style:{Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"},Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"v2DO44gylEy+Qq6JY1jNLw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                            Romans 10:1-13 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Romans</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
What does the Scripture say?
The word is near you, on your lips and in your heart (that is, the word of faith which we preach); </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>because, if you confess with your lips that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For man believes with his heart and so is justified, and he confesses with his lips and so is saved.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> The Scripture says, “No one who believes in him will be put to shame.”  For there is no distinction between Jew and Greek; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>the same Lord is Lord of all and bestows his riches upon all who call upon him.  For, every one who calls upon the name of the Lord will be saved.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                Matthew 4:4b</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Man does not live on bread alone, but on every word that comes from the mouth of God.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"UyXJnRaoeESLVVQJEXqJ4g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				        1 Corinthians 9:16-19,22-23</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>If I preach the Gospel, that gives me no ground for boasting.  For necessity is laid upon me.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>  Woe to me if I do not preach the Gospel! For if I do this of my own will, I have a reward; but if not of my own will,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> I am entrusted with a commission.  What then is my reward? Just this: </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>that in my preaching I may make the Gospel free of charge, not making full use of my right in the Gospel. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> For though I am free from all men, I have made myself a slave to all, that I might win the more.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>To the weak I became weak, that I might win the weak.  I have become all things to all men,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> that I might by all means save some.  I do it all for the sake of the Gospel, that I may share in its blessings.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Matthew 8:17</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Christ took our infirmities and bore our diseases.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"44ZhMeJGyEqjc8r7qcvHsQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Hebrews 4:14-16 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Since we have a great high priest who has passed through the heavens, Jesus, the Son of God, let us hold fast our confession.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  For we have not a high priest who is unable to sympathize with our weaknesses, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>but one who in every respect has been tempted as we are, yet without sinning. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Let us then with confidence draw near to the throne of grace, that we may receive mercy and find grace to help in time of need.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						             </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The Son of man came not to be served but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"BmazM5+ewUGv7oMz3XMn1w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     Ephesians 5:21-32</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Be subject to one another out of reverence for Christ.  Wives, be subject to your husbands, as to the Lord.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For the husband is the head of the wife as Christ is the head of the Church, his body, and is himself its Saviour.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>As the Church is subject to Christ, so let wives also be subject in everything to their husbands. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Husbands, love your wives, as Christ loved the Church and gave himself up for her, that he might sanctify her, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>having cleansed her by the washing of water with the word, that he might present the Church to himself in splendour,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> without spot or wrinkle or any such thing, that she might be holy and without blemish.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Even so husbands should love their wives as their own bodies.  He who loves his wife loves himself. </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> For no man ever hates his own flesh, but nourishes and cherishes it, as Christ does the Church, because we are members of his body.  </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>“For this reason a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>and the two shall become one flesh.” This is a great mystery, and I mean in reference to Christ and the Church</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                        John 6:63,68c</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Your words, Lord, are Spirit and life; you have the words of eternal life.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"otIwgZMXUkOe/GFrZvOa8w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                            Ephesians 2:4-10 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
God, who is rich in mercy, out of the great love with which he loved us, even when we were dead through our trespasses, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>made us alive together with Christ (by grace you have been saved), and raised us up with him, and made us sit with him in the heavenly places in Christ Jesus, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>that in the coming ages he might show the immeasurable riches of his grace in kindness toward us in Christ Jesus. For by grace you have been saved through faith; and this is not your own doing,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> it is the gift of God – not because of works, lest any man should boast.  For we are his workmanship,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand, that we should walk in them.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>    
Verse Before the Gospel								John 3:16</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>God so loved the world that he gave his only Son,
that whoever believes in him should have eternal life.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"psDF52/o7kOoM9l8N/er1A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     Ephesians 2:13-18</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethen:
Now in Christ Jesus you who once were far off have been brought near in the blood of Christ.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  For he is our peace, who has made us both one, and has broken down the dividing wall of hostility, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>by abolishing in his flesh the law of commandments and ordinances, that he might create in himself one new man in place of the two,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> so making peace, and might reconcile us both to God in one body through the cross, thereby bringing the hostility to an end.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And he came and preached peace to you who were far off and peace to those who were near; for through him we both have access in one Spirit to the Father.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                        John 10:27</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>My sheep hear my voice, says the Lord; and I know them, and they follow me.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"rrt2r8vrok2eziKft2eRhA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     1Corinthians 15:12, 16-20</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>If Christ is preached as raised from the dead, how can some of you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For if the dead are not raised, then Christ has not been raised. If Christ has not been raised, your faith is futile and you are still in your sins. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> Then those also who have fallen asleep in Christ have perished.  If for this life only we have hoped in Christ,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> we are of all men most to be pitied.
But in fact Christ has been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who have fallen asleep.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 									Luke 6:23ab					               </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Rejoice and leap for joy, says the Lord, for behold, your reward is great in heaven.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"gX8zDt4OAUaOcYitKusy8w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1846>SECOND READING					 1 Thessalonians 4:13-18</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1846>The beginning of the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1846>We would not have you ignorant, brethren, concerning those who are asleep, that you may not grieve as others do who have no hope.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1846>  For since we believe that Jesus died and rose again, even so, through Jesus, God will bring with him those who have fallen asleep. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1846>For this we declare to you by the word of the Lord, that we who are alive, who are left until the coming of the Lord,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1846> shall not precede those who have fallen asleep.  For the Lord himself will descend from heaven with a cry of command, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1846>with the archangel’s call, and with the sound of the trumpet of God.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1846>And the dead in Christ will rise first; then we who are alive, who are left,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1846> shall be caught up together with them in the clouds to meet the Lord in the air; </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1846>and so we shall always be with the Lord. Therefore comfort one another with these words.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1846> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1846>ALLELUIA								          
Alleluia.  Alleluia.							</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1846>Watch, therefore, and be ready; the son of man is coming at an hour you do not expect.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1846>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"fUQuMRA/TUSeEtK56oxSaw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                      Rev. 5:11-14</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Book of Revelation	
	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I John, looked, and I heard around the throne and the living creatures and the elders the voice of many angels,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> numbering myriads of myriads and thousands of thousands, saying with a loud voice, “Worthy is the Lamb who was slain,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> to receive power and wealth and wisdom and might and honour and glory and blessing!” </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And I heard every creature in heaven and on earth and under the earth and in the sea, and all therein, saying,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> “To him who sits upon the throne and to the Lamb be blessing and honour and glory and might for ever and ever!” </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And the four living creatures said, “Amen!” and the elders fell down and worshipped.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia								</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Christ has risen, who created all things and has had mercy on the human race.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"G6IRUMCYmUiwYyHPE9I4EQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     2 Corinthians 8:7,9,13-15</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the second Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
As you excel in everything – in faith, in utterance, in knowledge, in all earnestness, and in your love for us</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> – see that you excel in this gracious work also.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that though he was rich, yet for your sake he became poor, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>so that by his poverty you might become rich.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>I do not mean that others should be eased and you burdened, but that as a matter of equality your abundance at the present time should supply their want,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> so that their abundance may supply your want, that there may be equality.
As it is written, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>“He who gathered much had nothing over, and he who gathered little had no lack.”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						        See 2 Timothy 1:10</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Our Saviour Christ Jesus abolished death and brought life and immortality to light through the Gospel.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"ALZuUTQQyUeoIyLL3022PQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                           Hebrews 10:11-14,18 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Every priests stands daily at his service, offering repeatedly the same sacrifices, which can never take away sins. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> But when Christ had offered for all time a single sacrifice for sins, he sat down at the right hand of God, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>then to wait until his enemies should be made a stool for his feet. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For by a single offering he has perfected for all time those who are sanctified. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Where there is forgiveness of these, there is no longer any offering for sin.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						           </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Watch at all times, praying that you may be able to stand before the Son of man.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"D5p+1i/dA0W0iNXqTYSlcQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     1Corinthians 15:1-11</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>I would remind you, 
brethren, in what terms I preached to you the gospel, which you received, in which you stand, by which you are saved</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>if you hold it fast – unless you believed in vain. For I delivered to you as of first importance what I also received,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> that Christ died for our sins  in accordance with the Scriptures, that he was buried,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> that he was raised on the third day in accordance with the Scriptures, and that he appeared to Cephas,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> then to the Twelve. Then he appeared to more than five hundred brethren at one time, most of whom are still alive, though some have fallen asleep.
 </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Then he appeared to James, then to all the apostles.  Last of all, as to one untimely born,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> he appeared also to me.  For I am the least of the apostles, unfit to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the Church of God.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>But by the grace of God I am what I am, and his grace toward me was not in vain.  On the contrary,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> I worked harder than any of them, though it was not I, but the grace of God which is with me.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>  Whether then it was I or they, so we preach and so you believed.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Follow me, says the Lord, and I will make you fishers of men.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>L</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006600"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"/L9cAf+mbUquJcz/XObZrQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                            1Corinthians 12:4-11</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>There are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit; and there are varieties of service, but the same Lord;</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and there are varieties of working, but it is the same God who inspires them all in every one.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>To each is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the common good. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>To one is given through the Spirit the utterance of wisdom, and to another the utterance of knowledge according to the same Spirit,</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> to another faith by the same Spirit, to another gifts of healing by the one Spirit, to another the working of miracles, to another prophecy, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>to another the ability to distinguish between spirits, to another various kinds of tongues, to another the interpretation of tongues.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>All these are inspired by one and the same Spirit, who apportions to each one individually as he wills.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               2 Thessalonians 2:14</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>God has called us through the Gospel, to obtain the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"pZ72H7BYzUO4wTrePk4zJw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                         2 Corinthians 5:6-10</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the second Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
We are always of good courage;</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> we know that while we are at home in the body we are away from the Lord, for we walk by faith, not by sight. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> 
We are of good courage, and we would rather be away from the body and at home with the Lord.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>So whether we are at home or away, we make it our aim to please him.
For we must all appear before the judgement seat of Christ, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>so that each one may receive good or evil, according to what he has done in the body.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>The seed is the word of God, the sower is Christ; all who come to him will live for ever.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"DShjHrVXcECLJIw00eQXYQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                           1Corinthians 12:12-30</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Just as the body is one and has many members, and all the members of the body,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> though many, are one body, so it is with Christ.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For by one Spirit we were all baptized into one body- Jews or Greeks, slaves or free – and all were made to drink of one Spirit. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>For the body does not consist of one member but of many. If the foot should say, “Because I am not a hand, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>I do not belong to the body,” that would not make it any less a part of the body. And it the ear should say, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>“Because I am not an eye, I do not belong to the body,” that would not make it any less a part of the body.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>If the whole body were an eye, where would be the hearing? If the whole body were an ear, where would be the sense of smell?</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> But as it is, God arranged the organs in the body, each one of them, as he chose.  If all were a single organ, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>where would the body be? As it is, there are many parts, yet one body.
The eye cannot say to the hand, </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>“I have no need of you,” nor again the head to the feet, “I have no need of you.”
On the contrary,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> the parts of the body which seem to be weaker are indispensable,  and those parts of the body which we think less honourable we invest with the greater honour,</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384> and our unpresentable parts are treated with greater modesty, which our more presentable  parts do not require.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> But God has so adjusted the body, giving the greater honour to the  inferior part, that there may be no discord in the body,</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> but that the members may have the same care for one another.  If one member suffers, all suffer together;</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384> if one member is honoured, all rejoice together.
Now you are the body of Christ and individually members of it.  </s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>And God has appointed in the Church first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then workers of miracles, </s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>then healers, helpers, administrators, speakers in various kinds of tongues.  Are all apostles? Are all prophets? </s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>Are all teachers? Do all work miracles? Do all possess gifts of healing? Do all speak with tongues? Do all interpret?</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 	</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384>					               Luke 4:18</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord has sent me to preach good news to the poor, to proclaim release to the captives.</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"P4OoV81xoUySmZyZFOJlhQ",Verses:[{},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING					Galatians 5:16-25</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Galatians				</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Walk by the Spirit, and do not gratify the desires of the flesh.  </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>For the desires of the flesh are against the Spirit, and the desires of the Spirit are against the flesh;</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384> for these are opposed to each other, to prevent you from doing what you would. 
 
But if you are led by the Spirit you are not under the law.  </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>Now the works of the flesh are plain: immorality, impurity, licentiousness, idolatry, sorcery, enmity,</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384> strife, jealousy, anger, selfishness, dissension, party spirit, envy, drunkenness, carousing and the like.</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>I warn you, as I warned you before, that those who do such things shall not inherit the kingdom of God.</s>"},{ID:20,
Text:"<s1384>But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, self-control;</s>"},{ID:21,
Text:"<s1384> against such there is no law. 
And those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the flesh with its passions and desires.</s>"},{ID:22,
Text:"<s1384>If we live by the Spirit, let us also walk by the Spirit.</s>"},{ID:23,
Text:"<s1384> Let us have no self-conceit, no provoking of one another, no envy of one another.</s>"},{ID:24,
Text:"<s1384>Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:25,
Text:"<s1384>SEQUENCE (poetic text)</s>"},{ID:26,
Text:"<s1384>Come, Holy Spirit, Come!
And from thy celestial home
Shed a ray of light divine!</s>"},{ID:27,
Text:"<s1384>Come, Father of the poor! 
Come, source of all our store!
Come, within our bosoms shine!</s>"},{ID:28,
Text:"<s1384>Thou, of comforters the best;
Thou, the soul’s most welcome guest;
Sweet refreshment here below;</s>"},{ID:29,
Text:"<s1384>In our labour, rest most sweet;
Grateful coolness in the heat;
Solace in the midst of woe</s>"},{ID:30,
Text:"<s1384>O most blessed Light divine,
Shine within these hearts of thine, 
And our inmost being fill!</s>"},{ID:31,
Text:"<s1384>Where thou art not, man has naught,
Nothing good in deed or thought,
Nothing free from taint of ill.</s>"},{ID:32,
Text:"<s1384>Heal our wounds, our strength renew;
On our dryness pour thy dew;
Wash the stains of guilt away:</s>"},{ID:33,
Text:"<s1384>Bend the stubborn heart and will;
Melt the frozen, warm the chill;
Guide the steps that go astray.</s>"},{ID:34,
Text:"<s1384>On the faithful, who adore
And confess thee, evermore
In thy sev’nfold gift descend;</s>"},{ID:35,
Text:"<s1384>Give them virtue’s sure reward;
Give them thy salvation, Lord;
Give them joys that never end. Amen. Alleluia.</s>"},{ID:36,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA				</s>"},{ID:37,
Text:"<s1384>	
							
Alleluia.  Alleluia.</s>"},{ID:37,
Text:"<s1384>Come, O Holy Spirit, fill the hearts of your faithful; and kindle in them the fire of your love.</s>"},{ID:38,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"11M0NvQl7k6hiJy6HEpH3w",Verses:[{
Text:"SECOND READING					 1 Thessalonians 1:1-5b"},{ID:2,
Text:"The beginning of the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians 		"},{ID:3,
Text:"Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, 
To the Church of the Thessalonnians in God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ:
Grace to you and peace."},{ID:4,
Text:"We give thanks to God always for you all, constantly mentioning you in our prayers,"},{ID:5,
Text:" remembering before our God and Father your work of faith and labour of love and steadfastness of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ."},{ID:6,
Text:"For we know, brethren beloved by God, that he has chosen you; for our Gospel came to you not only in word, but also in power and in the Holy Spirit and with full conviction."},{ID:7,
Text:" Word of the Lord"},{ID:8,
Text:"ALLELUIA								          
Alleluia.  Alleluia.							Phillipians 2:15d-16a"},{ID:9,
Text:"You will shine as lights in the world, holding fast the word of life."},{ID:10,
Text:"Alleluia"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"6UWh7KmFCU+A0On0TlKeVQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             1John 5:1-7</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint John		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved:
Every one who believes that Jesus is the Christ has been born of God,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and everyone who loves the parent loves the one begotten by him. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God and obey his commandments. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> For this is the love of God, that we keep his commandments.  </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And his commandments are not burdensome. For whatever is born of God overcomes the world;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and this is the victory that overcomes the world, our faith.  </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Who is it that overcomes the world but he who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>This is he who came by water and blood, Jesus Christ, not with the water only but with the water and the blood. </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> And the Spirit is the witness, because the Spirit is the truth.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>John 20:29
Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>You believed, Thomas, because you have seen me, says the Lord; blessed are those who have not seen and yet believe.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"DLG2V43OK0+A8u5nmMq3OQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     2 Corinthians 12:7-10</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the second Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
To keep me from being too elated by the abundance of revelations, a thorn was given me in the flesh,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> a messenger of Satan, to harass me, to keep me from being too elated.  Three times I begged the Lord about this, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>that it should leave; but he said to me, “My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> 
I will all the more gladly boast of my weakness, that the power of Christ may rest upon me.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For the sake of Christ, then, I am content with weaknesses, insults,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> hardships, persecutions, and calamities; for when I am weak, then I am strong.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						  </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Spirit of the Lord is upon me; he has sent me to preach good news to the poor.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"Re6AlprjzEKt1JiuJs3B+Q",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						 Ephesians 3:2-3a,5-6</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the  Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
I assume that you heard of the stewardship of God’s grace that was given to me for you, how the mystery was made known to me by revelation, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>which was not made known to the sons of men in other generations as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> that is, how the Gentiles are fellow heirs, members of the same body, and partakers of the promise in Christ Jesus through the Gospel.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Matthew 2:2</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>We have seen his star in the east, and have come to worship the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"QXfrzrG/sUKd1M5dVde3Gw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING					 1 Corinthians 15:20-26</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The beginning of the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians  		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
Christ has been raised from the dead,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> the first fruits of those who have fallen asleep. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For as by a man came death,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> by a man has come also the resurrection of the dead. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ shall all be made alive. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> But each in his own order: 
Christ the first fruits,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> then at his coming those who belong to Christ.  </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Then comes the end, when he delivers the kingdom to God the Father after</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> destroying every rule and every authority and power. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> For he must reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet. </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> The last enemy to be destroyed is death.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>When all things are subjected to him,</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> then the Son himself will also be subjected to him who put all things under him,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> that God may be everything to every one. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.							Mark 11:9b,10a</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord! Blessed is the kingdom of our father David that is coming!</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"02p5JyQVHkW4bjfv9GM7hA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						 1 Thessalonians 5:16-24</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Rejoice always, pray constantly, give thanks in all circumstances; for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus for you.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Do not quench the Spirit, do not despise prophesying, but test everything; hold fast what is good, abstain from every form of evil.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>May the God of peace himself sanctify you wholly; </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>and may your spirit and soul and body be kept sound and blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>He who calls you is faithful, and he will do it.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Luke 4:18</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>The Spirit of the Lord is upon me;
He has sent me to preach good news to the poor.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"Yc96JYTvOkmfSS4xtOvJ+Q",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     1Corinthians 12:31- 13:13</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Earnestly desire the higher gifts. 
And I will show you a still more excellent way.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>If I speak in the tongues of men and of angels, but have not love, I am a noisy gong or a clanging cymbal. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> And if I have prophetic powers, and understand all mysteries and all knowledge,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and if I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but have not love, I am nothing. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> If I give away all I have, and if I deliver my body to be burned, but have not love, I gain nothing.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Love is patient and kind; love is not jealous or boastful; it is not arrogant or rude. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Love does not insist on its own way; it is not irritable or resentful; it does not rejoice at wrong, but rejoices in the right.
Love bears all things,</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Love never ends; as for prophecies, they will pass away; as for tongues, they will cease; as for knowledge, it will pass away. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For our knowledge is imperfect and our prophecy is imperfect; but when the perfect comes, the imperfect will pass away.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>When I was a child, I spoke like a child, I thought like a child, I reasoned like a child;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> when I became a man, I gave up childish ways. For now we see in a mirror dimly, but then face to face.
Now I know in part;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> then I shall understand fully, even as I have been fully understood. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>So faith, hope, love abide, these three; but the greatest of these is love.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						              </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The Lord has sent me to preach good news to the poor, to proclaim release to the captives.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"/hRjVWmHREGD6Kx/fffhzA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     1 Corinthians 15:20-27</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians 	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
Christ has been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who have fallen asleep.  For as by a man came death, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>by a man has come also the resurrection of the dead.  For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ shall all be made alive. </s>"},{ID:5},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> But each in his own order: Christ the first fruits, then at his coming those who belong to Christ. 
 </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Then comes the end, when he delivers the kingdom to God the Father after destroying every rule and every authority and power. </s>"},{ID:6},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> For he must reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet.  The last enemy to be destroyed his death.  “For God has put all things in subjection under his feet.” </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                        </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Mary has been taken up into heaven; the host of angels rejoices.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"BnsOMZXpOUeoM2E8V0Lwlg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						               1 John 5:1-9</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint John</s>		"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved: </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>Every one who believes that Jesus is the Christ has been born of God, and every one who loves the parent loves the one begotten by him.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>  By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God and obey his commandments.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>For this is the love of God, that we keep his commandments.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>  And his commandments are not burdensome.  For whatever is born of God overcomes the world;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and this is the victory that overcomes the world, our faith.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Who is it that overcomes the world but he who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>This is he who came by water and blood, Jesus Christ, not with the water only but with the water and the blood. </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> And the Spirit is the witness, because the Spirit is the truth.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>There are three witnesses, the Spirit, the water and the blood; and these three agree.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>If we receive the testimony of men, the testimony of God is greater;</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> for this is the testimony of God that he has borne witness to his Son.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          See John 1:29</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>John saw Jesus coming toward him and said: 
Behold the Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world.</s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"1xRMAwV90kOHQuwaIRQedQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     James 3:16 – 4:3</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint James	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved: 
Where jealousy and selfish ambition exist, there will be disorder and every vile practice. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>But the wisdom from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, open to reason, full of mercy and good fruits,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> without uncertainty or insincerity . and the harvest of righteousness is sown in peace by those who make peace.
What causes wars, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and what causes fightings  among you? Is it not your passions that are at war in your members? You desire and do not have; so you kill.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And you covet and cannot obtain; so you fight and wage war. You do not have, because you do not ask.  You ask and do not receive, because you ask wrongly, to spend it on your passions.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 				
		                 2 Thessalonians 2:14</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>God has called us through the Gospel, to obtain the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"IoYAKO96WEej/Z9QJunqdA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Colossians 3:12-21 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Colossians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Put on, as God’s chosen ones, holy and beloved, compassion, kindness, lowliness, meekness,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> and patience, forbearing one another and, if one has a complaint against another, forgiving each other; </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>as the Lord has forgiven you, so you also must forgive. And over all these put on love, which binds everything together in perfect harmony. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>And let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, to which indeed you were called in the one body.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> And be thankful.  
Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly, as you teach and admonish one another in all wisdom, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>and as you sing psalms and hymns and spiritual songs with thankfulness in your hearts to God.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>And whatever you do, in word or deed, do everything in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Wives, be subject to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.  Husbands, love your wives, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>and do not be harsh with them.  Children, obey your parents in everything, for this pleases the Lord. Fathers, do not provoke your children, lest they become discouraged.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 								               </s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts; let the word of Christ dwell in you richly.</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"zxs9BjR7hUWvQNrJdnrEMA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     James 1:17-18,21b-22,27</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint James	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>My dearest brethren:
Every good endowment and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights with whom there is no variation or shadow due to change.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>  Of his own will he brought us forth by the word of truth that we should be a kind of first fruits of his creatures. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Receive with meekness the implanted word, which is able to save your souls.  But be doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Religion that is pure and undefiled before God and the Father is this:</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> to visit orphans and widows in their affliction, and to keep oneself unstained from the world.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                        James 1:18</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Of his own will he brought us forth by the word of truth that we should be a kind of first fruits of his.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"rvkSIT+Ur06q0plyh4YZMA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                         Romans 4:13, 16-18,22</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Romans		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
The promise to Abraham and his descendants, that they should inherit the world, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>did not come through the law but through the righteousness of faith.
That is why all depends on faith, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>in order that the promise may rest on grace  and be guaranteed to all his descendants –</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> not only to the adherents of the law but also to those who share the faith of Abraham, for he is the father of us all, as it is written, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>“I have made you the father of many nations” – in the presence of the God in whom he believed,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> who gives life to the dead and calls into existence the things that do not exist.  In hope he believed against hope, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>that he should become the father of many nations; as he had been told, “So shall your descendants be.” </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>That is why his faith was “reckoned to him as righteousness.”</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Psalm 68:20
Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>Day after day, may the Lord be blest.  He bears our burdens; God is our Saviour.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"Apsos0h4Dk6Gp6/XLPD1WQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Hebrews 2:9-11 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>We see Jesus, who for a little while was made lower than the angels, crowned with 
glory and honour because of the suffering of death,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> so that by the grace of God he might taste death for every one. For it was fitting that he, for whom and by whom all things exist,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> in bringing many sons to glory, should make the pioneer of their salvation perfect through suffering.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>For he who sanctifies and those who are sanctified have all one origin.
That is why he is not ashamed to call them brethren.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 				
		
               
If we love one another, God abides in us, and his love is perfected in us.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	Hebrews 2:9-11 
"},{Guid:"Cr36E/XvgEORrIhwSeoO5g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING					 1 Thessalonians 5:1-6</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The beginning of the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>As to the times and the seasons, brethren, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>you have no need to have anything written to you. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> For you yourselves know well that the day of the Lord will come like a thief in the night. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> When people say,”There is peace and security,”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> then sudden destruction will come upon them as labour pains come upon a woman with child,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and there will be no escape.
But you are not in darkness, brethren, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>for that day to surprise you like a thief. </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> For you are all sons of light and sons of the day;</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> we are not of the night or of darkness. So then let us not sleep, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>as others do, but let us keep awake and be sober.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.							John 15:4a,5b</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Abide in me, and I in you, says the Lord; he who abides in me bears much fruit.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"aNE6USm0nEurBf4oBq9rjQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     James 2:14-18</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint James	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>What does it profit, my brethren, if a man says he has faith but has not works? Can his faith save him? </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>If a brother or sister is poorly clothed and in lack of daily food, and one of you says to them, “Go in peace,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> be warmed and filled,” without giving them the things needed for the body,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> what does it profit? So faith by itself,if it has no works, is dead.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>But some one will say, “You have faith and I have works.”
 
Show me your faith apart from your works, and I by my works will show you my faith.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>                        Galatians 6:14</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Far be it from me to glory except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by which the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"0+l922b42UCzHto5+SmOtw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     Ephesians 1:3-14</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us in Christ with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly places,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> even as he chose us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and blameless before him.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>He destined us in love to be his sons through Jesus Christ, according to the purpose of his will,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> to the praise of his glorious grace which he freely bestowed on us in the Beloved.  In him we have redemption through his blood, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>the forgiveness of our trespasses, according to the riches of his grace which he lavished upon us.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> For he has made known to us in all wisdom and insight the mystery of his will, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>according to his purpose which he set forth in Christ as a plan for the fullness of time, to unite all things in him, things in heaven and things on earth.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>In him, according to the purpose of him who accomplishes all things according to the counsel of his will, </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>we who first hoped in Christ have been destined and appointed to live for the praise of his glory.  </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>In him you also, who have heard the word of truth, the Gospel of your salvation,</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384> and have believed in him, were sealed with the promised Holy Spirit, </s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>who is the guarantee of our inheritance until we acquire possession of it, to the praise of his glory.</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:17,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						        See Ephesians 1:17-18</s>"},{ID:18,
Text:"<s1384>May the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ enlighten the eyes of our heart that we might know what is the hope to which he has called us.</s>"},{ID:19,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"V0rUTwIm00OhHhV+5baY8w",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Hebrews 4:12-13 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>The word of God is living and active, sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing to the division of soul and spirit, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>of joints and marrow, and discerning the thoughts and intentions of the heart.  And before him no creature is hidden,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> but all are open and laid bare to the eyes of him with whom we have to do.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						
                </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Blessed are the poor in spirit, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"ymnUsK4lDkOU8GJTmq8Rog",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             Philippians 2:6-11</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Philippians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Christ Jesus, though he was in the form of God, did not count equality with God a thing to be grasped, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>but emptied himself, taking the form of a servant, being born in the likeness of men. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> And being found in human form he humbled himself and became obedient unto death, even death on a cross.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore God has highly exalted him and bestowed on him the name which is above every name, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, in heaven and on earth and under the earth,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.	</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>							
Christ became obedient for us unto death, even death on a cross.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore God has highly exalted him: and bestowed on him the name which is above every name.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"XIt0E23/WEGstwMtYrY0Xw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     Ephesians 4:17,20-24</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethen:
This I affirm and testify in the Lord, that you must no longer walk as the Gentiles walk, in the futility of their minds. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>You did not so learn Christ! – assuming that you have heard about him and were taught in him, as the truth is in Jesus. </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> Put off the old man that belongs to your former manner of live and is corrupt through deceitful lusts, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>and be renewed in the spirit of your minds, and put on the new man, created after the likeness of God in true righteousness and holiness.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                      </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds from the mouth of God.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"UBpWeqUTpUyZ1Dglb4e8aQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Hebrews 10:5-10 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
When Christ came into the world, he said “Sacrifices and offerings you have not desired, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>but a body you have prepared for me; in burnt offerings and sin offerings you have taken no pressure.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Then I said, ‘Behold, I have come to do your will, O God,’ as it is written of me in the roll of the book.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>When he said above, “You have neither desired nor taken pleasure in sacrifices and offerings and burnt offerings and sin offerings”</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> (these are offered according to the law), then he added, “Behold, I have come to do your will.”</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>He abolishes the first in order to establish the second.  And by that will have been sanctified through the offering of the body of Jesus Christ once for all.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						               Luke 1:38</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Behold, I am the handmaid of the Lord: let it be to me according to your word.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"NWohOfHRvE2h7K85KdC28g",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                   1John 2:1-5a</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint John		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>My little children, I am writing this to you so that you may not sin; but if any one does sin, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>we have an advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the righteous; and he is the expiation for our sins, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and not for ours only but also for the sins of the whole world.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>  And by this we may be sure that we know him, if we keep his commandments.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>He who says “I know him” but disobeys his commandments is a liar,</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> and the truth is not in him; but whoever keeps his word, in him truly love for God is perfected.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Luke 24:32</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Lord Jesus, open the Scriptures to us; make our hearts burn with love when you speak to us.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF0000FF"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"u5khHDL8OUeAn4u6IJXJZw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                            Philipians 3:17 – 4:1 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Philippians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren, join in imitating me, and mark those who so walk as you have an example in us. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> For many, of whom I have often told you and now tell you even with tears, walk as enemies of the cross of Christ.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Their end is destruction, their god is the belly, and they glory in their shame, with minds set on earthly things. </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> But our commonwealth is in heaven, and from it we await a Saviour, the Lord Jesus Christ, who will change our lowly body to be like his glorious body, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>by the power which enables him even to subject all things to himself. Therefore, my brethren, </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>whom I love and long for, my joy and crown, stand firm in this way in the Lord, my beloved.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> 						                </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>From the shining cloud the Father’s voice is heard: this is my beloved Son, hear him.</s>"},{ID:12}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"aLHdfHnuzkWIXgiX9C7ySA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                                James 5:1-6 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint James	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Come now, you rich, weep and howl for the miseries that are coming upon you. Your riches have rotted and your garments are moth-eaten. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Your gold and silver have rusted, and their rust will be evidence against you and will eat your flesh like fire.  You have laid up treasure for the last days.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>  Behold, the wages of the labourers who mowed your fields, which you kept back by fraud, cry out;</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> and the cries of the harvesters have reached the ears of the Lord of hosts.
You have lived on the earth in luxury and in pleasure;</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> you have fattened your hearts in the day of slaughter.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>You have condemned, you have killed the righteous man; he does not resist you.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>						                 John 17:17b,a</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia </s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Your word, O Lord, is truth; sanctify us in the truth.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"Wl14o2Ry20+0bpJrURVzGA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                         1 Corinthians 15:54-58 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
When the perishable puts on the imperishable, and the mortal puts on immortality, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>then shall come to pass the saying that is written: 
“Death is swallowed up in victory.” O death, where is your victory?</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>O death, where is your sting?” The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.  But thanks be to God,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ. Therefore, my beloved brethren, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing that in the Lord your labour is not in vain.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>You will shine as lights in the world, holding fast the word of life.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF006631"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"prh68kb2DU+Xmw7sYkItxw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING						              Hebrews 9:11-15</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter to the Hebrews		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
When Christ appeared as a high priest of the good things that have come, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>then through the greater and more perfect tent (not made with hands,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> that is, not of this creation) he  entered once for all into the Holy place, taking not the blood of goats and calves but his own blood,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> thus securing an eternal redemption.
For if the sprinkling of defiled persons with the blood of goats and bulls and with the ashes</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> of a heifer sanctifies for the purification of the flesh, how much more shall the blood of Christ, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>who through the eternal Spirit offered himself without blemish to God, purify your conscience from dead works to serve the living God.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore he is the mediator of a new covenant, so that those who are called may receive the promised eternal inheritance, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>since a death has occurred which redeems them from the transgressions under the first covenant.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"l93azJf4aEyZQjRPGmyDog",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             Philippians 2:6-11</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Philippians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Christ Jesus, though he was in the form of God, did not count equality with God a thing to be grasped, but emptied himself,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> taking the form of a servant, being born in the likeness of men.  And being found in human form he humbled himself and became obedient unto death, even death on a cross.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore God has highly exalted him and bestowed on him the name which is above every name, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, </s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>in heaven and on earth and under the earth, and every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>VERSE BEFORE THE GOSPEL</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Ũkumio, rũgooco na gĩtĩo (nĩ ciaku)
Nĩ ciaku Mwathani  (we mũhonokia)
We ciana ciacanjamũkĩra  (ciothe ikiugaga)</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>“Ũrokumio kũu igũrũ”.   (na rĩngĩ)
We ciana ciacanjamũkĩra   (ciothe ikiugaga)
“Ũrokumio kũu igũrũ.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Christ became obedient for us even  to death, even death on a cross.Therefore God has highly exalted him:</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>and bestowed on him the name which is above every name.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF990000"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"59RGo+5blkyIjcOER/ZmWw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                             Romans 8:31b-34</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Romans 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
If God is for us, who is against us?
He who did not spare his own Son but gave him up for us all,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> will he not also give us all things with him?
Who shall bring any charge against God’s elect? It is God who justifies;</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> who is to condemn? Is it Christ Jesus, who died, yes, who was raised from the dead,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> who is at the right hand of God, who indeed intercedes for us?</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          		          </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Glory and praise to you, O Christ.
Glory and praise to you, O Christ.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>From the shining cloud the Father’s voice is heard: this is my beloved son, hear him.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Glory and praise to you, O Christ.</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"yX9b7V5rZk2bmoTlDq0pCg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				            1 Corinthians 10:31- 11:1</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Whether you eat or drink, or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> Give no offence to Jews or to Greeks or to the Church of God,</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384> just as I try to please all men in everything I do, not seeking my own advantage,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> but that of many, that they may be saved. Be imitators of me, as I am of Christ.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          Luke 7:16</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.  Alleluia.								</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>A great prophet has arisen among us, and God has visited his people.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"4r1RSGIK5k2F5ddaSN8Rug",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING					 1 Thessalonians 2:7-9,13</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>The beginning of the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Thessalonians 		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
We were gentle among you, like a nurse taking care of her children.  </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>So, being affectionately desirous of you, we were ready to share with you not only the Gospel of God but also our own selves, because you had become very dear to us.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For you remember our labour and toil, brethren; we worked night and day, that we might not burden any of you,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> while we preached to you the Gospel of God.
And we also thank God constantly for this, that when you received the word of God which you heard from us, </s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>you accepted it not as the word of men but as what it really is, the word of God, which is at work in you believers.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>ALLELUIA								          
Alleluia.  Alleluia.							John 23:9b, 10b</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>You have one Father, who is in heaven; and you have one master, the Christ.</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"BqYhOYmzWEuLgeamnkg6Gg",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                     Ephesians 4:30 – 5:2</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Ephesians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethen:
Do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God, in whom you were sealed for the day of redemption.</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>Let all bitterness and wrath and anger and clamour and slander be put away from you, with all malice, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>and be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, as God in Christ forgave you.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore be imitators of God, as beloved children. And walk in love, as Christ loved us and gave himself up for us, a fragrant offering and sacrifice to God.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						                     
</s>Verse 9
<s1384>I am the living bread which came down from heaven says the Lord; if any one eats of this bread, he will live for ever.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"R+Mou56o2UmxrJ3fL1wBkQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                      Rev. 7:9, 14b-17</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Book of Revelation	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>	
I John, looked, and behold, a great multitude which no man could number, from every nation,</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384> from all tribes and peoples and tongues, standing before the throne and before the Lamb, clothed in white robes,</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> with palm branches in their hands. Then one of the elders said to me, “These are they who have come out of the great tribulation; </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>they have washed their robes and made them white in the blood of the Lamb.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>Therefore are they before the throne of God, and serve him day and night within his temple; and he who sits upon the throne will shelter them with his presence.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>They shall hunger no more, neither thirst any more; the sun shall not strike them, nor any scorching heat.  </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>For the Lamb in the midst of the throne will be their shepherd, </s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>and he will guide them to springs of living water; and God will wipe away every tear from their eyes.”</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord	</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>								John 10:14</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia								</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>I am the good shepherd, says the Lord; I know my own, and my own know me.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"WMXlM1iskkqj88J8NhwB5A",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                              Philippians 4:4-7 </s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Letter of Saint Paul to the Philippians</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren: 
Rejoice in the Lord always; again I will say, Rejoice. Let all men know your forbearance. </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384> The Lord is at hand.  Have no anxiety about anything, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving let your requests be made known to God.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>And the peace of God, which passes all understanding, will keep your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia 						        </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>The Spirit of the Lord is upon me; he has sent me to preach good news to the poor.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{VerticalAlignment:1,Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"EzMQ7KO0YU6ERIoVYIK9cA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                      Rev. 21:1-5a</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the Book of Revelation	</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>	
I John, saw a new heaven and a new earth; for the first heaven and the first earth had passed away, and the sea was no more.</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>And I saw the holy city, new Jerusalem, coming down out of heaven from God, prepared as a bride adorned for her husband; </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>and I heard a great voice from the throne saying, “Behold, the dwelling of God is with men.
 </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>He will dwell with them, and they shall be his people, and God himself will be with them; he will wipe away every tear from their eyes, and death shall be no more, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>neither shall there be mourning nor crying nor pain any more, for the former things have passed away.”
And he who sat upon the throne said, “Behold, I make all things new.”</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord									</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>John 13:34</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia, Alleluia								</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>A new commandment I give you, says the Lord, that you love one another even as I have loved you.</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"ChatBsIaZUumtMmZd2oidQ",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SECOND READING				                            1 Corinthians 1:22-25</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint Paul to the Corinthians		</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Brethren:
Jews demand signs and Greeks seek wisdom, but we preach Christ crucified, a stumbling block to Jews and folly to Gentiles, </s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>but to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ the power of God  and the wisdom of God</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>For the foolishness of God is wiser than men, and the weakness of God is stronger than men.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384> Word of the Lord</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>	          </s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Verse Before the Gospel								John 3:16</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Ũkumio, rũgooco na gĩtĩo (nĩ ciaku)
Nĩ ciaku Mwathani  (we mũhonokia)</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>We ciana ciacanjamũkĩra  (ciothe ikiugaga)
“Ũrokumio kũu igũrũ”.   (na rĩngĩ)</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>We ciana ciacanjamũkĩra   (ciothe ikiugaga)
“Ũrokumio kũu igũrũ.”</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>God so loved the world that he gave his only Son; </s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>that whoever believes in him should have eternal life.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>Ũkumio, rũgooco na gĩtĩo (nĩ ciaku)
Nĩ ciaku Mwathani  (we mũhonokia)
We ciana ciacanjamũkĩra  (ciothe ikiugaga)
“Ũrokumio kũu igũrũ”.   (na rĩngĩ)
We ciana ciacanjamũkĩra   (ciothe ikiugaga)
“Ũrokumio kũu igũrũ.”</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF490099"}}},
Text:"SECOND READING	"},{Guid:"37A4E6ioeEC7Bfqrhnzguw",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>2 nd Reading</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>A reading from the first Letter of Saint John </s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved:</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>See what love the Father has given us, </s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>that we should be called children of God;
and so we are,
 
The reason why the world does not know us is that
it did not know him.</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Beloved, we are God's children now; 
it does not yet appear what we shall be,</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>but we know that when he appears we shall
be like him, for we shall see him as he is.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>And every one who thus hopes in him 
purifies himself as he is pure.</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>The word of the Lord.</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>Alleluia.</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Come to me, all who labour and are heavy
laden, and I will give you rest, says the Lord. </s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>Allelluia.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
Text:"Second Reading
"},{Guid:"Sr76j9jWAEK+ncoOJ/BGwA",Verses:[{
Text:"<s1384>SEKWENSIA</s>"},{ID:2,
Text:"<s1384>(K)  Kristo Paska yetu amechinjwa sadaka, 
	Tuile karamuye na twimbe aleluya</s>"},{ID:3,
Text:"<s1384>Aliyejitoa sadaka ya Paska 
Wakristo wamtolee sadaka ya sifa</s>"},{ID:4,
Text:"<s1384>(K)  	Kristo Paska yetu amechinjwa sadaka, 
	Tuile karamuye na twimbe aleluya</s>"},{ID:5,
Text:"<s1384>Mwanakondoo amewakomboa kondoo: 
Kristo asiye na dhambi 
amewapatanisha na Baba watu wenye dhambi.</s>"},{ID:6,
Text:"<s1384>(K)  	Kristo Paska yetu amechinjwa sadaka, 
	Tuile karamuye na twimbe aleluya</s>"},{ID:7,
Text:"<s1384>Mauti na uzima vimeshindana ajabu:
Mkuu wa uzima aliyekufa, atawala mzima</s>"},{ID:8,
Text:"<s1384>(K)  	Kristo Paska yetu amechinjwa sadaka, 
	Tuile karamuye na twimbe aleluya</s>"},{ID:9,
Text:"<s1384>Utuambie Maria, uliona nini njiani?
Niliona kaburi la Kristo mzima, 
na utukufu wa mwenye aliyekufa:</s>"},{ID:10,
Text:"<s1384>(K)  	Kristo Paska yetu amechinjwa sadaka, 
	Tuile karamuye na twimbe aleluya</s>"},{ID:11,
Text:"<s1384>Mashahidi ni malaika, leso ya uso na mavazi.
Kristo tumaini langu kafufuka: atawatangulia Galilaya.</s>"},{ID:12,
Text:"<s1384>(K)  	Kristo Paska yetu amechinjwa sadaka, 
	Tuile karamuye na twimbe aleluya</s>"},{ID:13,
Text:"<s1384>6.	Twajua Kristo amefufuka kweli katika wafu: ewe Mfalme mshindaji, utuhurumie.
Amina. Aleluya.</s>"},{ID:14,
Text:"<s1384>SHANGILIO	LA INJILI					     1 Wakorintho 5:7b, 8a</s>"},{ID:15,
Text:"<s1384>Aleluya 		Aleluya</s>"},{ID:16,
Text:"<s1384>Kristo, Mwanakondoo wetu wa Pasaka, ametolewa sadaka.  Haya, tuadhimishe sikukuu katika Bwana.</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Transition:0}},
